{"id":1,"text":"HARI\n\nSenior Java Developer\n\nLinkedIn: www.linkedin.com\/in\/hari | Phone: +1 (341)-203-5403 |\nemai:hari1912@gmail.com | New York, NY\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY:\n\n-   10+ years of experience in Java\/J2EE enterprise application\n    development, microservices architecture, and cloud-native solutions\n    across healthcare, financial services, aviation, and e-commerce\n    domains.\n\n-   Designed and developed enterprise-grade microservices using Spring\n    Boot, Spring Cloud, and Java 11\/17, deploying on AWS (ECS, EKS,\n    Lambda) and Azure, with RESTful and gRPC APIs consumed across\n    distributed engineering teams.\n\n-   Built production-grade data orchestration pipelines using Apache\n    Kafka, Apache Spark, and Dagster on AWS, leveraging ECS,\n    EventBridge, Lambda, and S3 to ingest and transform large-scale\n    datasets.\n\n-   Implemented AI\/ML-driven backend services using Java, DSPy,\n    LangChain, and LangGraph, integrating LLM-driven evaluation systems,\n    prompt chaining, and agentic retrieval workflows for code quality\n    metric computation.\n\n-   Engineered robust CI\/CD pipelines using Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes\n    (EKS\/GKE), and AWS CDK, enforcing PCI-DSS, HIPAA, SOX, and GLBA\n    compliance standards in regulated environments.\n\n-   Developed event-driven applications with Apache Kafka, AWS SQS, and\n    AWS EventBridge to enable real-time data ingestion, processing, and\n    asynchronous microservice communication.\n\n-   Expert in ORM frameworks (Hibernate, JPA), working with MySQL,\n    PostgreSQL, Oracle, AWS RDS, and Redshift to design normalized\n    relational schemas and optimize complex queries.\n\n-   Proficient in building observability frameworks using AWS\n    CloudWatch, Prometheus, Grafana, and ELK Stack, with centralized\n    logging, distributed tracing, and data quality alerting across\n    production systems.\n\n-   Led containerization and orchestration initiatives using Docker and\n    Kubernetes, managing Helm charts, resource policies, and multi-AZ\n    deployments for high availability and fault tolerance.\n\n-   Strong background in Agile\/Scrum methodologies, leading sprint\n    planning, design reviews, and cross-functional collaboration with\n    architects, DevOps, and QA teams.\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nCore Java & Frameworks: Java 8\/11\/17, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Spring\nCloud, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, Microservices, REST\nAPIs, gRPC, Multithreading, Design Patterns, JUnit, Mockito\n\nDatabases & Tools: MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle 11g\/10g, MS SQL Server, AWS\nRDS, Amazon Redshift, MongoDB, Cassandra, Teradata\n\nCloud Environment: AWS (EC2, S3, Lambda, ECS, EKS, Glue, RDS, SQS,\nEventBridge, CloudWatch, CDK, SageMaker, Redshift, SNS, ElastiCache),\nGCP (BigQuery, DataProc, GKE, Spanner), Azure (Data Factory, Databricks,\nSQL, Data Lake, Blob Storage, HDInsight, CosmosDB)\n\nBig Data Ecosystem: Apache Kafka, Spark, Spark Streaming, Airflow, Hive,\nHDFS, NiFi, Zookeeper, Sqoop, Flume, MapReduce, Yarn\n\nDevOps & CI\/CD: Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, AWS CDK, Git, GitHub,\nSonarQube, PMD, Maven, Gradle\n\nMonitoring & Observability: Prometheus, Grafana, AWS CloudWatch, AWS\nX-Ray, ELK Stack, Dagster, Collibra\n\nETL & Data Integration: AWS Glue, Informatica PowerCenter 10.x\/9.6,\nTalend 5.6, SSIS, Dagster, Apache Airflow\n\nLanguages & Scripting: Java, Python, Scala, PySpark, SQL, T-SQL, Unix\nShell, TypeScript\n\nML \/ AI Frameworks: DSPy, LangChain, LangGraph, MLflow, MLLIB, NumPy,\nPandas, Scikit-Learn, GPT-4, Claude\n\nReporting & BI: Power BI, Tableau, Splunk\n\nMethodologies: Agile\/Scrum, Waterfall, SDLC, TDD, BDD\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nHumana: August 2023 – Current (Location: Louisville, KY)\n\nRole: Senior Java Developer\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n-   Architected enterprise-grade Spring Boot microservices deployed on\n    AWS ECS and EKS, implementing HIPAA-compliant RESTful APIs for\n    healthcare claims processing, clinical records ingestion, and\n    patient data management across HL7 FHIR interfaces.\n\n-   Designed agentic retrieval workflows using Java, LangChain, and\n    LangGraph to build context-aware agents ingesting PR metadata,\n    commit metadata, and GitHub history, enabling automated CES scoring\n    and quality metric computation for healthcare pipelines.\n\n-   Migrated legacy Apache Airflow orchestration to Dagster across 40+\n    production pipelines processing healthcare claims, clinical records,\n    and patient data on AWS ECS and EKS, implementing retries,\n    backfills, scheduling, and data quality alerts exposed through Power\n    BI and Collibra.\n\n-   Built LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy and Java backend\n    services, integrating prompt optimization and context packing to\n    automate healthcare PR-level scoring using GPT-4, AWS SageMaker, and\n    MLflow for model versioning under HIPAA-compliant governance.\n\n-   Engineered Java Spring Boot backend services with AWS Lambda, AWS\n    EventBridge, and AWS CDK to ingest PR and commit metadata from\n    GitHub and Jenkins, computing CES metrics and exposing results\n    through RESTful APIs and Power BI dashboards under HIPAA compliance.\n\n-   Orchestrated large-scale backfills using Dagster and AWS Glue,\n    processing over 10 million commits and clinical record deltas with\n    batching, caching, and DSPy-based score optimization, with data\n    quality alerts in AWS CloudWatch and Collibra lineage tracking.\n\n-   Implemented SonarQube integration for Java codebase quality scoring,\n    linking static analysis results with GitHub PR metadata to enrich\n    CES metrics, and building Jira-integrated workflows for\n    epic\/work-type classification under HIPAA-compliant metadata\n    governance.\n\n-   Developed AI\/ML pipelines using Java ML integrations and MLLIB to\n    predict patient readmission risk, implementing clinical decision\n    support with LLMs, processing unstructured EHR data, and deploying\n    inference infrastructure on AWS EC2 with HIPAA\/HITECH compliance.\n\n-   Deployed AWS CDK infrastructure-as-code for Java microservices on\n    EC2, EKS, Lambda, and S3, automating provisioning, monitoring, and\n    scaling of Dagster orchestrators, LLM inference endpoints, and AWS\n    Glue jobs ensuring HIPAA compliance.\n\n-   Implemented conversational AI chatbots using LLMs and Java-based AWS\n    EC2 services to automate patient triage and scheduling, integrating\n    with EHR systems through secure API gateways with HIPAA privacy and\n    HITECH compliance.\n\nEnvironment: Java 11\/17, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Hibernate, JPA, AWS\nSageMaker, AWS Lambda, Dagster, Jira, Collibra, NumPy, ERWIN, Pandas,\nMLflow, MLLIB, AWS EC2, AWS RDS, S3, DSPy, Jenkins, EventBridge, Git,\nAWS EKS, LangGraph, AWS CDK, GitHub, Power BI, LangChain, Glue, Airflow,\nECS, SonarQube, Python, Docker, Kubernetes\n\nMorgan Stanley: October 2020 – July 2023 (Location: New York, NY)\n\nRole: Senior Java Developer\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n-   Designed production-grade Spring Boot and Spring Cloud microservices\n    on AWS, ingesting PR metadata, commit telemetry, and code quality\n    signals from GitHub and Jenkins, with PCI-DSS-compliant financial\n    workflows, automated retries, backfills, and observability with\n    metrics, traces, and logs.\n\n-   Built retrieval agents using Java and DSPy to extract historical\n    code context, diffs, and commit histories from GitHub, implementing\n    prompt chaining for LLM optimization, exposing CES and quality\n    metrics via JWT-secured REST APIs with SOX and GLBA-compliant audit\n    trails.\n\n-   Migrated orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster, enhancing\n    PR\/commit linking, branch tracking, and epic linking across Jira,\n    GitHub, and banking systems, integrating AWS EventBridge, SQS, and\n    Lambda with Power BI dashboards maintaining PCI-DSS and SOX\n    compliance.\n\n-   Developed anomaly detection and data quality monitoring using Java\n    Spring services, AWS Glue, and AWS CloudWatch, identifying\n    deviations in commit metadata, PR metadata, and code quality signals\n    from SonarQube and PMD, triggering automated alerts for\n    GLBA-compliant financial workflows.\n\n-   Built Java microservices backend services using Spring Boot on AWS\n    Lambda and EKS to ingest code quality signals from GitHub, Jenkins,\n    SonarQube, and PMD, computing CES metrics exposed via REST APIs with\n    JWT authentication and TLS 1.2+ under PCI-DSS and SOX compliance.\n\n-   Implemented observability using AWS CloudWatch, AWS X-Ray, and Java\n    instrumentation, tracking metrics, traces, and logs across financial\n    pipelines, triggering automated notifications through AWS SQS and\n    Slack, maintaining PCI-DSS, SOX, and GLBA compliance.\n\n-   Developed AWS CDK TypeScript infrastructure templates to provision\n    AWS EC2, VPCs, security groups, IAM roles, and backup policies for\n    loan origination Java systems, enforcing least-privilege access and\n    PCI-DSS\/SOX compliance with version-controlled provisioning\n    pipelines.\n\n-   Implemented AWS WAF rules and Java Spring Security policies for AWS\n    EC2-hosted banking applications, mitigating SQL injection, XSS, and\n    DDoS attacks, integrating CloudWatch monitoring, geo-blocking, and\n    rate-limiting for GLBA compliance.\n\n-   Maintained version control workflows using Git and ERWIN, managing\n    database schema changes, branch strategies, CI\/CD integration, and\n    schema validation, ensuring audit trail consistency and\n    GLBA-compliant governance across customer account and transaction\n    data models.\n\nEnvironment: Java 11, Spring Boot, Spring Security, Hibernate, AWS\nLambda, SonarQube, Dagster, ERWIN, JWT, E\/R Studio, ECS, AWS EC2, AWS\nRDS, Power BI, AWS EKS, AWS WAF, Jira, AWS CDK, DSPy, Python, Glue, AWS\nS3, Git, GitHub, PMD, EventBridge, AWS SQS, Jenkins, Docker, Kubernetes\n\nDelta Airlines: December 2017 – September 2020 (Location: Atlanta, GA)\n\nRole: Java Developer \/ Data Engineer\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n-   Designed and deployed Spring Boot Java microservices with Apache\n    Airflow to ingest commit metadata and PR metadata from GitHub,\n    integrating AWS Lambda and AWS EventBridge for real-time processing,\n    exposing quality metrics via REST APIs with SOC 2 audit trails and\n    FAA\/IATA compliance.\n\n-   Built end-to-end data modeling frameworks using Java, Hibernate, and\n    Python to link PRs and commits, tracking branch merges to main\n    repositories, integrating AWS Glue and Dagster pipelines for\n    historical backfills, and implementing Prometheus\/Grafana dashboards\n    for IOSA-compliant aviation software quality monitoring.\n\n-   Developed analytics platforms using Java Spring REST services, AWS\n    RDS, and Power BI to generate CES metrics correlating PR and commit\n    metadata with Jira epics, designing schemas in ERWIN to support\n    graph-like linking and FAA-compliant safety-critical audit\n    reporting.\n\n-   Implemented backend services using Java on AWS Lambda and AWS EC2,\n    processing thousands of daily PRs and commits, integrating Jenkins\n    CI\/CD pipelines with PMD static analysis, storing data in AWS S3,\n    ensuring IOSA-compliant traceability and FAA version control\n    governance.\n\n-   Built observability frameworks using Prometheus, Grafana, and AWS\n    CloudWatch, tracking Airflow DAG execution times, AWS Glue job\n    success rates, and Lambda invocation patterns, implementing Java\n    audit trail logging for SOC 2 compliance and root-cause analysis.\n\n-   Orchestrated backfills of historical GitHub repository data using\n    Dagster and AWS Glue, reconstructing branch\/main tracking histories,\n    implementing Java-based incremental processing, and detecting\n    duplicate PRs and timestamp inconsistencies for FAA-compliant\n    anomaly detection.\n\n-   Implemented distributed caching using AWS ElastiCache, optimizing\n    frequently accessed aircraft maintenance records, integrating PMD\n    static analysis in CI\/CD pipelines for Java-based aviation systems,\n    ensuring FAA maintenance approval compliance and improving response\n    times for pre-flight inspections.\n\n-   Built flight operations platforms using Java and AWS SQS for\n    asynchronous messaging between microservices handling flight\n    updates, maintenance alerts, and crew notifications, implementing\n    batching strategies for throughput optimization and FAA Part 121\n    operational integrity.\n\n-   Integrated SonarQube with Airflow and AWS Glue, ingesting static\n    analysis metrics into AWS S3, mapping Java code severity to FAA DAL\n    levels, and visualizing defect densities, technical debt, and\n    maintainability indices via Power BI for aviation software\n    compliance.\n\nEnvironment: Java 8\/11, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Hibernate, AWS CDK,\nPython, ERWIN, AWS EC2, EventBridge, GitHub, SonarQube, PMD, AWS Lambda,\nPrometheus, AWS EKS, Dagster, Airflow, AWS WAF, AWS S3, ECS, Glue,\nJenkins, AWS RDS, E\/R Studio, Grafana, Power BI, Git, AWS SQS, Collibra,\nAWS SNS, Jira, Docker\n\nCisco: February 2016 – November 2017 (Location: San Jose, CA)\n\nRole: Java Developer \/ Migration Specialist\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n-   Built a Network Data Integration platform using Java and Azure\n    Cloud, improving enterprise data integration efficiency and enabling\n    seamless data flow across global networking systems by consolidating\n    monitoring telemetry from thousands of devices in international data\n    centers.\n\n-   Developed scalable Java-based data ingestion pipelines integrating\n    Talend ETL and Azure Data Factory, efficiently processing large\n    volumes of network monitoring and security appliance data while\n    ensuring reliable ingestion, transformation, and availability for\n    downstream analytics.\n\n-   Executed data migration initiatives transferring configuration data\n    from legacy network management systems to modern SDN platforms using\n    Java Spring Batch, maintaining configuration accuracy and\n    uninterrupted network services throughout the transition.\n\n-   Built orchestration workflows using Apache Airflow and Java\n    microservices, coordinating ETL processes across distributed network\n    monitoring systems in multiple global regions while aligning\n    execution with regional compliance and time zone requirements.\n\n-   Implemented Azure SQL Database with Java Hibernate ORM to store\n    structured network performance metrics, optimizing data models and\n    query execution to support rapid access to critical network health\n    indicators for operations and engineering teams.\n\n-   Developed predictive capacity forecasting models using Azure\n    Databricks and Java ML integrations, analyzing historical traffic\n    trends to improve bandwidth planning accuracy and support proactive\n    infrastructure investment decisions for global network growth.\n\n-   Built custom Java REST integration APIs enabling connectivity\n    between network management platforms and IT Service Management\n    systems, supporting automated incident creation, updates, and\n    resolution workflows across operational teams.\n\n-   Implemented data security and privacy controls using Java Security\n    frameworks aligned with international regulations, applying\n    encryption, role-based access controls, and data anonymization\n    techniques while handling sensitive network configuration and\n    traffic analysis datasets.\n\nEnvironment: Java 8, Spring Boot, Spring Batch, Spring MVC, Hibernate,\nAzure Cloud, Talend ETL, Azure Data Factory, Apache Airflow, Azure SQL\nDatabase, Azure Data Lake Storage, Azure Databricks, Python, Streaming\nAnalytics, SDN Platforms, Maven, Git\n\nFlipkart: August 2014 – December 2015 (Location: Bangalore, India)\n\nRole: Java \/ ETL Developer\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n-   Built a scalable Java-based ETL pipeline integrating AWS Services,\n    Informatica, and Talend, connecting data from e-commerce platforms,\n    inventory systems, and customer databases to create a unified data\n    flow supporting high-volume daily transaction processing.\n\n-   Developed Java Spring Boot backend services consuming Amazon S3 for\n    secure storage of raw, staging, and transformed product catalog\n    datasets, enabling reliable ingestion workflows for large SKU\n    volumes with versioning and lifecycle policies.\n\n-   Utilized Informatica PowerCenter and Java JDBC to extract data from\n    MySQL, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB sources containing customer profiles\n    and purchase history, ensuring accurate extraction and consistent\n    high-volume processing.\n\n-   Designed AWS Glue jobs with Java-based Spark scripts to catalog,\n    transform, and load curated sales and inventory data into Amazon\n    Redshift, optimizing storage layouts for efficient analytical\n    queries for sales performance insights.\n\n-   Automated ETL job scheduling using AWS Lambda and Amazon CloudWatch\n    Events, improving reliability of time-sensitive processes such as\n    daily sales reporting and inventory refreshes through managed Java\n    execution and dependency handling.\n\n-   Connected Tableau to Amazon Redshift via Java JDBC connectors to\n    deliver interactive dashboards for real-time analysis of sales\n    trends, inventory positions, and customer behavior, enabling\n    data-driven merchandise decisions.\n\nEnvironment: Java 7\/8, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, JDBC, Hibernate, Maven,\nAWS (S3, Glue, Lambda, CloudWatch, Redshift), Informatica PowerCenter,\nTalend, Talend Open Studio, MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Tableau\n\nEDUCATION\n\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science & Engineering – Koneru\nLakshmaiah University, 2010–2014\n","label":[[0,4,"PERSON_NAME"],[6,27,"JOB_TITLE"],[38,64,"LINKEDIN"],[73,90,"PHONE_NUMBER"]