{"id":10,"text":"SANJAY KUMAR\n\nSr. FinTech Data Engineer – 13+ Years\n\nEmail: sanjay.kumar@fintechdata.io  \nPhone: +1 (917) 555-0562  \nLocation: New York, NY  \nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/sanjaykumar-de  \nGitHub: github.com\/skumar  \n\n---\n\nHIGHLIGHTS\n\nExperience: 13+ Years  \nTrading Book: $400B  \nEvents Processed: 5M\/min  \nCertification: FRM  \n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nSenior FinTech Data Engineer with 13 years delivering mission-critical data platforms for investment banks, hedge funds, and payment processors. Expertise in high-frequency trading data pipelines, risk management analytics, regulatory reporting (CCAR, DFAST, MiFID II, Basel III), and real-time market data processing. Proficient in Snowflake, AWS, Apache Kafka, and Python quantitative analytics. Proven experience working with Goldman Sachs, Morgan Stanley, and Two Sigma supporting $1T+ AUM clients.\n\n---\n\nSKILLS\n\nFinTech: FIX Protocol, Bloomberg B-PIPE, Refinitiv, MiFID II, CCAR, DFAST, Basel III, VaR, CVA, FpML  \n\nLanguages: Python, C++, Java, Scala, SQL, SnowSQL, T-SQL, R, MATLAB, Bash, JavaScript  \n\nData Warehousing: Snowflake, AWS Redshift, GCP BigQuery, Sybase IQ, Oracle DW, Teradata  \n\nStreaming: Apache Kafka, Kafka Streams, Apache Flink, Spark Streaming, AWS Kinesis, Redis Streams  \n\nQuantitative: NumPy, pandas, SciPy, statsmodels, QuantLib, Monte Carlo, Black-Scholes, Options Pricing  \n\nCloud: AWS (EMR, Kinesis, SageMaker, S3, Redshift), GCP (BigQuery, Dataflow), Azure (Synapse)  \n\nETL\/ELT: dbt, AWS Glue, Informatica, Talend, Fivetran, SSIS, Matillion, Python frameworks  \n\nDevOps: Git, GitHub Actions, Jenkins, Terraform, Docker, Kubernetes, Helm  \n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nLEAD DATA ENGINEER – MARKET RISK  \nGoldman Sachs  \nNov 2021 – Present  \n\nBuilt intraday risk aggregation pipeline processing 500M+ updates daily using Kafka, PySpark, Snowflake.  \nEngineered low-latency market data ingestion using Bloomberg B-PIPE and Refinitiv (<50ms latency).  \nDesigned CCAR\/DFAST reporting platform reducing cycle from 2 weeks to 3 days.  \nDeveloped quantitative analytics pipeline for 50,000+ securities using Python.  \nBuilt real-time P&L attribution system across 15 risk factors.  \nMigrated Sybase to Snowflake reducing latency by 80%.  \nImplemented FIX protocol message processing for regulatory reporting.  \nAutomated infrastructure using Terraform reducing setup time to 2 hours.  \n\nEnvironment: Snowflake, Kafka, PySpark, Python, AWS, Terraform, Redis, Flink, NumPy, pandas  \n\n---\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER  \nMorgan Stanley  \nMay 2018 – Oct 2021  \n\nBuilt enterprise risk data lake on AWS S3 and Redshift integrating 40+ systems.  \nDeveloped MiFID II reporting pipeline processing 2M+ trades daily.  \nCreated Monte Carlo simulation framework using Python and NumPy.  \nBuilt credit risk analytics for CVA\/DVA\/FVA calculations.  \nDeveloped reconciliation platform reducing breaks by 85%.  \n\nEnvironment: AWS S3, Redshift, Python, Kafka, Airflow, dbt, Jenkins, Tableau  \n\n---\n\nDATA ENGINEER – ALGO TRADING  \nTwo Sigma Investments  \nJan 2015 – Apr 2018  \n\nBuilt tick-level market data pipeline for 5,000+ equities.  \nDeveloped distributed backtesting framework on AWS EMR.  \nCreated alternative data ingestion pipelines for alpha research.  \n\nEnvironment: Python, C++, AWS EMR, Kafka, Spark, HBase, Redis, Hadoop  \n\n---\n\nETL \/ DATA ANALYST  \nCitibank Technology  \nJun 2012 – Dec 2014  \n\nDeveloped ETL pipelines for Basel III regulatory calculations.  \nBuilt reconciliation system processing 500K+ daily transactions.  \nCreated reporting dashboards using SQL Server and SSRS.  \n\nEnvironment: Informatica, SQL Server, Oracle, ETL  \n\n---\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\nCFA Level II Candidate  \nFRM Part I Certified (GARP)  \nAWS Solutions Architect Professional  \nSnowflake SnowPro Core  \nGCP Professional Data Engineer  \nDatabricks Certified Developer  \nSeries 63 License  \nBloomberg Market Concepts (BMC)  \n\n---\n\nEDUCATION\n\nM.S. Financial Engineering – Columbia University – 2012  \nB.Tech. Computer Science – IIT Bombay – 2010  \n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL LINKS\n\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/sanjaykumar-de  \nGitHub: github.com\/skumar  \nSSRN: papers.ssrn.com\/author=sanjay-kumar  \nBloomberg Certification: Available on request  ","label":[[0,12,"PERSON_NAME"],[14,39,"JOB_TITLE"],[42,45,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[60,87,"EMAIL"],[97,115,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[127,139,"LOCATION"],[151,182,"LINKEDIN"],[193,211,"GITHUB"],[243,246,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[353,381,"JOB_TITLE"],[549,565,"SKILL"],[599,603,"SKILL"],[605,610,"SKILL"],[686,695,"SKILL"],[697,700,"SKILL"],[702,714,"SKILL"],[720,727,"SKILL"],[782,789,"COMPANY_NAME"],[797,811,"COMPANY_NAME"],[879,891,"SKILL"],[892,909,"SKILL"],[911,920,"SKILL"],[922,930,"SKILL"],[932,936,"SKILL"],[938,943,"SKILL"],[945,954,"SKILL"],[956,959,"SKILL"],[961,964,"SKILL"],[966,972,"SKILL"],[985,991,"SKILL"],[994,995,"SKILL"],[998,1002,"SKILL"],[1004,1009,"SKILL"],[1011,1014,"SKILL"],[1016,1023,"SKILL"],[1027,1030,"SKILL"],[1032,1033,"SKILL"],[1035,1041,"SKILL"],[1043,1047,"SKILL"],[1049,1061,"SKILL"],[1081,1090,"SKILL"],[1092,1096,"SKILL"],[1096,1104,"SKILL"],[1106,1110,"SKILL"],[1110,1118,"SKILL"],[1120,1129,"SKILL"],[1131,1138,"SKILL"],[1138,1140,"SKILL"],[1142,1152,"SKILL"],[1164,1177,"SKILL"],[1179,1192,"SKILL"],[1194,1206,"SKILL"],[1208,1223,"SKILL"],[1225,1229,"SKILL"],[1229,1236,"SKILL"],[1238,1251,"SKILL"],[1269,1274,"SKILL"],[1276,1282,"SKILL"],[1284,1289,"SKILL"],[1291,1302,"SKILL"],[1304,1312,"SKILL"],[1313,1325,"SKILL"],[1327,1340,"SKILL"],[1342,1357,"SKILL"],[1368,1372,"SKILL"],[1373,1376,"SKILL"],[1378,1385,"SKILL"],[1387,1396,"SKILL"],[1398,1400,"SKILL"],[1402,1410,"SKILL"],[1413,1417,"SKILL"],[1418,1426,"SKILL"],[1428,1436,"SKILL"],[1439,1445,"SKILL"],[1467,1470,"SKILL"],[1472,1480,"SKILL"],[1482,1493,"SKILL"],[1495,1501,"SKILL"],[1503,1511,"SKILL"],[1513,1517,"SKILL"],[1519,1528,"SKILL"],[1530,1537,"SKILL"],[1537,1549,"SKILL"],