{"id":13,"text":"ARJUN MEHTA\n\nSenior Data Engineer | 13+ Years Experience\n\nAtlanta, GA 30301\nEmail: arjun.mehta@techmail.com\nPhone: +1 (678) 555-0143\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/arjunmehta\nGitHub: github.com\/arjunmehta\n\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nSenior Data Engineer with 13+ years designing enterprise-scale ETL\/ELT pipelines, real-time streaming architectures, and cloud data platforms across Snowflake, AWS, Azure, and GCP.\n\nTrack record delivering mission-critical data solutions for Fortune 500 companies including State Farm, Delta Airlines, and UPS.\n\nExpert in DataOps, data governance, and ML pipeline integration. Strong communicator bridging business requirements with technical execution for cross-functional teams.\n\n\nKEY METRICS\n\n- 13+ Years Experience\n- 200+ Pipelines Built\n- $45M Cost Savings\n- 99.98% Pipeline Uptime\n\n\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n\n- Snowflake \/ SnowSQL \/ Snowpipe\n- PySpark \/ Apache Spark\n- Python \/ SQL \/ Scala \/ Java\n- AWS S3 \/ Redshift \/ Glue\n- Azure ADF \/ Synapse \/ Blob\n- GCP BigQuery \/ Dataflow\n- Apache Kafka \/ Pulsar\n- dbt \/ Matillion \/ Talend\n- Airflow \/ Prefect \/ Luigi\n- MLflow \/ scikit-learn \/ TensorFlow \/ PyTorch\n- Terraform \/ CloudFormation\n- Docker \/ Kubernetes\n- React.js \/ FastAPI \/ Flask\n- Collibra \/ Alation \/ Atlas\n- Datadog \/ CloudWatch\n- Git \/ GitHub Actions \/ Jenkins\n\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nSR. BIG DATA ENGINEER | State Farm Insurance\nOct 2022 – Present\nLocation: Bloomington, IL\nDomain: Insurance & Risk Analytics\n\n- Designed end-to-end ETL pipelines using Python, PySpark, Apache Spark ingesting policy and claims data from AWS S3 into Snowflake; reduced processing latency by 55%.\n- Managed real-time streaming with Apache Kafka, Snowpipe, and Snowflake Streams enabling ingestion of 10M+ daily events for actuarial dashboards serving 800+ analysts.\n- Built ML pipelines using scikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch orchestrated via MLflow and deployed with Snowflake Cortex AI achieving 94% accuracy.\n- Automated workflows with Airflow and Jenkins scheduling 200+ ETL\/ELT jobs with 99.98% uptime SLA.\n- Designed secure architecture using Terraform, AWS IAM, and Snowflake RBAC; led SOC 2 Type II compliance.\n- Developed dashboards using React.js, Redux, Zustand, and Plotly integrated with Flask APIs.\n- Modeled enterprise data using dimensional modeling and star schema for $2B+ policy data.\n- Implemented data governance using Collibra and Informatica ensuring GDPR, SOX, and CCPA compliance.\n- Created reusable dbt and Matillion templates reducing development time by 40%.\n- Implemented Snowflake Tasks, Streams, and Kafka for real-time processing.\n- Monitored pipelines using Datadog and CloudWatch reducing costs by $8M annually.\n\nEnvironment:\nPython, PySpark, Apache Spark, AWS S3, Snowflake, Kafka, Snowpipe, dbt, Matillion, MLflow, Airflow, Jenkins, Terraform, Datadog, React.js, Flask, Collibra, Informatica\n\n\nSR. DATA ENGINEER | Delta Air Lines\nDec 2019 – Sep 2022\nLocation: Atlanta, GA\nDomain: Aviation & Transportation\n\n- Built scalable ETL pipelines using Snowflake, Snowpipe, and Fivetran processing 200M+ passenger records.\n- Developed dbt workflows with CI\/CD via GitHub Actions.\n- Engineered batch and streaming pipelines using Python, PySpark, and Spark.\n- Built real-time streaming using Kafka and Pulsar.\n- Designed Azure Data Factory pipelines for analytics across 5 business units.\n- Created dimensional models for flight and customer analytics.\n- Developed FastAPI services for real-time dashboards.\n- Implemented monitoring using New Relic and Azure Monitor.\n- Used Terraform for infrastructure automation.\n\nEnvironment:\nSnowflake, dbt, GitHub Actions, PySpark, Kafka, Prefect, Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse, FastAPI, React.js, Terraform, New Relic\n\n\nDATA ENGINEER \/ DATA ANALYST | UPS\nFeb 2017 – Nov 2019\nLocation: Atlanta, GA\nDomain: Logistics & Supply Chain\n\n- Built ETL pipelines using Snowflake, Snowpipe, and Talend processing 15M+ daily shipment events.\n- Developed dbt workflows and automated CI\/CD.\n- Integrated GCP Dataflow and BigQuery for analytics.\n- Built dashboards using D3.js and React.js.\n- Managed data lineage using Apache Atlas.\n- Automated infrastructure using Terraform.\n\nEnvironment:\nSnowflake, dbt, GitLab CI\/CD, PySpark, Kafka, GCP Dataflow, BigQuery, D3.js, React.js, Terraform\n\n\nDATA ENGINEER | ADP\nJan 2016 – Jan 2017\nLocation: Roseland, NJ\nDomain: HR & Payroll\n\n- Built payroll data integration pipelines using Azure.\n- Developed Talend and ADF pipelines.\n- Migrated legacy systems to Azure cloud.\n- Optimized Azure SQL and Data Lake performance.\n- Built ML models for workforce planning.\n- Implemented SOX-compliant data security.\n\nEnvironment:\nAzure Cloud, Talend, Azure Data Factory, Azure Databricks, Azure SQL, Data Lake, Tableau\n\n\nETL DEVELOPER | Inno Minds Technologies\nMay 2014 – Nov 2015\nLocation: Pune, India\nDomain: Retail & E-Commerce\n\n- Built ETL pipelines using ODI and SSIS.\n- Designed SQL Server data warehouse.\n- Processed XML and Excel POS data.\n- Built SSAS cubes and Power BI dashboards.\n\nEnvironment:\nODI, SSIS, SQL Server, SSAS, Power BI, Oracle, MySQL\n\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nETL\/ELT Tools:\nSnowflake, SnowSQL, Snowpipe, dbt, Matillion, Talend, Informatica, SSIS, AWS Glue, Fivetran, ODI\n\nLanguages:\nPython, PySpark, Scala, Java, SQL, T-SQL, SnowSQL, Bash, JavaScript, TypeScript, R\n\nCloud:\nAWS, Azure, GCP\n\nBig Data:\nApache Spark, Kafka, Pulsar, Airflow, Prefect, Luigi, Hive, NiFi\n\nML\/AI:\nscikit-learn, TensorFlow, PyTorch, MLflow, Snowflake Cortex AI, Pandas, NumPy, XGBoost\n\nMonitoring:\nDatadog, CloudWatch, New Relic, Azure Monitor, Dynatrace, Splunk\n\nGovernance:\nCollibra, Alation, Apache Atlas, Erwin, GDPR, SOX, HIPAA, PCI-DSS\n\nDevOps:\nGit, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI\/CD, Jenkins, Terraform, Docker, Kubernetes, Helm\n\nVisualization:\nTableau, Power BI, React.js, D3.js, Plotly, Looker\n\n\nKEY ACHIEVEMENTS\n\n- Built Snowflake + Kafka platform processing 50M daily events saving $8M annually\n- Migrated UPS system to BigQuery reducing infra cost by 42%\n- Developed ML delay prediction model with 92% accuracy\n- Migrated ADP ETL jobs reducing batch time from 8 hours to 90 minutes\n\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n- AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Professional (2023)\n- Snowflake SnowPro Core (2022)\n- GCP Professional Data Engineer (2022)\n- Azure Data Engineer Associate (2021)\n- Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)\n- HashiCorp Terraform Associate\n- Databricks Certified Developer\n\n\nEDUCATION\n\nM.S. Computer Science – Georgia Tech, 2013\nB.E. Information Technology – Mumbai University, 2011\n\n\nLANGUAGES\n\n- English (Fluent)\n- Hindi (Native)\n- Gujarati (Native)\n\n\nPROFESSIONAL LINKS\n\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/arjunmehta\nGitHub: github.com\/arjunmehta\nPortfolio: arjunmehta.dev\nBlog: medium.com\/@arjunmehta\nAWS Certification: aws.amazon.com\/certification","label":[[0,11,"PERSON_NAME"],[13,33,"JOB_TITLE"],[36,40,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[58,75,"LOCATION"],[83,107,"EMAIL"],[115,132,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[143,169,"LINKEDIN"],[178,199,"GITHUB"],[224,244,"JOB_TITLE"],[250,253,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[345,351,"SKILL"],[373,382,"SKILL"],[384,387,"SKILL"],[389,394,"SKILL"],[400,403,"SKILL"],[498,508,"COMPANY_NAME"],[510,524,"COMPANY_NAME"],[530,533,"COMPANY_NAME"],[546,553,"SKILL"],[576,579,"SKILL"],[722,725,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[834,844,"SKILL"],[846,854,"SKILL"],[856,864,"SKILL"],[867,875,"SKILL"],[877,889,"SKILL"],[892,899,"SKILL"],[901,905,"SKILL"],[907,913,"SKILL"],[915,919,"SKILL"],[922,928,"SKILL"],[931,940,"SKILL"],[942,946,"SKILL"],[949,958,"SKILL"],[961,969,"SKILL"],[971,975,"SKILL"],[978,990,"SKILL"],[993,1001,"SKILL"],[1004,1016,"SKILL"],[1019,1025,"SKILL"],[1028,1032,"SKILL"],[1034,1044,"SKILL"],[1046,1052,"SKILL"],[1055,1063,"SKILL"],[1065,1073,"SKILL"],[1075,1080,"SKILL"],[1083,1090,"SKILL"],[1091,1104,"SKILL"],[1107,1118,"S