{"id":14,"text":"PRIYA KRISHNAMURTHY\nLead Cloud Data Architect\nEmail: [priya.krish@clouddata.io](mailto:priya.krish@clouddata.io)\nPhone: +1 (512) 555-0287\nLocation: Austin, TX\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/priyakrishn\nGitHub: github.com\/pkrishn\n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nCloud Data Architect with 12+ years of experience building enterprise-grade data lakes, real-time streaming platforms, and AI-enabled analytics solutions across Snowflake, AWS, Azure, and GCP. Expert in translating complex business requirements into scalable and cost-effective data architectures. Delivered 50+ successful data engineering projects for Fortune 500 companies. Specialized in optimizing Snowflake workloads with significant cost reduction and high performance. Skilled in PySpark, dbt, Kafka, Airflow, and MLOps tools such as MLflow and Kubeflow.\n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nLEAD CLOUD DATA ARCHITECT\nJPMorgan Chase, New York, NY\nJan 2023 – Present\n\n* Architected enterprise-scale Snowflake platform serving 2000+ analysts processing large-scale transaction data\n* Migrated 400+ legacy ETL jobs to Snowflake and dbt, improving performance and reducing cost\n* Designed real-time fraud detection pipeline using Kafka and PySpark Streaming\n* Built ML feature store integrated with MLflow and SageMaker\n* Implemented data mesh architecture with governance tools\n* Led team of 18 engineers and implemented Agile\/SAFe framework\n* Reduced Snowflake compute costs significantly through optimization strategies\n* Developed self-service analytics platform using React.js and FastAPI\n* Ensured compliance with PCI-DSS and SOX standards\n\nEnvironment: Snowflake, dbt, Kafka, PySpark, MLflow, SageMaker, AWS, React.js, FastAPI, Terraform\n\n---\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER\nWalmart Labs, Bentonville, AR\nMar 2020 – Dec 2022\n\n* Built large-scale AWS data lake supporting thousands of ETL jobs\n* Developed real-time inventory tracking system using Kinesis and Lambda\n* Created reusable PySpark framework for ETL pipelines\n* Implemented ML pipelines for demand forecasting\n* Designed high-availability Redshift architecture\n* Built metadata platform for data lineage tracking\n* Reduced cloud costs using optimization strategies\n\nEnvironment: AWS S3, Glue, Redshift, Kinesis, Lambda, DynamoDB, PySpark, Terraform\n\n---\n\nDATA ENGINEER\nAmerican Airlines, Fort Worth, TX\nJun 2017 – Feb 2020\n\n* Designed Snowflake analytics platform integrating multiple data sources\n* Built real-time streaming pipelines using Azure tools\n* Developed dbt models for financial analytics\n* Managed workflows using Apache Airflow\n* Created dashboards using Power BI\n* Built ETL pipelines using Azure Data Factory\n\nEnvironment: Snowflake, Azure Event Hubs, Airflow, dbt, Power BI, ADF\n\n---\n\nDATA ENGINEER\nCapital One, McLean, VA\nAug 2014 – May 2017\n\n* Built large-scale data pipelines using Hadoop and Spark\n* Developed feature engineering platform for ML models\n* Migrated ETL jobs to PySpark framework\n* Implemented real-time anomaly detection systems\n\nEnvironment: Hadoop, Hive, Spark, Kafka, AWS EMR\n\n---\n\nJUNIOR DATA ANALYST\nInfosys, Hyderabad, India\nJan 2013 – Jul 2014\n\n* Developed SQL reports for banking clients\n* Automated reporting using Python and VBA\n* Assisted in ETL development using SSIS\n\n---\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nData Warehousing: Snowflake, AWS Redshift, BigQuery, Azure Synapse, Teradata, Oracle\nETL \/ ELT: dbt, AWS Glue, Azure Data Factory, Informatica, SSIS\nStreaming: Kafka, Kinesis, Event Hubs, Spark Streaming, Flink\nOrchestration: Airflow, Prefect, Luigi, Dagster\nLanguages: Python, PySpark, Scala, SQL, JavaScript, TypeScript\nML \/ MLOps: MLflow, Kubeflow, SageMaker, TensorFlow, PyTorch\n\n---\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n* AWS Solutions Architect Professional\n* AWS Data Engineer Associate\n* Snowflake SnowPro Core & Advanced\n* GCP Professional Data Engineer\n* Azure Data Engineer Associate (DP-203)\n* Databricks Certified Associate Developer\n* dbt Certified Developer\n* Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)\n\n---\n\nEDUCATION\n\nM.S. Data Science – University of Texas at Austin – 2013\nB.Tech Computer Science – IIT Madras – 2011\n\n---\n\nPUBLICATIONS\n\n* Optimizing Snowflake for Financial Services Data Workloads – Data + AI Summit 2023\n* Real-Time Data Mesh at Petabyte Scale – Kafka Summit 2022\n* MLOps on Snowflake – Snowflake Summit 2022\n* Cost Optimization Strategies for Data Lakes – AWS re:Invent 2021\n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL LINKS\n\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/priyakrishn\nGitHub: github.com\/pkrishn\nBlog: priyakrishn.medium.com\nSpeaker Profile: datasummit.databricks.com\/speakers\/priya\n","label":[[0,19,"PERSON_NAME"],[20,45,"JOB_TITLE"],[53,78,"EMAIL"],[120,137,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[148,158,"LOCATION"],[169,196,"LINKEDIN"],[205,223,"GITHUB"],[278,281,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[328,338,"SKILL"],[413,422,"SKILL"],[424,427,"SKILL"],[429,434,"SKILL"],[440,443,"SKILL"],[654,664,"SKILL"],[739,746,"SKILL"],[748,751,"SKILL"],[753,758,"SKILL"],[760,767,"SKILL"],[773,779,"SKILL"],[793,800,"SKILL"],[804,812,"SKILL"],[845,870,"JOB_TITLE"],[871,885,"COMPANY_NAME"],[887,899,"LOCATION"],[900,918,"WORK_PERIOD"],[951,961,"SKILL"],[1068,1078,"SKILL"],[1082,1085,"SKILL"],[1179,1185,"SKILL"],[1189,1197,"SKILL"],[1215,1218,"SKILL"],[1248,1255,"SKILL"],[1259,1268,"SKILL"],[1371,1376,"SKILL"],[1377,1391,"SKILL"],[1402,1412,"SKILL"],[1522,1531,"SKILL"],[1535,1542,"SKILL"],[1569,1576,"SKILL"],[1581,1585,"SKILL"],[1609,1618,"SKILL"],[1620,1623,"SKILL"],[1625,1630,"SKILL"],[1632,1639,"SKILL"],[1641,1647,"SKILL"],[1649,1658,"SKILL"],[1660,1663,"SKILL"],[1665,1673,"SKILL"],[1675,1682,"SKILL"],[1684,1693,"SKILL"],[1700,1720,"JOB_TITLE"],[1721,1733,"COMPANY_NAME"],[1735,1750,"LOCATION"],[1751,1760,"START_DATE"],[1762,1770,"END_DATE"],[1792,1796,"SKILL"],[1841,1851,"SKILL"],[1893,1901,"SKILL"],[1905,1911,"SKILL"],[1931,1939,"SKILL"],[1939,1949,"SKILL"],[1981,1984,"SKILL"],[2046,2055,"SKILL"],[2186,2192,"SKILL"],[2194,2198,