{"id":15,"text":"RAVI SHANKAR NAIDU\nSenior Telecom Data Engineer\nEmail: [ravi.naidu@telecomdata.io](mailto:ravi.naidu@telecomdata.io)\nPhone: +1 (972) 555-0628\nLocation: Dallas, TX\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/ravishankar-de\n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nTelecom Data Engineer with 14 years of experience building CDR processing systems, network analytics platforms, and 5G data solutions for major telecom carriers. Expert in processing large-scale Call Detail Records using Spark, Kafka, and GCP. Strong knowledge of telecom standards such as 3GPP, IPDR, and CALEA. Experienced in network protocol analysis and real-time network management systems. Delivered analytics solutions for major telecom companies, driving significant cost savings through network optimization.\n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER – 5G ANALYTICS\nAT&T\nMar 2021 – Present\n\n* Built 5G analytics platform processing billions of daily network events using GCP Pub\/Sub and Dataflow\n* Designed CDR processing pipelines using Spark and BigQuery for network analytics\n* Developed real-time anomaly detection using Flink and machine learning models\n* Built subscriber experience analytics platform for large-scale telecom data\n* Implemented CALEA-compliant data platform with audit and retention policies\n* Developed ML models for network capacity planning and optimization\n* Reduced cloud costs through BigQuery optimization strategies\n* Led team of 12 data engineers\n\nEnvironment: GCP BigQuery, Pub\/Sub, Dataflow, Vertex AI, Flink, Spark, Python, PySpark, dbt, Kafka, Terraform\n\n---\n\nDATA ENGINEER – NETWORK ANALYTICS\nVerizon Communications\nJun 2017 – Feb 2021\n\n* Built IPDR processing platform on AWS EMR handling large-scale network data\n* Developed fraud detection pipelines using SageMaker\n* Created network performance analytics using Spark\n* Built churn prediction models for telecom customers\n* Implemented real-time spectrum management analytics using Kafka and Flink\n\nEnvironment: AWS EMR, S3, SageMaker, Kafka, Spark, PySpark, MLflow, Airflow, Redshift\n\n---\n\nDATA ENGINEER – CDR ANALYTICS\nT-Mobile US\nJan 2014 – May 2017\n\n* Built high-volume CDR processing pipelines using Hadoop and HBase\n* Developed roaming analytics using NRTRDE standards\n* Created prepaid analytics systems for telecom revenue tracking\n\n---\n\nETL DEVELOPER\nEricsson Consulting\nStockholm \/ Dallas\n\n* Developed telecom data integration solutions using Informatica and ODI\n* Built network inventory data warehouse integrating multi-vendor systems\n\n---\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nTelecom: 3GPP, CDR, IPDR, NRTRDE, CALEA, SS7, Diameter, SIP, OSS\/BSS\nCloud: GCP (BigQuery, Pub\/Sub, Dataflow), AWS (EMR, S3, SageMaker, Redshift)\nBig Data: Spark, PySpark, Kafka, Flink, Hadoop, Hive, HBase, Presto\nLanguages: Python, Java, Scala, SQL, R, Bash\nML\/Analytics: scikit-learn, MLflow, SageMaker, TensorFlow, XGBoost\n\n---\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n* GCP Professional Data Engineer\n* GCP Professional Cloud Architect\n* AWS Solutions Architect Professional\n* AWS Machine Learning Specialty\n* Confluent Certified Developer for Apache Kafka\n* Databricks Certified Data Engineer Professional\n\n---\n\nEDUCATION\n\nM.S. Telecommunications Engineering – University of Texas at Dallas – 2011\nB.E. Electronics and Communication – VIT University – 2009\n\n---\n\nPROFESSIONAL LINKS\n\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/ravishankar-de\nGitHub: github.com\/rsnaidu\nBlog: telecomdata.medium.com\n","label":[[0,18,"PERSON_NAME"],[19,47,"JOB_TITLE"],[56,81,"EMAIL"],[90,115,"EMAIL"],[125,141,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[152,162,"LOCATION"],[172,203,"LINKEDIN"],[232,254,"JOB_TITLE"],[259,262,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[291,295,"SKILL"],[315,333,"SKILL"],[453,458,"SKILL"],[460,465,"SKILL"],[471,474,"SKILL"],[522,526,"SKILL"],[528,532,"SKILL"],[538,543,"SKILL"],[560,577,"SKILL"],[600,618,"SKILL"],[668,676,"SKILL"],[728,736,"SKILL"],[781,816,"JOB_TITLE"],[817,821,"COMPANY_NAME"],[822,840,"WORK_PERIOD"],[900,915,