{"id":22,"text":"NAME: Raju\nROLE: AWS DevOps Engineer\n\nLocation: New York, USA\nPhone: +1 800-667-6389\nEmail: raju@salesforce.com\nLinkedIn: https:\/\/linkedin.com\/in\/salesforcechange\nGitHub: https:\/\/github.com\/rajue\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n------------------------------------------------------------\nSenior Salesforce Change Manager, AWS DevOps Engineer, and Data Engineer with 10+ years of experience designing, deploying, and supporting enterprise CRM, cloud, and data platforms.\n\nExpertise in Salesforce release management, AWS DevOps automation, CI\/CD pipelines, and large-scale data integration architectures. Proven track record of delivering secure, scalable, and highly available solutions across Finance, Healthcare, Insurance, and Telecommunications domains.\n\nStrong background in production release management, infrastructure automation, and supporting mission-critical applications in regulated environments.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n------------------------------------------------------------\nSalesforce Change Management\nAWS DevOps Engineering\nCI\/CD Automation\nSalesforce Integrations\nCloud Data Engineering\nInfrastructure as Code\nETL and Data Pipelines\nData Governance and Security\nRelease Management\nProduction Support\nAgile and Scrum\nCloud Architecture\nBlue-Green Deployment\nCapacity Planning\nIncident Management\nRoot Cause Analysis\nProblem Management\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n------------------------------------------------------------\nSalesforce:\nSales Cloud, Service Cloud, Experience Cloud, DevOps Center, Change Sets, Data Loader\nSalesforce REST API, Bulk API, SOQL, Apex (basic), Reports, Dashboards, Sandbox Strategy\n\nCloud (AWS):\nEC2, S3, RDS, Aurora, DynamoDB, Redshift, Lambda, Glue, Step Functions, Kinesis\nIAM, VPC, Route53, API Gateway, CloudFront\n\nCI\/CD and Automation:\nJenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI\/CD, Azure DevOps\nTerraform, CloudFormation, AWS CDK\nDocker, Kubernetes, Helm, ArgoCD\n\nObservability:\nCloudWatch, Prometheus, Grafana, ELK Stack, OpenSearch\nDatadog, New Relic, Splunk\n\nSecurity and Governance:\nIAM, RBAC, SSO, MFA, OAuth, SAML\nSecrets Manager, KMS, WAF, Shield, GuardDuty, Inspector\nCompliance: SOX, HIPAA, SOC2, PCI-DSS\n\nResilience:\nAuto Scaling, Blue-Green Deployment, Canary Deployment\nMulti-region DR, Backup and Restore, Chaos Engineering\n\nScripting:\nPython, Bash, PowerShell\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCERTIFICATIONS\n------------------------------------------------------------\nSalesforce Certified Administrator\nSalesforce Certified Platform App Builder\nSalesforce Certified DevOps Engineer\nSalesforce Certified Data Cloud Consultant\n\nAWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate\nAWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional\n\nMicrosoft Azure Data Engineer\nSnowflake SnowPro Advanced\nDatabricks Data Engineer Professional\nITIL v4 Foundation\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nClient: Morgan Stanley, New York, NY\nRole: Senior Salesforce Change Manager \/ AWS DevOps and Data Engineer\nDuration: 2022 – Present\n\n• Managed end-to-end Salesforce change lifecycle including analysis, approvals, deployment, and validation\n• Maintained enterprise release calendars and coordinated cross-functional teams\n• Built Salesforce data pipelines using REST API, Bulk API, and Streaming API\n• Developed ETL frameworks using AWS Glue, Lambda, Airflow, and dbt\n• Implemented CI\/CD pipelines using Jenkins, GitHub, and Salesforce DevOps Center\n• Built Infrastructure as Code using Terraform and CloudFormation\n• Managed sandbox strategy, data masking, and test data setup\n• Led large-scale CRM data migrations (50M+ records)\n• Designed reconciliation frameworks for data validation\n• Implemented Salesforce security and governance policies\n• Built dashboards using Power BI and Salesforce analytics\n• Configured monitoring using CloudWatch and Splunk\n• Provided production support, incident management, and RCA\n• Optimized API performance and implemented blue-green deployments\n• Mentored junior engineers and documented processes\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nClient: Humana, Louisville, KY\nRole: Salesforce Data Engineer \/ DevOps Engineer\nDuration: 2019 – 2022\n\n• Built Salesforce ingestion pipelines using Azure Data Factory\n• Integrated Salesforce with Azure SQL, Data Lake, and Databricks\n• Managed release cycles, UAT, and deployments\n• Developed data quality frameworks and reconciliation reports\n• Implemented HIPAA-compliant security controls\n• Automated data pipelines using Python and Salesforce APIs\n• Built Power BI dashboards and analytics datasets\n• Implemented CI\/CD pipelines and monitoring systems\n• Optimized queries and performance\n• Supported audits and compliance\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nClient: Great American Insurance, Cincinnati, OH\nRole: Salesforce Integration Engineer\nDuration: 2017 – 2019\n\n• Built Salesforce integrations with AWS and Snowflake\n• Developed batch and streaming pipelines using Kafka and Spark\n• Implemented CI\/CD pipelines using Terraform and Jenkins\n• Built monitoring, retry mechanisms, and reconciliation scripts\n• Optimized performance and supported production releases\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nClient: AT&T, Dallas, TX\nRole: Salesforce Data Engineer\nDuration: 2015 – 2016\n\n• Built analytics pipelines using BigQuery and Dataflow\n• Integrated Salesforce with telecom systems\n• Developed ingestion pipelines and reporting dashboards\n• Implemented data security and performance tuning\n\n----------------------------------