{"id":23,"text":"OLIVIA OGILVY\nSenior Python Developer | Backend Engineer | ML & Data Systems Specialist\nolivia@novoresume.com | (555) 123-4567 | Los Angeles, CA 90291 | linkedin.com\/in\/oliviaogilvy | github.com\/oliviaogilvy\n\nExperience Overview:\n14+ Years of Experience\n90+ Python Projects Delivered\n70+ APIs & Services Built\n25+ ML Models Deployed\nTeam Members Led: 40+\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nVersatile and results-driven Senior Python Developer with 14+ years of experience building high-performance backend systems, data pipelines, RESTful APIs, and machine learning solutions across financial services, e-commerce, healthcare, and SaaS industries. Expert in Python 3.x, Django, FastAPI, Flask, and the scientific Python ecosystem (NumPy, pandas, scikit-learn, PyTorch). Proven ability to architect scalable, cloud-native systems on AWS, GCP, and Azure serving millions of users and processing billions of data points.\nRecognized for reducing API latency by 65%, cutting infrastructure costs by 40%, and shipping ML models generating $3M+ in business value. Experienced technical leader, open source contributor, and conference speaker. Passionate about clean Pythonic code, TDD, MLOps best practices, and mentoring Python engineers.\n\nCORE COMPETENCIES\nPython 3.x (Expert) | Django & DRF | FastAPI & Flask\nRESTful & GraphQL APIs | Machine Learning (scikit-learn) | Deep Learning (PyTorch\/TF)\nData Engineering (pandas\/Spark) | Cloud-Native Development | Docker & Kubernetes\nAsync Python (asyncio\/aiohttp) | CI\/CD & DevOps | SQL & NoSQL Databases\nMLOps & Model Deployment | Test-Driven Development | Apache Kafka & Celery\nData Visualization | Agile\/Scrum Leadership | Technical Mentoring & Training\n\nCAREER HIGHLIGHTS & KEY ACHIEVEMENTS\n- 65% API Latency Reduction at Sweet Oranges Technology\n- $3M+ Revenue Impact via recommendation engine at BZG Bank\n- 40% Infrastructure Cost Reduction at KCR Industries\n- 25 ML Models in Production across fraud, forecasting, NLP\n- 85% Manual Work Eliminated at Five Brothers Marketing\n- 10x Data Processing Speed using Polars\/Dask at Mediterraneo Group\n- Zero-Downtime Migration of 6TB PostgreSQL to Aurora\n- 99.97% API Uptime via multi-region FastAPI deployment\n- 60% Faster Model Delivery using MLflow & Airflow\n- 5,000+ Developers Reached via PyCon US & EuroPython talks\n- Open Source Impact: python-api-toolkit (8,000+ stars) & fastapi-auth-middleware (7,200+ stars)\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\nSenior Python Developer \/ Backend Architect | Sweet Oranges Technology\nMar 2018 – Present | Los Angeles, CA\n- Migrated Django monolith to 18 FastAPI microservices\n- Built async REST APIs handling 40,000+ req\/sec with <100ms latency\n- Event-driven architecture with Kafka, 150M+ events\/day\n- OAuth2\/JWT auth layer using python-jose\/Authlib\n- Redis caching, PostgreSQL optimization, MLOps pipeline (MLflow\/Airflow)\n- AWS ECS\/EKS deployment, TDD culture (pytest, Testcontainers)\n- Mentored 6 Python developers; built internal SDK\n\nSenior Python Developer \/ Data Engineer | KCR Industries\nMar 2014 – Feb 2018 | Dallas, TX\n- FastAPI microservices on AWS ECS; saved $150K\/year\n- ETL pipelines with pandas, SQLAlchemy, Airflow\n- IoT sensor data processing via Python + Kafka\n- Predictive maintenance ML models (scikit-learn\/XGBoost)\n- REST APIs (FastAPI + Swagger); Celery + Redis for background tasks\n- Docker\/Kubernetes deployment on Azure AKS; Helm & ArgoCD\n\nPython Developer \/ Full Stack Engineer | Five Brothers Digital Marketing\nFeb 2009 – Feb 2014 | Austin, TX\n- Core campaign management platform (Django, Celery, PostgreSQL)\n- Python API integrations with Google Ads, Meta Ads, Salesforce\n- Automated reporting engine (pandas, ReportLab)\n- Multi-touch attribution, real-time A\/B testing framework\n- GitHub workflows, pytest testing; test coverage 70%\n\nPython Developer \/ Integration Engineer | Mediterraneo Group\nSep 2018 – Dec 2019 | New York, NY\n- Rewrote pandas ETL with Polars\/Dask (10x throughput)\n- FastAPI contract lifecycle service; Kafka consumer pipelines\n- Bank reconciliation automation; SWIFT MT parser\n- NLP document processing pipeline with spaCy & HuggingFace\n\nSenior Python Developer \/ Platform Lead | Resume Worded \/ GrowthSI\n2012 – 2018 | New York, NY\n- Multi-tenant Django SaaS platform; fraud scoring microservice\n- Churn prediction ML model (scikit-learn\/XGBoost)\n- Financial reporting API; cookiecutter scaffolding tool\n- GitHub Actions CI\/CD pipelines; technical due diligence\n\nPython Developer \/ ML Engineer | BZG Bank\nJan 2013 – Mar 2017 | Los Angeles, CA\n- Recommendation engine (collaborative filtering, matrix factorization)\n- Credit risk scoring ML model (scikit-learn, LightGBM)\n- Real-time fraud detection with Kafka + online learning\n- Automated regulatory reporting (pandas + Jinja2)\n- ATM reconciliation, PostgreSQL migration, data quality monitoring\n\nJunior Python Developer \/ Data Analyst | Cobb & Associates\nJan 2011 – Dec 2012 | San Diego, CA\n- Flask web app for client financial management\n- ETL scripts with pandas + SQLAlchemy; AR aging reports\n- Automated financial statements; pytest introduction\n\nJunior Python Developer \/ Analyst Intern | ABC Company\n2008 – 2011 | Sometown, CO\n- Tax automation scripts; stock option tracking\n- Audit sampling & financial analysis (pandas, NumPy)\n- SOX compliance documentation; QuickBooks migration\n\nEDUCATION\nM.Sc. in Computer Science – Machine Learning & Intelligent Systems | Northeastern University\n2016 – 2018 | Boston, MA | GPA: 3.9\/4.0\n- Thesis: \"Adaptive Online Learning for Real-Time Financial Fraud Detection Using Python\" (ACM KDD Workshop 2018)\n- Graduate Research Assistant & Teaching Assistant\n\nB.Sc. in Computer Science | University of Florida\n2005 – 2008 | Gainesville, FL | GPA: 3.85\/4.0 | Summa Cum Laude\n- Minor: Statistics & Applied Mathematics\n- Senior Project: Python distributed web crawler\/search engine (Best Capstone)\n\nCareer Certificate: Machine Learning & AI Engineering | American University in Cairo (Online)\nFeb 2020 – Present\n- Deep Learning (PyTorch), Transformers (HuggingFace), MLOps (MLflow, Kubeflow), AWS SageMaker\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\nAWS Certified Developer – Associate | 2021, Renewed 2023\nAWS Certified ML – Specialty | 2022\nGoogle Professional ML Engineer | 2022\nMicrosoft Azure AI Engineer Associate | 2021\nCertified Kubernetes Application Developer (CKAD) | 2020\nDatabricks Certified ML Professional | 2022\nTensorFlow Developer Certificate | 2020\nMongoDB Certified Python Developer | 2019\nCertified Data Management Professional (CDMP) | 2019\nLean Six Sigma Green Belt | 2016\nCertified ScrumMaster (CSM) | 2015, Renewed 2021\nQualified Financial Accountant (QFA) | 2018\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n- Python 3.x, FastAPI, Django\/DRF, Flask, Celery, asyncio, httpx, Pydantic\n- ML: scikit-learn, PyTorch, TensorFlow, HuggingFace, XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost\n- Data: pandas, NumPy, Polars, Dask, Spark\/PySpark, Airflow, Kafka, dbt, Great Expectations\n- Cloud\/DevOps: AWS, GCP, Azure, Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, ArgoCD\n- Databases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB, Redis, Elasticsearch\n- Testing: pytest, Testcontainers, Hypothesis, CI\/CD, OpenTelemetry, Sentry\n- Languages: English (native), French (C1), Spanish (B2), German (B1), Mandarin (A2)\n\nLEADERSHIP & TEACHING\n- Conference Speaker: PyCon US 2021, EuroPython 2022\n- Technical Blog: Medium \/ oliviaogilvy.dev\n- Senior Python Mentor: Udemy, Springboard, Corporate Workshops\n- Open Source Contributor & Maintainer: python-api-toolkit, fastapi-auth-middleware, PyPI\n\nKEY PROJECTS\n- ML Recommendation Engine (BZG Bank)\n- Monolith-to-Microservices Migration (Sweet Oranges Technology)\n- MLOps Platform (Sweet Oranges Technology)\n- Real-Time Fraud Detection (BZG Bank)\n- NLP Document Processing Pipeline (Mediterraneo Group)\n- Financial Reporting Automation (KCR Industries)\n\nPUBLICATIONS & PRESENTATIONS\n- EuroPython 2022,