{"id":25,"text":"MANASA\nSr. Big Data Engineer\n+1 (341) 203-5403 | Manasa1912@gmail.com | linkedin.com\/in\/manasa | New York, NY\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nResults-driven Sr. Big Data Engineer with 10+ years of experience designing and deploying production-grade data pipelines, agentic AI\/LLM systems, and cloud-native architectures across healthcare, finance, aviation, and technology sectors. Expert in Python, Apache Spark, AWS, Azure, Dagster, DSPy, LangChain, and distributed systems. Proven track record of leading complex migrations, building HIPAA\/PCI-DSS\/SOX-compliant platforms, and delivering scalable solutions processing millions of records daily. Deep expertise in LLM prompt optimization, NER-based metadata classification, and real-time streaming architectures.\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nProgramming Languages: Python, Scala, Java, PySpark, SQL, T-SQL, Unix, Spring Boot\n\nCloud Platforms:\n- AWS (S3, Glue, EMR, Lambda, ECS, EKS, EC2, RDS, Redshift, SageMaker, CDK, EventBridge, CloudWatch, SQS, SNS)\n- GCP (BigQuery, DataProc, GKE, Spanner, Cloud Functions)\n- Azure (Data Factory, Databricks, SQL, Data Lake, Blob Storage, HDInsight, CosmosDB)\n\nBig Data Ecosystem:\nApache Spark, Kafka, Airflow, Hive, HDFS, NiFi, Spark Streaming, Zookeeper, Sqoop, Flume, MapReduce, Yarn, Dagster\n\nDatabases:\nTeradata, MySQL, Oracle, MS SQL Server, MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Snowflake\n\nETL Tools:\nAWS Glue, Informatica PowerCenter, Talend, SSIS, Semarchy xDM\n\nML \/ AI Frameworks:\nDSPy, LangChain, LangGraph, MLflow, MLLIB, NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-Learn, Gradient Boosting, Random Forest, Logistic Regression\n\nDevOps & CI\/CD:\nDocker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, Git, AWS CDK, SonarQube, PMD\n\nBI & Reporting:\nTableau, Power BI, Grafana, Prometheus, Collibra, Splunk\n\nCompliance & Methodologies:\nAgile, Waterfall, SDLC, HIPAA, HITECH, PCI-DSS, SOX, GLBA, SOC 2, FAA\/IATA\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nSr. Big Data Engineer | Humana\nAugust 2023 – Present | Louisville, KY\n- Designed agentic retrieval workflows using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph for context-aware systems.\n- Migrated orchestration from Airflow to Dagster across 40+ pipelines.\n- Built LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy, GPT-4, Claude, and MLflow.\n- Developed backend services using AWS Lambda, EventBridge, and CDK.\n- Processed 10M+ commits and healthcare records using AWS Glue and Dagster.\n- Implemented SonarQube integrations for code quality scoring.\n- Built monitoring using CloudWatch and Dagster sensors.\n- Developed ML pipelines for patient readmission prediction.\n- Built conversational AI chatbots for healthcare automation.\n\nSr. Data Engineer | Morgan Stanley\nOctober 2020 – July 2023 | New York, NY\n- Built production pipelines using Python and Dagster on AWS.\n- Developed retrieval agents using DSPy for LLM optimization.\n- Migrated Airflow workflows to Dagster.\n- Implemented anomaly detection and monitoring using AWS services.\n- Built REST APIs using AWS Lambda and EKS.\n- Designed evaluation pipelines for LLM optimization.\n- Implemented AWS WAF security and compliance controls.\n- Developed infrastructure using AWS CDK.\n\nData Engineer \/ Data Analyst | Delta Airlines\nDecember 2017 – September 2020 | Atlanta, GA\n- Built data pipelines using Python and Airflow.\n- Developed data models linking PR and commit metadata.\n- Integrated SonarQube and AWS data lakes.\n- Built dashboards using Power BI.\n- Implemented monitoring using Prometheus and Grafana.\n\nData Engineer \/ Migration Specialist | Cisco\nFebruary 2016 – November 2017 | San Jose, CA\n- Built Azure-based data integration platform.\n- Developed pipelines using Talend and Azure Data Factory.\n- Executed large-scale data migrations.\n- Built Airflow workflows for orchestration.\n- Developed forecasting models using Databricks.\n\nETL Developer | Flipkart\nAugust 2014 – December 2015 | Bangalore, India\n- Built ETL pipelines using AWS, Informatica, and Talend.\n- Developed AWS Glue jobs and Redshift in