{"id":26,"text":"YUKI TANAKA\nVP of Design \/ Head of Product Design\nEmail: yuki.tanaka@uxdesign.pro\nPhone: +1 (415) 672-0049\nLocation: San Francisco, CA 94105\nAddress: 188 Spear Street, San Francisco, CA 94105\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/yuki-tanaka-pro\n\nSUMMARY\nAward-winning design executive with 13+ years crafting transformative digital experiences used by 200M+ people globally. Led product design at Airbnb, Apple, and Figma, building and scaling world-class design systems, research programs, and design organizations. Expert in 0→1 product design, design systems architecture, accessibility-first design, and inclusive design cultures. Recipient of Fast Company Innovation by Design Gold (2023), Webby Award Best UX (2022), and Apple Design Award (2017). MFA from Rhode Island School of Design.\n\nSKILLS & EXPERTISE\n\nDesign Disciplines:\nInteraction Design, Visual Design, UX Research, Design Systems, Motion Design, Service Design, Accessibility\n\nLeadership:\nDesign Org Building, Creative Direction, Roadmap Ownership, Cross-functional Partnership, Design Critique\n\nResearch Methods:\nUsability Testing, Journey Mapping, Jobs-to-be-Done, Diary Studies, A\/B Testing, Quant Research\n\nTools:\nFigma (Expert), Framer (Expert), Principle (Advanced), After Effects (Advanced), Sketch (Expert), ProtoPie\n\nPrototyping \/ Code:\nReact (Proficient), HTML\/CSS, TypeScript (Basic), Storybook, Lottie\n\nAnalytics:\nAmplitude, Mixpanel, FullStory, Hotjar, Heap, Maze, UserTesting\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n- Nielsen Norman UX Certified (2020)\n- Google UX Design Professional (2021)\n- Interaction Design Foundation – Advanced (2019)\n- CPACC Accessibility Certification (2022)\n\nWORK EXPERIENCE\n\nAirbnb — VP of Product Design\nApr 2021 – Present | San Francisco, CA\n- Lead 75-person product design organization across Homes, Experiences, and Host Platform.\n- Launched “Reimagined Airbnb” (2023): +24% conversion, $840M incremental GMV.\n- Built Airbnb Design System (ADS 3.0) with 1,800+ components.\n- Achieved WCAG 2.1 AAA accessibility across 12 core journeys.\n- Scaled team from 38 to 75, reduced attrition from 22% to 7%.\n- Launched AI UX research program for trust and explainability.\n\nStack: Figma, Framer, Lottie, Storybook, React, TypeScript, Maze, FullStory, Amplitude\n\nFigma — Design Director, Product Design\nJul 2018 – Mar 2021 | San Francisco, CA\n- Led team of 28 designers across core product areas.\n- Shipped FigJam (0→1), reached 3M MAU in 6 months.\n- Built Spectrum Design System (1,200+ components).\n- Scaled team and established design research function.\n\nStack: Figma, Principle, After Effects, React, Storybook\n\nApple Inc. — Senior UX Designer\nAug 2013 – Jun 2018 | Cupertino, CA\n- Core UX designer for iOS 10–13 (1.2B+ devices).\n- Led Control Center redesign (iOS 11), Apple Design Award 2017.\n- Designed Apple Maps transit navigation for 22 cities.\n- Filed 3 design patents on gesture interactions.\n\nStack: Sketch, Keynote, Xcode, Motion, Swift\n\nIDEO — UI\/UX Designer\nJun 2011 – Jul 2013 | San Francisco, CA\n- Delivered human-centered design for Fortune 500 clients.\n- Led design sprints resulting in $90M+ revenue products.\n\nStack: Sketch, InVision, Balsamiq\n\nEDUCATION\nMFA, Interaction Design — Rhode Island School of Design (RISD), 2011\n- Valedictorian, Full Fellowship\n\nB.A., Fine Arts & Cognitive Science — UC Berkeley, 2009\n- Highest Honors\n\nLANGUAGES\nEnglish (Native)\nJapanese (Native, C2)\nFrench (Conversational, B2)\nMandarin (Basic, A2)\n\nAWARDS\n- Fast Company Innovation by Design – Gold (2023)\n- Webby Award – Best UX Design (2022)\n- HOW International Design Award – Gold (2021)\n- Apple Design Award (2017)\n- AIGA 50 Books \/ 50 Covers (2019)\n- Core77 Award – Digital Category (2018)\n\nKEY PROJECTS\n- Airbnb 2023 Redesign (2022–2023): +24% conversion, $840M GMV\n- FigJam (2020–2021): 3M MAU in 6 months\n- iOS Control Center (2016–2017): Apple Design Award, 700M+ users\n\nPUBLICATIONS & TALKS\n- “The Design System Field Guide” – Rosenfeld Media (2022)\n- Speaker: Figma Config (2021–2023 Keynote)\n- Speaker: UX London (2020)\n- Guest: Design Better Podcast (2022)\n- Contributor: Nielsen Norman Group UX Library\n\nVOLUNTEERING\n- Design for America – Mentor (2016–Present)\n- ADPList – Design Mentor (1,200+ sessions)\n- RISD Career Advisory Board (2020–Present)\n- Women in Product Design – Co-founder (Chicago chapter)\n\nCONTACT\nEmail: yuki.tanaka@uxdesign.pro\nPhone: +1 (415) 672-0049\nAddress: 188 Spear Street, San Francisco, CA 94105\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/yuki-tanaka-pro","label":[[0,11,"PERSON_NAME"],[12,49,"JOB_TITLE"],[57,81,"EMAIL"],[89,106,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[116,140,"LOCATION"],[150,191,"ADDRESS"],[201,233,"LINKEDIN"],[279,282,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[824,842,"SKILL"],[844,857,"SKILL"],[858,870,"SKILL"],[872,886,"SKILL"],[888,901,"SKILL"],[902,917,"SKILL"],[919,932,"SKILL"],[946,965,"SKILL"],[967,985,"SKILL"],[987,1004,"SKILL"],[1006,1034,"SKILL"],[1036,1051,"SKILL"],[1071,1088,"SKILL"],[1090,1105,"SKILL"],[1107,1123,"SKILL"],[1124,1137,"SKILL"],[1139,1150,"SKILL"],[1152,1166,"SKILL"],[1175,1181,"SKILL"],[1191,1198,"SKILL"],[1208,1218,"SKILL"],[1230,1243,"SKILL"],[1256,1263,"SKILL"],[1273,1281,"SKILL"],[1303,1309,"SKILL"],[1323,1327,"SKILL"],[1328,1331,"SKILL"],[1333,1344,"SKILL"],[1353,1362,"SKILL"],[1364,1370,"SKILL"],[1383,1392,"SKILL"],[1394,1402,"SKILL"],[1404,1413,"SKILL"],[1415,1421,"SKILL"],[1423,1427,"SKILL"],[1429,1433,"SKILL"],[1435,1446,"SKILL"],[1465,1492,"CERTIFICATION"],[1502,1531,"CERTIFICATION"],[1541,1570,"CERTIFICATION"],[1591,1624,"CERTIFICATION"],[1650,1657,"COMPANY_NAME"],[1659,1679,"JOB_TITLE"],[1680,1698,"WORK_PERIOD"],[1701,1718,"LOCATION"],[1795,1808,"SKILL"],[1833,1839,"SKILL"],[1884,1887,"SKILL"],[1904,1911,"SKILL"],[2089,2092,"SKILL"],[2092,2095,"SKILL"],[2150,2155,"SKILL"],[2157,2163,"SKILL"],[2165,2171,"SKILL"],[2173,2182,"SKILL"],[2184,2189,"SKILL"],[2191,2201,"SKILL"],[2203,2207,"SKILL"],[2209,2218,"SKILL"],[2220,22