{"id":27,"text":"================================================================================\nNATHANIEL J. PARK\nPrincipal Cloud Architect | DevSecOps | Platform Engineering\n================================================================================\nEmail: nathaniel.park@cloudarch.dev\nPhone: +1 (617) 403-9928\nLocation: 47 Beacon St, Boston, MA 02101\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/nathaniel-park-arch\nGitHub: github.com\/njpark-cloud\nPortfolio: njpark.io\n\nSUMMARY\nPrincipal Cloud Architect and DevSecOps leader with 16+ years designing, implementing, and\ngoverning enterprise-scale cloud infrastructure across AWS, Azure, and GCP. Specializes in\nmulti-cloud strategy, Kubernetes at scale, FinOps optimization, and building platform\nengineering cultures. Led cloud transformations at Fidelity Investments, Akamai Technologies,\nHubSpot, and Rackspace. Author of 3 AWS whitepapers, 2 O'Reilly courses, and speaker at\nKubeCon, AWS re:Invent (2021, 2022, 2023), and HashiConf.\n\nHIGHLIGHTS\n- 16+ Years Experience\n- $85M Infrastructure Cost Saved\n- 350+ Cloud Migrations\n- 15 Certifications\n- 99.99% SLA Achieved\n- 4000+ Engineers Enabled\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nCloud Platforms     : AWS (98%), Azure (92%), GCP (85%)\nContainer\/Orch      : Kubernetes (97%), Docker\/Containerd (95%), Helm\/Kustomize (93%)\nIaC & Automation    : Terraform (98%), Pulumi (88%), Ansible (90%)\nCI\/CD Pipelines     : GitHub Actions (96%), ArgoCD\/Flux (94%), Jenkins\/Tekton (88%)\nProgramming         : Python (90%), Go\/Golang (82%), Bash\/Shell (95%)\nObservability       : Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, Jaeger, ELK Stack, OpenTelemetry\nNetworking\/Security : Istio, Envoy, Vault (HashiCorp), Cilium, Zero Trust, mTLS\nDatabases\/Messaging : PostgreSQL, Redis, Kafka, RabbitMQ, DynamoDB, Cassandra\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nPrincipal Cloud Architect | Fidelity Investments | Jan 2021 – Present | Boston, MA\n- Designed and governed multi-cloud architecture (AWS primary, Azure DR\/analytics, on-premise)\n  supporting 380 critical financial applications with 99.99% SLA; managed $52M annual cloud budget.\n- Led $42M cloud modernization migrating 120 legacy Java\/mainframe apps to cloud-native\n  microservices; delivered on time and 8% under budget, achieving 40% OPEX reduction ($14M\/year).\n- Built enterprise Kubernetes platform (EKS) supporting 4,000+ daily deployments across 200 teams;\n  reduced deployment time from 45 min to under 4 min.\n- Architected FinOps practice reducing cloud spend from $18M\/month to $10.8M\/month ($85M 5-year\n  savings projection).\n- Designed zero-trust security architecture meeting FINRA, SOC 2 Type II, PCI-DSS Level 1,\n  and ISO 27001.\n- Led internal IDP (Backstage) adopted by 2,200+ engineers; reduced onboarding from 3 weeks to\n  2 days; eliminated 78% of infra tickets.\n- Established SRE practice; achieved 35% reduction in P0\/P1 incidents YoY.\n- Mentored 8 senior engineers to staff\/principal level; co-led Cloud Architecture Guild (120 members).\nStack: AWS EKS, Terraform, Istio, ArgoCD, Vault, Backstage, Python, Go, Prometheus, Datadog\n\nSenior Platform Engineer → Staff Architect | Akamai Technologies | Mar 2017 – Dec 2020 | Cambridge, MA\n- Designed Akamai's internal CI\/CD platform handling 50,000+ daily deployments across 350,000+\n  edge servers in 130 countries; reduced release cycle from weekly to multiple times per day.\n- Rebuilt service mesh using Envoy Proxy + Istio; reduced P99 inter-service latency by 41%.\n- Led Terraform IaC transformation; codified 400+ reusable infrastructure modules, achieving\n  100% IaC coverage for all production environments.\n- Built chaos engineering program; ran 300+ automated fault injection experiments.\n- Designed multi-region active-active Cassandra cluster for 280TB telemetry data; 99.999% availability.\n- Promoted from Senior to Staff Architect in 18 months; led initiatives worth $28M in efficiency gains.\nStack: Kubernetes, Envoy, Istio, Terraform, Cassandra, Jenkins, Python, Chaos Engineering\n\nLead DevOps Engineer | HubSpot, Inc. | Aug 2014 – Feb 2017 | Cambridge, MA\n- Drove HubSpot's migration from 800+ bare-metal servers to AWS; reduced provisioning from\n  2 weeks to 20 min; saved $4.2M annually.\n- Built observability platform on ELK + Prometheus + Grafana; reduced MTTR from 4 hours to\n  18 min for P1 incidents.\n- Implemented GitOps workflow with ArgoCD; increased deployment frequency from 2x\/week to 15x\/day.\n- Designed auto-scaling architecture handling 10x traffic spikes with zero downtime.\n- Led team of 6 DevOps engineers; established on-call rotation, runbook standards, post-mortem culture.\nStack: AWS, Docker, ELK, ArgoCD, Prometheus, Grafana, Ansible\n\nCloud Solutions Engineer | Rackspace Technology | Jun 2011 – Jul 2014 | San Antonio, TX\n- Designed cloud infrastructure solutions for 220+ enterprise customers.\n- Developed automated cost optimization tooling reducing over-provisioning by 30% ($18M savings).\n- Achieved Rackspace Certified Expert status (top 5%) within 18 months.\nStack: OpenStack, Linux, Python, MySQL, Nginx, HAProxy\n\nSystems Administrator | TeleCommunication Systems (TCS) | Sep 2008 – May 2011 | Annapolis, MD\n- Administered Linux\/Windows hybrid infrastructure for 911\/public-safety platforms in 200+ municipalities.\n- Implemented automated backup\/DR with RTO of 4 hours \/ RPO of 15 minutes.\n\nKEY PROJECTS\n- Enterprise IDP @ Fidelity (2022–2023): Backstage + Terraform + GitHub Actions. Onboarded\n  2,200+ engineers; reduced time-to-prod from 3 weeks to 6 hours.\n- FinOps Automation Platform (2021–2022): Saved $7.2M in year 1. Open-sourced (1,400+ GitHub stars).\n- Akamai Edge Deploy (2018–2020): Reduced deployment-related incidents by 94%.\n- k8s-cost-analyzer OSS (2020–Present): 3,200+ GitHub stars, adopted by 180+ organizations.\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n- AWS Solutions Architect Professional (2022)\n- AWS DevOps Engineer Professional (2021)\n- AWS Security Specialty (2021)\n- CKA – Certified