ointment scheduling on Azure.\n- Built HL7 FHIR-based interoperability APIs with Spring Security, OAuth 2.0, and JWT tokens.\n- Integrated AI\/ML clinical decision support using Spring AI, LangChain, Azure Functions,\n  TensorFlow, and PyTorch.\n- Developed microservices with Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and Apache Kafka on Azure Kubernetes Service.\n- Built CI\/CD pipelines using Jenkins and Azure DevOps; provisioned infrastructure with Terraform.\n- Enhanced patient portals using Angular, React.js, and Next.js.\n- Integrated Azure OpenAI Service for automated medical coding (ICD-10\/CPT) workflows.\n- Optimized performance using Prometheus, Grafana, and Azure Monitor; maintained 99.9% uptime.\n- Mentored developers on Core Java, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, and AI\/ML integration strategies.\nStack: Spring AI, LangChain, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, Angular, React.js, Next.js, Azure,\n  Kubernetes, Kafka, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Cosmos DB, Docker, Terraform, Jenkins\n\nSenior Full Stack Developer | BNY Mellon | July 2020 – April 2023 | New York, NY\n- Developed enterprise banking applications using Core Java, Java EE, and Spring Boot on AWS\n  EC2 and EKS with PCI-DSS compliance.\n- Built microservices for loan origination and fraud detection with Spring Boot and RabbitMQ.\n- Architected payment processing systems using Java EE, Spring Boot, AWS SQS, Oracle, DynamoDB.\n- Integrated AI for credit risk assessment connecting Java backend with AWS SageMaker.\n- Designed cloud-native solutions on AWS (EC2, RDS, S3, Lambda, Redshift, EKS).\n- Implemented DevOps practices using GitHub Actions, Docker, Kubernetes, and Ansible.\n- Created automated testing using Mockito, Cucumber, and Postman.\n- Built ETL pipelines using AWS Glue, Lambda, and S3.\nStack: Java, Spring Boot, React.js, Next.js, AWS, EKS, Oracle, DynamoDB, Cassandra,\n  RabbitMQ, ELK Stack, GitHub Actions, Docker\n\nJava Developer | Target | September 2017 – June 2020 | Minneapolis, MN\n- Designed enterprise Java applications for retail platforms using Core Java, Spring Boot,\n  Spring MVC, and Spring Data JPA processing millions of daily transactions.\n- Built scalable microservices on AWS EKS and OpenShift with GitLab CI and Helm CI\/CD.\n- Integrated MySQL, MongoDB, AWS RDS, and DynamoDB for retail catalog, customer profiles,\n  and inventory.\n- Developed RESTful APIs and GraphQL services using Spring Boot and OpenAPI.\n- Built asynchronous messaging using ActiveMQ and AWS SNS\/SQS.\nStack: Java, Spring Boot, Spring MVC, Angular, React.js, AWS, Kubernetes, EKS, Docker,\n  MySQL, MongoDB, DynamoDB, Maven\n\nBackend Developer | Southwest Airlines | January 2016 – August 2017 | Dallas, TX\n- Designed and developed backend microservices using Java 8 and Spring Boot for OpsSuite,\n  a real-time airline operations platform at 100+ airport locations.\n- Built secured RESTful APIs using Spring Security and Apigee API Management.\n- Worked with PostgreSQL on GCP Cloud SQL; developed PL\/SQL procedures.\n- Implemented asynchronous messaging using RabbitMQ.\n- Containerized services using Docker; deployed on GKE and OpenShift.\n- Automated infrastructure provisioning with Terraform on GCP.\nStack: Java 8, Spring Boot, Spring Cloud, PostgreSQL, GCP, RabbitMQ, Docker, Kubernetes,\n  GKE, OpenShift, Terraform, Jenkins\n\nBackend Developer | Ramco Systems | August 2014 – October 2015 | Chennai, India\n- Worked on enterprise Java applications using Java 8, J2EE, and Spring MVC.\n- Applied design patterns: Singleton, Factory, DAO, Business Delegate, Session Facade.\n- Implemented Spring IoC, Dependency Injection, and Spring AOP.\n- Used Hibernate ORM with Microsoft SQL Server; improved data access performance by 25%.\n- Built web services using SOAP, WSDL, JAX-B, XML, JMS, and JNDI.\n- Reduced code conflicts by 30% through structured SVN source control practices.\nStack: Java 8, Spring MVC, Hibernate, Microsoft SQL Server, JMS, SOAP, JUnit, IBM WebSphere\n\nEDUCATION\nBachelor of Technology 