ig Data Engineer | Humana | August 2023 – Present | Louisville, KY\n- Designed and deployed agentic retrieval workflows using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph\n  for automated CES scoring and healthcare quality metrics.\n- Migrated legacy orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster across 40+ production\n  pipelines on AWS ECS and EKS.\n- Built production-grade LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy (GPT-4, Claude, AWS SageMaker,\n  MLflow) for healthcare PR-level scoring.\n- Engineered backend services using Python, AWS Lambda, AWS EventBridge, and AWS CDK.\n- Orchestrated large-scale backfills processing over 10 million commits and clinical records.\n- Implemented SonarQube integration for code-quality scoring with HIPAA-compliant governance.\n- Built observability using AWS CloudWatch, AWS Lambda, and Dagster asset sensors.\n- Deployed AI\/ML pipelines using MLLIB and NumPy to predict patient readmission risk.\nStack: AWS SageMaker, Dagster, DSPy, LangChain, LangGraph, Python, MLflow, Power BI,\n  Pandas, NumPy, AWS EKS, AWS Glue, Airflow, ECS, SonarQube\n\nSr. Data Engineer | Morgan Stanley | October 2020 – July 2023 | New York, NY\n- Designed production-grade data pipelines using Python and Dagster on AWS with PCI-DSS\n  compliance.\n- Built retrieval agents using Python and DSPy with SOX-compliant audit trails.\n- Migrated orchestration from Airflow to Dagster; enhanced PR\/commit linking and epic tracking.\n- Developed anomaly detection using Python, AWS Glue, and AWS CloudWatch.\n- Built AWS-native pipelines (ECS, Lambda, S3, RDS, CDK) for high-volume financial data ingestion.\n- Implemented AWS WAF rules mitigating SQL injection, XSS, and DDoS attacks.\nStack: Lambda, Airflow, S3, Dagster, ECS, AWS EC2, AWS RDS, AWS EKS, AWS WAF, DSPy,\n  Python, Glue, EventBridge, AWS SQS\n\nData Engineer \/ Data Analyst | Delta Airlines | December 2017 – September 2020 | Atlanta, GA\n- Designed production data pipelines using Python and Apache Airflow with FAA\/IATA compliance.\n- Orchestrated migration using Dagster and Airflow on AWS ECS and EKS.\n- Built analytics platforms using Python, AWS RDS, and Power BI for CES metrics.\n- Built observability using Prometheus, Grafana, and AWS CloudWatch.\n- Integrated SonarQube with Airflow and AWS Glue; mapped code severity to FAA DAL levels.\nStack: AWS CDK, Python, AWS EC2, EventBridge, SonarQube, AWS Lambda, Prometheus, AWS EKS,\n  Dagster, Airflow, AWS S3, ECS, Glue, Jenkins, AWS RDS, Grafana, Power BI, Collibra\n\nData Engineer \/ Migration Specialist | Cisco | February 2016 – November 2017 | San Jose, CA\n- Built Network Data Integration platform using Azure Cloud for global networking systems.\n- Developed scalable data ingestion pipelines using Talend ETL and Azure Data Factory.\n- Executed data migration from legacy network management systems to modern SDN platforms.\n- Built orchestration workflows using Apache Airflow for distributed ETL across global regions.\n- Developed predictive capacity forecasting models using Azure Databricks.\nStack: Azure Cloud, Talend ETL, Azure Data Factory, Apache Airflow, Azure SQL, Azure\n  Databricks, Python, Streaming Analytics\n\nETL Developer | Flipkart | August 2014 – December 2015 | Bangalore, India\n- Built scalable ETL pipeline using AWS Services, Informatica, and Talend for e-commerce data.\n- Utilized Informatica PowerCenter to extract from MySQL, PostgreSQL, and MongoDB.\n- Designed AWS Glue jobs loading data into Amazon Redshift.\n- Connected Tableau to Amazon Redshift for interactive sales and inventory dashboards.\nStack: AWS (S3, Glue, Lambda, CloudWatch, Redshift), Informatica PowerCenter, Talend,\n  MySQL, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Tableau\n\nEDUCATION\nB.Tech Computer Science & Engineering – Koneru Lakshmaiah University, 2010–2014\n","label":[[81,84,"PERSON_NAME"],[85,106,"JOB_TITLE"],[195,212,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[220,237,"EMAIL"],[248,260,"LOCATION"],[270,290,"LINKEDIN"],[315,336,"JOB_TITLE"],[342,345,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[431,433,"SKILL