rvability tools\n- Built AI chatbots and ML pipelines for healthcare systems\n\nEnvironment: AWS, Dagster, DSPy, LangChain, Python, MLflow, Power BI, GitHub\n\nMorgan Stanley – Senior Data Engineer  \nOct 2020 – Jul 2023 | New York, NY\n- Built scalable AWS pipelines using Python and Dagster\n- Developed anomaly detection and data quality systems\n- Implemented security and compliance (PCI-DSS, SOX, GLBA)\n- Built backend APIs using Lambda and EKS\n- Automated workflows using Airflow and AWS services\n\nEnvironment: AWS, Lambda, Airflow, Dagster, Python, Glue, GitHub\n\nDelta Airlines – Data Engineer \/ Analyst  \nDec 2017 – Sep 2020 | Atlanta, GA\n- Built real-time pipelines using Airflow and AWS\n- Developed dashboards using Power BI\n- Implemented monitoring with Prometheus and Grafana\n- Built analytics systems for aviation data\n\nEnvironment: AWS, Airflow, Python, Grafana, Power BI\n\nCisco – Data Engineer \/ Migration Specialist  \nFeb 2016 – Nov 2017 | San Jose, CA\n- Built Azure-based data integration platforms\n- Developed ETL pipelines using Talend and Data Factory\n- Migrated legacy systems to cloud environments\n\nEnvironment: Azure, Talend, Data Factory, Python\n\nFlipkart – ETL Developer  \nAug 2014 – Dec 2015 | Bangalore, India\n- Built ETL pipelines using AWS, Informatica, Talend\n- Designed data models and dashboards using Tableau\n- Automated workflows using Lambda and CloudWatch\n\nEnvironment: AWS, Informatica, Talend, MySQL, Tableau\n\n\nEDUCATION\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science & Engineering  \nKoneru Lakshmaiah University (2010–2014)\n\n\nKEY ACHIEVEMENTS\n- Migrated 40+ production pipelines to Dagster with 99.9% reliability\n- Processed 10M+ records using AWS and distributed systems\n- Built AI\/LLM-based automation systems\n- Designed multi-cloud architectures (AWS, Azure, GCP)\n- Delivered compliant platforms (HIPAA, PCI-DSS, SOX)\n- Improved code quality using SonarQube and automation pipelines","label":[[0,4,"PERSON_NAME"],[5