{"id":48,"text":"STEPHEN GREET\nSenior AWS Cloud Engineer | Solutions Architect | DevOps & Infrastructure Lead\n\nEmail: stephen@beamjobs.com\nPhone: (123) 456-7890\nLocation: New York, NY, USA\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/stephengreet\nGitHub: github.com\/stephengreet-aws\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nResults-driven Senior AWS Cloud Engineer and Solutions Architect with 14+ years of experience designing, building, and managing enterprise-scale cloud infrastructure across financial services, manufacturing, e-commerce, healthcare, and SaaS industries.\n\nExpert in cloud migration, infrastructure-as-code, serverless architectures, containers (EKS\/ECS), security, compliance, and cost optimization.\n\nKey achievements:\n- Delivered $5M+ in cloud cost savings\n- Led 20+ zero-downtime cloud migrations\n- Achieved 99.99% platform availability\n- Built multi-region disaster recovery systems\n- AWS Community Builder and conference speaker\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nCORE SKILLS\n\n- AWS Architecture & Cloud Design\n- Cloud Migration & Modernization\n- Infrastructure as Code (Terraform, CDK)\n- Kubernetes (EKS), ECS, Fargate\n- Serverless (Lambda, API Gateway)\n- CI\/CD & GitOps\n- AWS Security, IAM, Compliance (SOC2, HIPAA, PCI-DSS)\n- Networking (VPC, Transit Gateway, PrivateLink)\n- Observability & SRE Practices\n- Cost Optimization & FinOps\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nSenior AWS Cloud Engineer \/ Solutions Architect\nSweet Oranges Technology, New York, NY\nMarch 2018 – Present\n\n- Led migration of 80+ services from on-premises to AWS\n- Re-architected monolithic systems to microservices using ECS, Lambda, and API Gateway\n- Designed multi-region architecture achieving 99.99% availability\n- Built Terraform-based IaC with 50,000+ lines across 200+ modules\n- Implemented CI\/CD pipelines reducing deployment time from 2 hours to 18 minutes\n- Delivered $1.8M annual cloud cost savings\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nAWS Cloud Engineer \/ DevOps Lead\nKCR Industries, Dallas, TX\nMarch 2014 – February 2018\n\n- Migrated 200+ workloads to AWS with zero downtime\n- Built disaster recovery system reducing RTO to 40 minutes\n- Designed IoT pipeline processing 10,000+ sensor events\/sec\n- Implemented CI\/CD pipelines for 40+ applications\n- Achieved $800K annual cost savings\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nAWS Solutions Architect \/ Cloud Engineer\nFive Brothers Digital Marketing, Austin, TX\nFebruary 2009 – February 2014\n\n- Built AWS infrastructure from scratch\n- Designed scalable architecture supporting 10x traffic spikes\n- Reduced page load time from 3.2s to 0.8s\n- Implemented data lake using S3, Glue, and Athena\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nEDUCATION\n\nMaster of Science in Cloud Computing & Distributed Systems\nNortheastern University, Boston, MA\n2016 – 2018\nGPA: 3.9\/4.0\n\nBachelor of Science in Computer Science & Network Engineering\nSan Jose State University, CA\n2005 – 2010\nGPA: 3.8\/4.0\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n- AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Professional\n- AWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional\n- AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate\n- AWS Certified Developer – Associate\n- AWS Certified SysOps Administrator – Associate\n- AWS Certified Security – Specialty\n- AWS Certified Advanced Networking – Specialty\n- AWS Certified Database – Specialty\n- HashiCorp Terraform Associate\n- Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)\n- Certified Kubernetes Application Developer (CKAD)\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nCloud Platforms:\nAWS (EC2, S3, Lambda, ECS, EKS, RDS, DynamoDB, CloudFront)\n\nDevOps & IaC:\nTerraform, CloudFormation, CDK, GitHub Actions, CodePipeline\n\nContainers & Orchestration:\nDocker, Kubernetes, EKS, ECS, Fargate\n\nData & Analytics:\nS3, Glue, Athena, Kinesis, Redshift\n\nSecurity:\nIAM, KMS, GuardDuty, Security Hub, WAF, CloudTrail\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nLANGUAGES\n\nEnglish – Native\nGerman – Professional\nSpanish – Intermediate\nFrench – Basic\nMandarin – Basic\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION\n\n- AWS Community Builder (Architecture Track)\n- Conference Speaker (AWS re:Invent, DevOpsDays)\n- Open Source Contributor (Terraform & AWS tools)\n- Trained 4,500+ engineers in cloud technologies\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nREFERENCES\n\nAvailable upon request","label":[[0,13,"PERSON_NAME"],[14,39,"JOB_TITLE"],[42,61,"JOB_TITLE"],[64,92,"JOB_TITLE"],[101,121,"EMAIL"],[128,143,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[153,171,"LOCATION"],[182,210,"LINKEDIN"],[219,246,"GITHUB"],[337,362,"JOB_TITLE"],[392,395,"COMPANY_NAME"],[515,528,"SKILL"],[530,540,"SKILL"],[558,563,"SKILL"],[586,601,"SKILL"],[638,651,"SKILL"],[665,668,"SKILL"],[669,672,"SKILL"],[759,765,"SKILL"],[1021,1037,"SKILL"],[1040,1052,"SKILL"],[1055,1071,"SKILL"],[1073,1086,"SKILL"],[1113,1122,"SKILL"],[1124,1127,"SKILL"],[1131,1142,"SKILL"],[1143,1146,"SKILL"],[1149,1152,"SKILL"],[1154,1161,"SKILL"],[1164,1175,"SKILL"],[1176,1182,"SKILL"],[1184,1195,"SKILL"],[1199,1205,"SKILL"],[1207,1213,"SKILL"],[1216,1228,"SKILL"],[1230,1233,"SKILL"],[1247,1251,"SKILL"],[1253,1258,"SKILL"],[1260,1267,"SKILL"],[1271,1282,"SKILL"],[1283,1286,"SKILL"],[1287,1303,"SKILL"],[1305,1316,"SKILL"],[1336,1349,"SKILL"],[1372,1378,"SKILL"],[1457,1504,"JOB_TITLE"],[1505,1529,"COMPANY_NAME"],[1531,1543,"LOCATION"],[1544,1564,"WORK_PERIOD"],[1618,1621,"SKILL"],[1661,1675,"SKILL"],[1681,1684,"SKILL"],[1686,1692,"SKILL"],[1698,1702,"SKILL"],[1801,1805,"SKILL"],[1857,1872,"SKILL"],[1951,1957,"SKILL"],[2023,2055,"JOB_TITLE"],[2056,2070,"COMPANY_NAME"],[2072,2082,"LOCATION"],[2083,2093,"START_DATE"],[2095,2109,"END_DATE"],[2140,2144,"SKILL"]