{"id":49,"text":"ARJUN\nMEHTA\nSENIOR DATA ENGINEER\tData Engineering Leader | 13+ Years\nEmail: arjun.mehta@techmail.com   Phone: +1 (678) 555-0143   Location: Atlanta, GA\nlinkedin.com\/in\/arjunmehta   |   github.com\/arjunmehta\nExpertise in Snowflake, PySpark, AWS\/Azure\/GCP, dbt, Kafka, ML Pipelines, and enterprise-scale ETL\/ELT engineering with a track record of delivering mission-critical data solutions.\nCONTACT\narjun.mehta@techmail.com\n+1 (678) 555-0143\nAtlanta, GA 30301\n\nLINKS\nLinkedIn Profile\nGitHub Portfolio\nPortfolio Site\n\nCORE SKILLS\n•\tSnowflake \/ SnowSQL \/ Snowpipe\n•\tPySpark \/ Apache Spark\n•\tPython \/ SQL \/ Scala\n•\tAWS \/ Azure \/ GCP\n•\tdbt \/ Matillion \/ Talend\n•\tApache Kafka \/ Pulsar\n•\tAirflow \/ Prefect \/ Luigi\n•\tTerraform \/ CloudFormation\n•\tReact.js \/ FastAPI\n•\tMLflow \/ scikit-learn \/ TF\n•\tDocker \/ Kubernetes\n•\tGit \/ GitHub Actions\n\nCLOUD PLATFORMS\n•\tAWS S3, Redshift, Glue\n•\tAWS Lambda, EMR, EC2\n•\tAzure Synapse, ADF\n•\tAzure Blob, CosmosDB\n•\tGCP BigQuery, Dataflow\n•\tGCP Cloud Storage, GKE\n\nDATABASES\n•\tSnowflake \/ Redshift\n•\tOracle \/ MySQL \/ MSSQL\n•\tTeradata \/ Hive\n•\tMongoDB \/ Cassandra\n•\tPostgreSQL \/ DynamoDB\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\nAWS Solutions Architect Pro\nSnowflake SnowPro Core\nGCP Professional DE\nAzure Data Engineer\nCKA (Kubernetes)\n\nEDUCATION\nM.S. Computer Science\nGeorgia Tech, 2013\n\nB.E. Information Tech\nMumbai University, 2011\n\nLANGUAGES\n•\tEnglish (Fluent)\n•\tHindi (Native)\n•\tGujarati (Native)\n\nINTERESTS\n•\tOpen Source Contributions\n•\tData Mesh Architecture\n•\tChess & Competitive Programming\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\tPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nSenior Data Engineer with 13+ years designing enterprise-scale data architectures and ETL\/ELT pipelines across Snowflake, AWS, Azure, and GCP. Proven expertise in building real-time and batch data platforms that serve millions of daily transactions. Deep knowledge of cloud-native data engineering, ML pipeline orchestration, data governance, and modern DataOps practices. Strong communicator who bridges business requirements with technical execution for Fortune 500 clients.\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\nSR. BIG DATA ENGINEER  |  State Farm Insurance  —  Bloomington, IL   Oct 2022 – Present\n•\tDesigned end-to-end ETL pipelines using Python, PySpark, and Apache Spark ingesting large-scale claims and policy data from AWS S3 into Snowflake; reduced processing latency by 55% through optimized partitioning.\n•\tManaged real-time streaming workflows integrating Apache Kafka and Snowpipe with Snowflake Streams, enabling continuous ingestion of 10M+ daily events for actuarial and risk analytics dashboards.\n•\tBuilt ML pipelines with scikit-learn, TensorFlow, and PyTorch, orchestrating experiments via MLflow and deploying models integrated with Snowflake Cortex AI for enterprise fraud detection.\n•\tAutomated workflow orchestration with Airflow and Jenkins scheduling ETL\/ELT jobs from AWS Glue and Lambda, maintaining fault-tolerant execution and 99.98% pipeline uptime across 200+ jobs.\n•\tDesigned secure architectures using Terraform, AWS IAM, and Snowflake RBAC; led SOC 2 Type II compliance effort covering 80% of evidence collection through automated tooling.\n•\tDeveloped interactive dashboards using React.js, Redux, Zustand, and Plotly, fetching data through Axios APIs from Flask services, serving 500+ internal analysts with real-time P&C metrics.\n•\tModeled enterprise data structures via Dimensional Modeling and Erwin, defining Star schema and Data Marts enabling seamless integration with Snowflake for BI reporting consuming $2B+ policy data.\n•\tImplemented data governance and lineage tracking using Collibra and Informatica, maintaining metadata and enforcing enterprise standards for security, compliance, and data quality.\n•\tCreated reusable ELT templates in dbt and Matillion, standardizing Data Marts and Dimensional Modeling principles to support analytics and reduce development cycle times by 40%.\n•\tOrchestrated event-driven processing using Snowflake Tasks, Snowflake Streams, and Apache Kafka, ensuring real-time updates across AWS environments with fault-tolerance guarantees.\n•\tMonitored pipeline performance with Datadog and CloudWatch, tracking metrics, detecting anomalies, and tuning Apache Spark jobs and Snowflake queries for improved throughput.\n•\tCollaborated with cross-functional teams using Jira and Slack to define requirements, design pipelines, and deliver production-ready Snowflake solutions aligned with business compliance policies.\nEnvironment: Python, PySpark, Apache Spark, AWS S3, Snowflake, Kafka, Snowpipe, dbt, Matillion, MLflow, Airflow, Jenkins, Terraform, Datadog, React.js, Flask, Collibra\nSR. DATA ENGINEER  |  Delta Air Lines  —  Atlanta, GA   Dec 2019 – Sep 2022\n•\tDesigned scalable ETL pipelines using Snowflake, Snowpipe, SnowSQL, and Fivetran automating real-time ingestion of flight and operational data for 200M+ annual passenger records.\n•\tDeveloped modular transformation workflows with dbt and Snowflake Tasks\/Streams, implementing version-controlled CI\/CD deployments via GitHub Actions for production-ready pipelines.\n•\tEngineered high-performance batch\/streaming pipelines using Python, PySpark, and Apache Spark processing flight telemetry and booking data at petabyte scale.\n•\tBuilt real-time event processing with Apache Kafka and Pulsar ensuring reliable ingestion of aircraft telemetry; coordinated with Prefect to schedule and retry failed pipelines automatically.\n•\tDesigned Azure Data Factory workflows orchestrating data from Azure Blob Storage to Azure Synapse and Snowflake for near real-time aviation analytics across 5 business units.\n•\tDeveloped dimensional models and data marts using Snowflake schema structures, providing consolidated flight operations, ticketing, and customer analytics for downstream BI tools.\n•\tDesigned RESTful APIs with FastAPI serving processed datasets to React.js\/Redux front-end dashboards, enabling interactive visualization of real-time flight metrics for ops teams.\n•\tAutomated CI\/CD for ETL, dbt models, and APIs using GitHub Actions with testing, linting, and version control; seamless promotion from dev to production environments.\n•\tUtilized Terraform to provision Azure Synapse and Blob Storage following IaC principles, maintaining reproducible, version-controlled cloud environment deployments.\n•\tImplemented monitoring with New Relic and Azure Monitor tracking pipeline health and latency; automated alerts for failed ETL jobs enabling proactive resolution within 15-minute SLA.\nEnvironment: Snowflake, dbt, GitHub Actions, PySpark, Kafka, Prefect, Azure Data Factory, Azure Synapse, FastAPI, React.js, Terraform, New Relic, Alation, Chart.js\nDATA ENGINEER \/ DATA ANALYST  |  UPS  —  Atlanta, GA   Feb 2017 – Nov 2019\n•\tDesigned scalable ETL pipelines using Snowflake, SnowSQL, Snowpipe, and Talend automating ingestion of shipment and logistics data for 15M+ daily package tracking events.\n•\tDeveloped modular dbt transformation workflows with Snowflake Tasks\/Streams for incremental updates; automated deployments via GitLab CI\/CD for seamless production rollout.\n•\tEngineered batch and streaming pipelines using Python, PySpark, and Apache Spark for large-scale processing of operational and shipment tracking data with optimal memory efficiency.\n•\tOrchestrated cloud-based integration using GCP Dataflow and Cloud Storage, transferring datasets to GCP BigQuery for logistics analytics across supply chain business units.\n•\tBuilt dynamic dashboards using D3.js and Fetch API consuming data from Snowflake and BigQuery, enabling operations teams to monitor delivery performance and shipment delays in real time.\n•\tLeveraged Power Designer and Apache Atlas to document data lineage, relationships, and metadata ensuring governance compliance and accurate audit trails for logistics operations.\n•\tManaged cloud infrastructure provisioning using Terraform, automating deployments of GCP Cloud Storage, Dataflow jobs, and BigQuery datasets for scalable analytics pipelines.\nEnvironment: Snowflake, dbt, GitLab CI\/CD, PySpark, Kafka, GCP Dataflow, BigQuery, D3.js, React.js, Terraform, Dynatrace, Power Designer, Apache Atlas\nDATA ENGINEER \/ MIGRATION SPECIALIST  |  ADP  —  Roseland, NJ   Jan 2016 – Jan 2017\n•\tDeveloped Payroll Data Integration platform using Azure Cloud improving data flow between time-tracking, benefits, and payroll modules for 40,000+ employee records.\n•\tCreated ingestion pipelines using Talend ETL and Azure Data Factory to process employee data with validation rules ensuring payroll accuracy across multiple corporate clients.\n•\tExecuted data migration from legacy payroll systems to cloud-based platforms preserving historical payroll information while enabling new functionality through comprehensive data mapping.\n•\tImplemented Azure SQL Database and Azure Data Lake Storage reducing processing response times by 40% through strategic indexing and query optimization.\n•\tCreated predictive models using Azure Databricks applying ML techniques to historical employment data for optimized workforce planning and resource allocation.\n•\tBuilt interactive Tableau dashboards visualizing payroll metrics and labor cost analytics providing actionable insights into compensation trends and cost-saving opportunities.\n•\tEstablished SOX-compliant data security protocols implementing encryption, access controls, and audit logging to protect personally identifiable payroll information.\nETL DEVELOPER  |  Inno Minds (Pune, India)  —  Pune, India   May 2014 – Nov 2015\n•\tDeveloped scalable ETL pipelines using Oracle Data Integrator (ODI) and SSIS integrating data from legacy retail systems and third-party applications.\n•\tSet up SQL Server data warehouse with partitioning strategies and incremental loading for retail transaction data, reducing processing windows for nightly batch operations.\n•\tCreated SSIS packages processing XML and Excel data from POS systems with error handling routines reducing data processing time by 40%.\n•\tSet up SSAS for multidimensional data modeling with optimized aggregation designs, reducing report generation time by 30% for retail KPI dashboards.\n•\tBuilt Power BI connections to SQL Server data warehouse creating interactive dashboards for real-time store performance and inventory metrics.\nEnvironment: ODI, SSIS, SQL Server, SSAS, Power BI, Oracle, MySQL, SQL Server Agent\nKEY PROJECTS & ACHIEVEMENTS\n•\tState Farm Real-Time Claims Analytics — Architected Snowflake + Kafka streaming platform processing 50M daily events, reducing claims processing time by 35% and saving $8M annually.\n•\tDelta Airlines Flight Intelligence Platform — Built ML-powered predictive delay model (92% accuracy) using PySpark and MLflow, improving on-time performance metrics by 18%.\n•\tUPS Shipment Tracking Modernization — Led GCP BigQuery migration from legacy Oracle DW, cutting infrastructure costs by 42% while improving query performance 10x.\n•\tADP Payroll Cloud Migration — Migrated 120+ legacy COBOL-based payroll ETL jobs to Azure Data Factory, reducing nightly processing window from 8 hours to 90 minutes.\n•\tEnterprise Data Governance Framework — Designed Collibra-based governance framework adopted across 5 enterprise clients, achieving 98% metadata coverage and ISO 27001 compliance.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nETL\/ELT Tools\tSnowflake, SnowSQL, Snowpipe, dbt, Matillion, Talend, Informatica, SSIS, AWS Glue, Fivetran, ODI\nLanguages\tPython, PySpark, Scala, Java, SQL, T-SQL, SnowSQL, Bash, JavaScript, TypeScript\nCloud Platforms\tAWS (S3, Redshift, Glue, Lambda, EMR, EC2, Athena, SQS, CloudWatch), Azure (ADF, Synapse, Blob, Databricks, CosmosDB), GCP (BigQuery, Dataflow, Cloud Storage, GKE)\nBig Data\tApache Spark, PySpark, Kafka, Pulsar, Airflow, Prefect, Luigi, HDFS, Hive, NiFi, Sqoop, Flume, Zookeeper, YARN\nML \