{"id":50,"text":"resume 01_DIEGO FERNÁNDEZ\nSenior Blockchain & Web3 Engineer\n\nCONTACT\nEmail: diego.fernandez@web3.dev\nPhone: +1 (305) 512-4490\nLocation: Miami, FL\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/diegofernandez\n\nSUMMARY\nPioneering Web3 Engineer with 8 years architecting DeFi protocols, NFT platforms, and enterprise blockchain solutions at scale. Audited smart contracts securing $500M+ in TVL. Expert in Solidity, Rust, and zero-knowledge proof systems with a deep commitment to decentralized application security.\n\nSKILLS & COMPETENCIES\n- Solidity \/ Rust \/ Vyper \/ EVM — 96%\n- DeFi Protocol Architecture — 94%\n- Zero-Knowledge Proofs (zk-SNARKs) — 88%\n- TypeScript \/ Python \/ Foundry — 90%\n- Smart Contract Security Auditing — 92%\n- Layer 2 & Rollup Engineering — 89%\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nCoinbase | Mar 2022 – Present\nSenior Blockchain Engineer – Base L2\nLocation: Miami, FL (Remote)\n- Built Layer 2 scaling solutions on Base chain reducing average gas costs by 80% for end users\n- Developed Base chain developer tooling (SDKs, CLI, faucets) adopted by 50,000+ developers globally\n- Conducted security audits of 8 major DeFi protocols securing $200M+ in combined TVL\n- Contributed 15+ PRs to OP Stack open-source codebase used by 10+ Superchain networks\n\nUniswap Labs | May 2019 – Feb 2022\nSmart Contract Engineer\nLocation: New York, NY\n- Core contributor to Uniswap v3 concentrated liquidity AMM processing $1T+ in cumulative volume\n- Wrote and maintained formal verification specifications for all core protocol contracts\n- Developed Uniswap v3 deployment scripts and governance contracts for 10+ chain deployments\n- Performed comprehensive security reviews identifying and remediating 3 critical vulnerabilities pre-launch\n\nConsenSys | Feb 2016 – Apr 2019\nSenior Ethereum Developer\nLocation: Brooklyn, NY\n- Built enterprise Ethereum solutions for JPMorgan Quorum and ING bank consortium networks\n- Delivered Hyperledger Besu implementations for 4