{"id":52,"text":"ADARSH REDDY BODHA\nSR. BIG DATA ENGINEER\n\nCONTACT\nEmail: adarshbodha214@gmail.com\nPhone: +1 (281) 810-1863\nLinkedIn: www.linkedin.com\/in\/abodha13reddy\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n- Designed and maintained C#\/.NET data integration applications using ADO.NET, dependency injection, and class inheritance to connect EMR systems, Microsoft SQL Server, and Azure SQL ensuring scalability and compliance.\n- Developed ETL pipelines in Azure Databricks with data extraction, transformation, validation, and loading into SQL Server and Databricks SQL.\n- Engineered complex SQL queries, stored procedures, joins, and indexing strategies for large healthcare datasets.\n- Collaborated with healthcare providers for data validation, reconciliation, and mapping across EMR systems.\n- Deployed applications across healthcare environments with secure configurations and HIPAA compliance.\n- Built Azure-based integration solutions with Databricks, Azure SQL, and secure connectivity.\n- Developed CI\/CD pipelines using Azure DevOps for automated deployments and testing.\n- Implemented Docker-based containerization and AKS orchestration for scalable deployments.\n- Managed API integrations, authentication, VPN connectivity, and data pipelines.\n- Created PowerShell automation scripts for deployment, monitoring, and maintenance.\n- Performed troubleshooting across ETL pipelines, SQL performance, and application errors.\n- Designed data validation frameworks and reporting systems.\n- Managed Azure infrastructure including AKS, networking, and disaster recovery.\n- Developed transformation logic using SQL and Python in Databricks.\n- Implemented security controls including encryption and RBAC for HIPAA compliance.\n- Orchestrated Java microservices and deployments integrated with ETL pipelines.\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nETL Tools\n- Informatica PowerCenter 10.x\/9.6\n- AWS Glue\n- Talend 5.6\n- SSIS\n- Semarchy xDM\n\nDatabases & Tools\n- Microsoft SQL Server (2012\/2014)\n- Teradata 14\/15\n- Oracle 10g\/11g\n- Erwin 8\/9\n- MySQL\n\nCloud Platforms\n- AWS: Snowflake, RDS, Redshift, EC2, EMR, S3, Lambda, Glue, Athena, SQS, VPC, CloudWatch, Jenkins\n- Azure: HDInsight, Cosmos DB, Fabric, Blob Storage, Data Lake, Data Factory, SQL, Databricks\n- GCP: DataProc, BigQuery, Cloud Storage, GKE, Functions, Spanner\n\nReporting Tools\n- Tableau\n- Power BI\n- EHR\n- Semarchy\n\nBig Data Ecosystem\n- HDFS, Hive, MapReduce, Sqoop, Flume\n- Spark, Spark Streaming\n- NiFi, Yarn, Zookeeper\n- Airflow, Kafka\n\nProgramming Languages\n- SQL, Python, Java, Scala\n- T-SQL, PySpark\n- Unix, Spring Boot\n\nMethodologies\n- SDLC, Waterfall, Agile\n\nContainerization & DevOps\n- Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, Docker Hub\n\nMachine Learning Libraries\n- Pandas, NumPy, Matplotlib, Scikit-Learn\n- Decision Tree, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, Gradient Boosting\n\nData Warehousing\n- Star Schema, Snowflake Schema\n- Facts & Dimensions\n- SSIS, Splunk, Cloudera\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nJohnson & Johnson | Oct 2023 – Current\nRole: SR. BIG DATA ENGINEER\nLocation: New Brunswick, NJ\n\n- Developed C#\/.NET applications integrating EMR systems with Azure environments ensuring HIPAA compliance\n- Designed ETL pipelines using Azure Data Factory, Databricks, and Spark with HL7 standards\n- Built SQL queries across SQL Server, Azure SQL, Synapse, and Databricks SQL\n- Configured APIs, VPNs, and Azure infrastructure for data exchange\n- Implemented CI\/CD pipelines using Jenkins, Git, and PowerShell\n- Built Kafka streaming pipelines for real-time clinical data ingestion\n- Deployed containerized services on AKS with monitoring (Prometheus, Grafana)\n- Created data lineage and governance using Erwin and Collibra\n- Managed Azure services including VMs, Storage, Cosmos DB, Synapse\n- Optimized SQL performance and ETL workflows\n- Implemented Azure security (AAD, encryption, RBAC)\n\nEnvironment\nGit, Erwin, Tableau, SQL Server, Azure, Databricks, Kafka, AKS, Jenkins, PowerShell, Snowflake, Synapse, Cosmos DB\n\neBay | Dec 2020 – Sep 2023\nRole: SR DATA ENGINEER\nLocation: San Jose, CA\n\n- Built ETL pipelines using Azure Data Factory, Databricks, NiFi\n- Developed SQL procedures and validation pipelines\n- Implemented CI\/CD using GitHub Actions and Azure DevOps\n- Deployed microservices on AKS with Docker\n- Integrated APIs with OAuth and VPN for secure data exchange\n- Used dbt for transformation modeling\n- Managed Azure SQL, Cosmos DB, and Synapse\n- Monitored workflows using ELK and Azure Monitor\n\nEnvironment\nAzure, Databricks, Snowflake, SQL Server, AKS, GitHub, ELK, Power BI, dbt, NiFi\n\nAT&T | Feb 2018 – Nov 2020\nRole: DATA ENGINEER\nLocation: Dallas, TX\n\n- Developed ETL pipelines for telecom data using Azure Data Factory and Databricks\n- Built reusable C# data integration frameworks\n- Designed Azure Functions for event-driven pipelines\n- Implemented CI\/CD using GitLab\n- Built streaming pipelines using Flume and Apache Beam\n- Performed SQL optimization and data validation\n- Managed AKS clusters and monitoring systems\n\nEnvironment\nAzure, Databricks, SQL Server, Flume, Beam, GitLab, Splunk, Cosmos DB, AKS\n\nHoneywell | Dec 2015 – Jan 2018\nRole: DATA ENGINEER\nLocation: Charlotte, NC\n\n- Built manufacturing data integration platform using Azure\n- Developed ETL pipelines using Talend and ADF\n- Migrated legacy systems to modern platforms\n- Built Airflow workflows and Tableau dashboards\n- Implemented ADLS and Synapse Analytics\n- Developed predictive models using Databricks\n\nEnvironment\nAzure, Talend, ADF, Databricks, ADLS, Tableau, Airflow\n\nRamco Systems | May 2014 – Sep 2015\nRole: ETL TESTER\nLocation: Chennai, India\n\n- Built ETL pipelines using AWS, Informatica, and Talend\n- Processed aviation maintenance data\n- Developed AWS Glue and Redshift pipelines\n- Created Tableau dashboards for analytics\n\nEnvironment\nAWS, Informatica, Talend, S3, Glue, Redshift, Tableau\n\nEDUCATION\nBachelo