{"id":53,"text":"ISABELLA FERREIRA\nQA Lead | Ruby on Rails | RSpec | Shopify | E-Commerce Platforms\n\nCONTACT\nEmail: isabella.ferreira.qa@gmail.com\nPhone: +1 (604) 662-1184\nLocation: Vancouver, BC\nExperience: 10+ years\n\nSUMMARY\n\"Delivering exceptional quality for Ruby on Rails commerce platforms serving millions of merchants worldwide\"\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nAccomplished QA Lead with 10+ years of expertise in Ruby on Rails test automation, RSpec BDD frameworks, and e-commerce platform quality engineering at Shopify, Hootsuite, and SAP. Expert in RSpec, Capybara, FactoryBot, and VCR cassette testing with deep Rails ecosystem knowledge. Strong background in Shopify App testing, Liquid template validation, and Partner API testing. Experienced in multi-tenant Rails platform testing, Sidekiq background jobs, and Action Cable WebSocket testing. Built automated test suites for Shopify apps and enterprise implementations. Expertise in PIPEDA, GDPR, and accessibility testing. Led automation programs achieving 92% test coverage.\n\nCORE TECHNICAL COMPETENCIES\n\nRuby Testing\n- RSpec 3.12+\n- Minitest\n- Capybara 3.x\n- FactoryBot 6.x\n- Faker\n- VCR\n- WebMock\n- Shoulda-Matchers\n- RuboCop\n\nRails Ecosystem\n- Rails 7.x Testing (request, system, job specs)\n- Sidekiq (background jobs)\n- Action Cable (WebSockets)\n- Active Storage\n\nShopify\n- Shopify App Testing\n- Shopify Partner API\n- Liquid Template Testing\n- Shopify Plus\n- Checkout Extensibility\n- Polaris Design System\n\nLanguages\n- Ruby 3.2\n- JavaScript\n- TypeScript\n- SQL (PostgreSQL)\n- Bash\n- Liquid (Shopify)\n\nUI Automation\n- Capybara + Selenium\n- Playwright\n- Cypress\n- Headless Chrome (Ferrum)\n\nAPI Testing\n- RSpec Request Specs\n- HTTParty\n- Faraday\n- Postman\n- GraphQL Admin API\n\nPerformance\n- Artillery\n- k6\n- rack-mini-profiler\n- Bullet (N+1 detection)\n- Skylight APM\n\nCI\/CD\n- GitHub Actions\n- CircleCI\n- Buildkite\n- Docker\n- Heroku CI\n- Semaphore CI\n\nCloud\n- Heroku\n- AWS (EC2, S3, RDS, CloudFront)\n- Shopify Cloud\n\nDatabases\n- PostgreSQL\n- MySQL\n- Redis\n- Elasticsearch\n- Active Record query testing\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nShopify Inc. | Mar 2020 – Present\nRole: QA Lead – Merchant Platform\nLocation: Ottawa, ON (Remote)\n\n- Led QA automation strategy achieving 94% RSpec system coverage\n- Built Capybara + Playwright hybrid automation framework\n- Developed Partner API testing suite covering 80+ endpoints\n- Implemented Liquid template testing framework\n- Designed Checkout Extensibility automation testing\n- Built Shopify Flow automation testing for workflows\n- Implemented Sidekiq background job validation\n- Built Action Cable WebSocket testing for real-time features\n- Automated Shopify Payments testing (cards, payouts, disputes)\n- Implemented N+1 query detection using Bullet gem\n- Built multi-currency testing across 130 currencies\n- Designed Shopify Markets international testing\n- Implemented GDPR\/PIPEDA compliance testing\n- Reduced regression cycle from 4 days to 5 hours\n- Led team of 6 QA engineers\n\nEnvironment\nRSpec, Capybara, FactoryBot, Playwright, Rails 7.x, Sidekiq, Action Cable, PostgreSQL, Redis, GitHub Actions, Docker, Heroku\n\nHootsuite Inc. | Jul 2016 – Feb 2020\nRole: Senior QA Automation Engineer\nLocation: Vancouver, BC\n\n- Built RSpec automation suite for backend services\n- Designed Capybara + Selenium E2E automation\n- Implemented OAuth 2.0 testing for social integrations\n- Built workflow and approval testing frameworks\n- Conducted performance testing using k6\n- Designed multi-tenant SaaS data isolation testing\n- Implemented webhook testing for 30+ event streams\n- Built UTM validation for campaign tracking\n- Designed timezone-aware scheduling validation\n\nEnvironment\nRSpec, Capybara, Rails, Ruby, JavaScript, k6, CircleCI, PostgreSQL, Redis, Docker, Elasticsearch\n\nSAP | Aug 2014 – Jun 2016\nRole: QA Engineer – Commerce Cloud\nLocation: Vancouver, BC\n\n- Performed