{"id":65,"text":"Bharath Kumar\nLead Data Engineer\nCONTACT\n+1 (212) 456-7890\nbharath.kumar@outlook.com\nlinkedin.com\/in\/bharath-kumar\nNew York, NY\nCERTIFICATIONS\n✔ AWS Certified Data Analytics – Specialty\n✔ Apache Kafka Confluent Certified Developer\n✔ Azure AZ-900: Microsoft Azure Fundamentals\n✔ ServiceNow Certified Application Developer (CAD)\n✔ Snowflake SnowPro Core Certification\n✔ HashiCorp Terraform Associate\nEDUCATION\nB.Tech – CS & Engineering\nKL University\n2010 – 2014\nCORE SKILLS\nPython \/ PySpark\nApache Spark \/ Kafka\nAWS \/ Azure \/ GCP\nDagster \/ Airflow\nDSPy \/ LangChain\nSQL \/ Scala\nDocker \/ Kubernetes\nPower BI \/ Tableau\nMLflow \/ SageMaker\nHIPAA \/ PCI-DSS\tPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n▸\tDesigned and deployed production-grade agentic retrieval systems using Python and DSPy to build intelligent agents integrating LLM-driven evaluation frameworks with prompt chaining and context packing techniques for accurate metric computation across large-scale distributed pipelines.\n▸\tBuilt and maintained robust data orchestration pipelines using Dagster and Apache Airflow on AWS, leveraging ECS, EventBridge, Lambda, and S3 to ingest metadata and commit records, implementing backfill procedures and monitoring systems ensuring high reliability and data quality.\n▸\tImplemented advanced LLM prompt optimization frameworks using DSPy to develop eval set creation, feedback-driven correction systems, and structured dataset preparation pipelines with batching and caching strategies for cost-efficient scoring at enterprise scale.\n▸\tDeveloped data modeling architectures using Python and AWS Glue, establishing epic-level associations and work-type classification, implementing anomaly detection algorithms to identify data quality issues while ensuring backend services compute metrics accurately.\n▸\tCreated backend integration services using Python, AWS Glue, Lambda, and S3 to ingest metadata, compute LLM-driven code quality metrics, and expose results via APIs with observability layers maintaining real-time pipeline health visibility across engineering workflows.\n▸\tEngineered eval and feedback loop systems with DSPy frameworks, designing evaluation set structures and automated score correction workflows, integrating backend services to close the loop between scoring, context retrieval, and metric computation.\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\nCloud Platforms: AWS (S3, Glue, EMR, Lambda, Athena, EC2, Redshift, ECS, EKS, SageMaker, CDK, CloudWatch, RDS, SQS, SNS, EventBridge, WAF), GCP (BigQuery, DataProc, GKE, Cloud Functions), Azure (Data Factory, Databricks, SQL, Data Lake, Blob Storage, HDInsight, CosmosDB, Fabric)\nBig Data Ecosystem: Apache Spark, Kafka, Airflow, Dagster, Hive, HDFS, NiFi, Spark Streaming, Zookeeper, Sqoop, Flume, MapReduce, YARN, Flink, Delta Lake, Apache Iceberg\nAI \/ LLM Frameworks: DSPy, LangChain, LangGraph, GPT-4, Claude (Anthropic), AWS SageMaker, MLflow, Prompt Engineering, RAG, Agentic Workflows, MLLIB, Scikit-Learn\nETL & Integration: AWS Glue, Informatica PowerCenter 10.x\/9.6, Talend 5.6, SSIS, Azure Data Factory, SonarQube, PMD, Collibra, ERWIN, E\/R Studio\nDatabases & Warehousing: Teradata 15\/14, MySQL, Oracle 11g\/10g, MS SQL Server 2014\/2012, Snowflake, Amazon Redshift, AWS RDS, CosmosDB, Azure SQL, Spanner\nProgramming Languages: Python, Scala, Java, PySpark, SQL, T-SQL, Unix Shell, TypeScript, Spring Boot\nDevOps & Containerization: Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, Git, AWS CDK, Terraform, AWS WAF, Prometheus, Grafana\nReporting & BI Tools: Tableau, Power BI, Splunk, Semarchy, EHR, Collibra Data Catalog\nML \/ Python Libraries: NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-Learn, Matplotlib, Gradient Boosting, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, Decision Tree\nMethodologies: Agile \/ Scrum, Waterfall, SDLC, CI\/CD, DataOps, MLOps, HIPAA\/HITECH, PCI-DSS, SOX, GLBA, GDPR, FAA\/IATA Compliance\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\nAetna Health  |  Lead Data Engineer  |  August 2023 – Present\n▸\tDesigned and deployed agentic retrieval workflows using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph to build context-aware agents enabling automated scoring and quality metric computation while ensuring HIPAA-compliant audit trails across AWS S3, Lambda, and Glue.\n▸\tMigrated legacy orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster across 40+ production pipelines on AWS ECS and EKS, implementing retries, backfills, scheduling, and data quality alerts with Power BI and Collibra frameworks.\n▸\tBuilt production-grade LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy, integrating prompt optimization with GPT-4 and Claude on AWS SageMaker, leveraging MLflow for model versioning, eval set generation, and continuous feedback loops under HIPAA-compliant governance.\n▸\tEngineered backend services using Python, AWS Lambda, EventBridge, and AWS CDK to ingest metadata from GitHub and Jenkins, computing quality signals and anomalies exposed through RESTful APIs and Power BI dashboards under HIPAA compliance.\n▸\tOrchestrated large-scale backfills using Dagster and AWS Glue, processing over 10M records with batching, caching, and DSPy-based score optimization, ensuring data quality captured in AWS CloudWatch and Collibra lineage tracking.\n▸\tImplemented SonarQube integration for code-quality scoring, linking static analysis with PR metadata and commit history, building Jira-integrated workflows for epic\/work-type classification and automated tagging ensuring HIPAA-compliant metadata governance.\n▸\tDeveloped AI\/ML pipelines using MLLIB and Numpy to predict patient readmission risk, orchestrated with Airflow for ingestion and model retraining, ensuring HIPAA-compliant data handling, HL7 interoperability, and audit trails aligned with HITECH regulations.\nJPMorgan Chase  |  Sr. Data Engineer  |  October 2020 – July 2023\n▸\tDesigned and deployed production-grade data pipelines using Python and Dagster on AWS, integrating Lambda, S3, Glue, and ECS for PCI-DSS-compliant financial workflows with automated retries, backfills, and observability including metrics, traces, and logs.\n▸\tBuilt retrieval agents using Python and DSPy to extract historical code context from GitHub, implementing prompt chaining and context packing for LLM optimization, ensuring SOX and GLBA-compliant secure audit trails across financial pipelines.\n▸\tMigrated orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster, enhancing artifact linking across Jira, GitHub, and banking systems while exposing quality metrics to Power BI dashboards maintaining PCI-DSS and SOX compliance.\n▸\tDeveloped anomaly detection and data quality monitoring using Python, AWS Glue, and CloudWatch, identifying deviations from SonarQube and PMD, triggering automated alerts and implementing DSPy-based score correction.\n▸\tImplemented AWS WAF rules and security policies mitigating SQL injection, XSS, and DDoS attacks, integrating CloudWatch monitoring and geo-blocking to ensure GLBA compliance for digital banking platforms.\n▸\tDeveloped infrastructure-as-code templates using AWS CDK in TypeScript to provision EC2, VPCs, IAM roles, and backup policies for loan origination systems, enforcing least-privilege access and PCI-DSS compliance.\nSouthwest Airlines  |  Data Engineer \/ Data Analyst  |  December 2017 – September 2020\n▸\tDesigned and deployed production-grade data pipelines using Python and Apache Airflow ingesting metadata from GitHub, integrating AWS Lambda and EventBridge for real-time processing ensuring SOC 2 audit trails and FAA\/IATA compliance.\n▸\tBuilt end-to-end data modeling frameworks using Python to link PRs and commits with Dagster pipelines, implementing Prometheus and Grafana dashboards for anomaly detection and aviation quality monitoring.\n▸\tEngineered retrieval agents using Python to extract contextual metadata from GitHub, integrating SonarQube outputs into AWS S3 data lakes and computing technical debt metrics exposed via Power BI.\n▸\tBuilt observability frameworks using Prometheus, Grafana, and CloudWatch, tracking Airflow DAG execution, Glue job success rates, and Lambda invocation patterns ensuring SOC 2 compliance.\n▸\tDeveloped analytics platforms using Python, AWS RDS, and Power BI to generate quality metrics, correlating metadata with Jira epics and designing schemas in ERWIN aligned with FAA documentation standards.\nIBM Corporation  |  Data Engineer \/ Migration Specialist  |  February 2016 – November 2017\n▸\tBuilt an Enterprise Data Integration platform using Azure Cloud, improving data integration efficiency by 40% and enabling seamless data flow across global systems consolidating telemetry from thousands of distributed devices.\n▸\tDeveloped scalable data ingestion pipelines using Talend ETL and Azure Data Factory, processing large volumes of monitoring and security appliance data for downstream operational analytics.\n▸\tImplemented Azure SQL Database and Data Lake Storage for structured metrics and scalable retention of semi-structured traffic data, supporting long-term security analysis and capacity planning.\n▸\tDeveloped predictive capacity forecasting models using Azure Databricks, analyzing historical trends to improve bandwidth planning accuracy and support proactive infrastructure investment decisions.\n▸\tCreated real-time network anomaly detection solutions using streaming analytics, enabling early identification of security threats and performance degradation across high-volume event streams.\nSnapdeal  |  ETL Developer  |  August 2014 – December 2015\n▸\tBuilt a scalable ETL pipeline using AWS Services, Informatica, and Talend integrating data from multiple e-commerce platforms and inventory systems to support high-volume daily transaction processing.\n▸\tDesigned AWS Glue jobs to catalog, transform, and load curated sales and inventory data into Amazon Redshift, optimizing storage layouts for efficient analytical queries supporting category-level insights.\n▸\tAutomated ETL job scheduling using AWS Lambda and CloudWatch Events, improving reliability of time-sen