{"id":69,"text":"VENKATESH\nSr. Big Data Engineer\n10+ Years Experience\n\nPhone: +1 (972) 234-5678\nEmail: venkatesh@gmail.com\nLinkedIn: linkedin.com\/in\/venkatesh\nLocation: Dallas, TX\n\n--------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\n• Designed and deployed production-grade agentic retrieval systems using Python and DSPy to build intelligent agents integrating LLM-driven evaluation frameworks with prompt chaining and context packing techniques for accurate metric computation across large-scale distributed pipelines.\n• Built and maintained robust data orchestration pipelines using Dagster and Apache Airflow on AWS, leveraging ECS, EventBridge, Lambda, and S3 to ingest metadata and commit records, implementing backfill procedures and monitoring systems ensuring high reliability and data quality.\n• Implemented advanced LLM prompt optimization frameworks using DSPy to develop eval set creation, feedback-driven correction systems, and structured dataset preparation pipelines with batching and caching strategies for cost-efficient scoring at enterprise scale.\n• Developed data modeling architectures using Python and AWS Glue, establishing epic-level associations and work-type classification, implementing anomaly detection algorithms to identify data quality issues while ensuring backend services compute metrics accurately.\n• Created backend integration services using Python, AWS Glue, Lambda, and S3 to ingest metadata, compute LLM-driven code quality metrics, and expose results via APIs with observability layers maintaining real-time pipeline health visibility across engineering workflows.\n• Engineered eval and feedback loop systems with DSPy frameworks, designing evaluation set structures and automated score correction workflows, integrating backend services to close the loop between scoring, context retrieval, and metric computation.\n\n--------------------------------------------------\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n• AWS Certified Data Analytics – Specialty\n• Snowflake SnowPro Core Certified\n• Microsoft Azure Data Engineer Associate (DP-203)\n• Certified Kubernetes Application Developer (CKAD)\n• Tableau Server Certified Associate\n• ServiceNow Certified System Administrator (CSA)\n\n--------------------------------------------------\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nCloud Platforms:\nAWS (S3, Glue, EMR, Lambda, Athena, EC2, Redshift, ECS, EKS, SageMaker, CDK, CloudWatch, RDS, SQS, SNS, EventBridge, WAF),\nGCP (BigQuery, DataProc, GKE, Cloud Functions),\nAzure (Data Factory, Databricks, SQL, Data Lake, Blob Storage, HDInsight, CosmosDB, Fabric)\n\nBig Data Ecosystem:\nApache Spark, Kafka, Airflow, Dagster, Hive, HDFS, NiFi, Spark Streaming, Zookeeper, Sqoop, Flume, MapReduce, YARN, Flink, Delta Lake, Apache Iceberg\n\nAI \/ LLM Frameworks:\nDSPy, LangChain, LangGraph, GPT-4, Claude (Anthropic), AWS SageMaker, MLflow, Prompt Engineering, RAG, Agentic Workflows, MLLIB, Scikit-Learn\n\nETL & Integration:\nAWS Glue, Informatica PowerCenter, Talend, SSIS, Azure Data Factory, SonarQube, PMD, Collibra, ERWIN, ER Studio\n\nDatabases & Warehousing:\nTeradata, MySQL, Oracle, MS SQL Server, Snowflake, Amazon Redshift, AWS RDS, CosmosDB, Azure SQL, Spanner\n\nProgramming Languages:\nPython, Scala, Java, PySpark, SQL, T-SQL, Unix Shell, TypeScript, Spring Boot\n\nDevOps & Containerization:\nDocker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, Git, AWS CDK, Terraform, AWS WAF, Prometheus, Grafana\n\nReporting & BI Tools:\nTableau, Power BI, Splunk, Semarchy, EHR, Collibra Data Catalog\n\nML \/ Python Libraries:\nNumPy, Pandas, Scikit-Learn, Matplotlib, Gradient Boosting, Random Forest, Logistic Regression, Decision Tree\n\nMethodologies:\nAgile \/ Scrum, Waterfall, SDLC, CI\/CD, DataOps, MLOps, HIPAA, HITECH, PCI-DSS, SOX, GLBA, GDPR, FAA\/IATA Compliance\n\n--------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nCigna Corporation\nSr. Big Data Engineer\nAugust 2023 – Present\n\n• Designed and deployed agentic retrieval workflows using Python, LangChain, and LangGraph to build context-aware agents enabling automated scoring and quality metric computation while ensuring HIPAA-compliant audit trails across AWS S3, Lambda, and Glue.\n• Migrated orchestration from Apache Airflow to Dagster across 40+ production pipelines on AWS ECS and EKS with retries, backfills, scheduling, and monitoring.\n• Built LLM-driven scoring systems using DSPy with GPT-4 and Claude via AWS SageMaker and MLflow.\n• Engineered backend services using AWS Lambda, EventBridge, and CDK integrating GitHub and Jenkins metadata.\n• Orchestrated large-scale backfills processing 10M+ records with caching and optimization.\n• Integrated SonarQube for code quality scoring and Jira-based metadata classification.\n• Developed ML pipelines for patient readmission prediction using MLLIB and NumPy.\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nAmerican Express\nSr. Data Engineer\nOctober 2020 – July 2023\n\n• Designed data pipelines using Python and Dagster on AWS ensuring PCI-DSS compliance.\n• Built retrieval agents using DSPy and GitHub metadata.\n• Migrated Airflow pipelines to Dagster improving orchestration.\n• Implemented anomaly detection and monitoring systems using AWS Glue and CloudWatch.\n• Developed infrastructure using AWS CDK and TypeScript.\n• Implemented AWS WAF security policies.\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nSouthwest Airlines\nData Engineer \/ Data Analyst\nDecember 2017 – September 2020\n\n• Built Airflow pipelines integrating AWS Lambda and EventBridge.\n• Developed data modeling frameworks and observability systems.\n• Built dashboards using Prometheus, Grafana, and Power BI.\n• Integrated SonarQube outputs into AWS S3.\n• Developed analytics systems using AWS RDS and Power BI.\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nNokia Networks\nData Engineer \/ Migration Specialist\nFebruary 2016 – November 2017\n\n• Built enterprise data integration platform on Azure.\n• Developed pipelines using Talend and Azure Data Factory.\n• Implemented Azure SQL Database and Data Lake.\n• Built predictive models using Azure Databricks.\n• Created real-time anomaly detection systems.\n\n--------------------------------------------------\n\nReliance Jio\nETL Developer\nAugust 2014 – December 2015\n\n• Built ETL pipelines using AWS, Informatica, and Talend.\n• Designed AWS Glue jobs and Redshift pipelines.\n• Automated scheduling using Lambda and CloudWatch.\n• Built Tableau dashboards for analytics.\n\n--------------------------------------------------\nEDUCATION\n\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science & Engineering\nKoneru Lakshmaiah University\n2010 – 2014\n\n--------------------------------------------------","label":[[0,9,"PERSON_NAME"],[10,31,"JOB_TITLE"],[32,35,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[61,78,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[85,105,"EMAIL"],[116,141,"LINKEDIN"],[152,162,"LOCATION"],[310,317,"SKILL"],[321,326,"SKILL"],[388,399,"SKILL"],[490,523,"SKILL"],[590,598,"SKILL"],[602,616,"SKILL"],[620,623,"SKILL"],[636,639,"SKILL"],[641,652,"SKILL"],[654,660,"SKILL"],[666,669,"SKILL"],[855,866,"SKILL"],[872,877,"SKILL"],[1119,1126,"SKILL"],[1130,1138,"SKILL"],[1386,1392,"SKILL"],[1393,1402,"SKILL"],[1404,1410,"SKILL"],[1416,1419,"SKILL"],[1503,1508,"SKILL"],[1662,1677,"SKILL"],[1934,1962,"CERTIFICATION"],[1976,2009,"CERTIFICATION"],[2012,2052,"CERTIFICATION"],[2063,2112,"CERTIFICATION"],[2115,2149,"CERTIFICATION"],[2152,2201,"CERTIFICATION"],[2287,2291,"SKILL"],[2292,2294,"SKILL"],[2296,2300,"SKILL"],[2302,2305,"SKILL"],[2307,2313,"SKILL"],[2315,2321,"SKILL"],[2323,2326,"SKILL"],[2328,2336,"SKILL"],[2338,2341,"SKILL"],[2343,2346,"SKILL"],[2348,2357,"SKILL"],[2359,2362,"SKILL"],[2364,2374,"SKILL"],[2376,2379,"SKILL"],[2381,2384,"SKILL"],[2386,2389,"SKILL"],[2410,2414,"SKILL"],[2415,2423,"SKILL"],[2425,2433,"SKILL"],[2435,2438,"SKILL"],[2440,2455,"SKILL"],[2458,2464,"SKILL"],[2465,2477,"SKILL"],[2479,2489,"SKILL"],[2491,2494,"SKILL"],[2494,2505,"SKILL"],[2506,2