{"id":73,"text":"BUNNY\nChicago, IL • (555) 987-6543 • bunny.hr@email.com\nlinkedin.com\/in\/sarahjenkins-hr • shrm.org\/profile\/sjenkins\n\nEXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n\nVisionary and high-impact Senior HR Executive with over 9+ years of leadership experience overseeing global human resources operations for Fortune 500 organizations and high-growth technology sectors. Expert in transforming HR departments from administrative cost centers into strategic business engines.\n\nProven success in architecting scalable talent acquisition frameworks, designing competitive total rewards programs, and fostering inclusive corporate cultures that drive employee retention and high performance. Specialized in post-merger integration (M&A), large-scale workforce restructuring, and the implementation of advanced HRIS solutions (Workday, SAP SuccessFactors).\n\nA trusted advisor to C-suite executives on organizational health, executive compensation, and succession planning.\n\nCORE COMPETENCIES & HR EXPERTISE\n\nStrategic Planning:\nOrganizational Design, Succession Planning, M&A Integration, Change Management, Crisis Management\n\nTalent Management:\nGlobal Talent Acquisition, Employer Branding, Performance Management, Executive Search, Workforce Planning\n\nEmployee Relations:\nConflict Resolution, Labor Law Compliance (EEOC, FLSA, FMLA), Workplace Investigations, Union Negotiations\n\nTotal Rewards:\nCompensation Modeling, Benefits Administration, Equity\/Stock Option Planning, Wellness Programs, Executive Pay\n\nLearning & Development:\nLeadership Coaching, Skill Gap Analysis, Onboarding Optimization, Diversity & Inclusion (DEI)\n\nHR Technology:\nWorkday, Oracle HCM, BambooHR, Lever\/Greenhouse ATS, Tableau, ADP GlobalView\n\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nChief People Officer\nNexus Financial Group | Chicago, IL\nMarch 2021 – Present\n\n• Designed and executed global HR strategy for a workforce of 2,500+ employees across North America, EMEA, and APAC  \n• Led “Culture First” transformation increasing eNPS from +12 to +54 within 18 months  \n• Managed HR integration for 3 acquisitions totaling $450M with 95% retention  \n• Built Tableau-based workforce analytics dashboard reducing attrition by 20%  \n• Advised CEO and Board on compensation, governance, and succession planning  \n• Redesigned bonus structure aligned with ESG goals  \n\nSenior Director of HR\nTechStream Solutions | Austin, TX\nJune 2017 – February 2021\n\n• Scaled company from 150 to 900 employees while maintaining hiring quality  \n• Replaced annual reviews with continuous feedback model improving engagement by 35%  \n• Built DEI programs increasing leadership diversity by 40%  \n• Managed global payroll and compliance across UK and Germany  \n• Controlled $15M HR budget with 5% cost savings  \n\nHR Business Partner (HRBP)\nZenith Manufacturing | Detroit, MI\nAugust 2014 – May 2017\n\n• Led union negotiations with zero work stoppages  \n• Created company-wide employee handbook for 5,000+ employees  \n• Developed supervisor training reducing safety incidents by 25%  \n• Built university hiring pipeline contributing 40% of entry-level hires  \n\nHR CASE STUDIES & STRATEGIC PROJECTS\n\nGlobal HRIS Implementation (Workday)\n\nChallenge:\nMultiple disconnected HR systems across countries causing data inconsistencies  \n\nSolution:\n• Led 14-month Workday global rollout  \n• Trained 200+ managers globally  \n\nResult:\n• Unified HR data system  \n• Reduced payroll processing time by 40%  \n\nPost-Acquisition Cultural Integration\n\nChallenge:\nCultural mismatch causing high attrition  \n\nSolution:\n• Implemented “Best of Both Worlds” integration model  \n• Introduced integration buddy program  \n\nResult:\n• Attrition normalized within 4 months  \n• Achieved early milestone delivery  \n\nEDUCATION\n\nMaster of Business Administration (MBA)\nNorthwestern University – Kellogg School of Management | 2014\n\nBachelor of Science in Psychology\nMichigan State University | 2011\n\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n• SHRM Senior Certified Professional (SHRM-SCP)  \n• Senior Professional in Human Resources (SPHR)  \n• Global Professional in Human Resources (GPHR)  \n\nDETAILED HR EXPERTISE\n\nEmployee Engagement & Retention:\n• Recognition programs and peer rewards  \n• Stay interviews for high-potential employees  \n• Wellness programs across mental and financial health  \n\nLegal Compliance & Risk:\n• HR audits (I-9, FLSA, payroll)  \n• Policy updates for remote workforce  \n• Internal investigations  \n\nTotal Rewards Strategy:\n• Market benchmarking (Radford, Mercer)  \n• Equity and stock planning  \n• Innovative benefits (fertility support, unlimited PTO)  \n\nEXECUTIVE MANAGEMENT\n\n• Board-level reporting on HR and ESG metrics  \n• Executive compensation planning  \n• Crisis management leadership  \n\nINDUSTRY CONTRIBUTIONS\n\n• Board Member – Chicago HR Strategy Forum  \n• Mentor – HR Open Source  \n• Volunteer – Career coaching for veterans  \n\nCAREER TIMELINE\n\n• 2014–2015: Labor relations and HR foundations  \n• 2016–2017: Regional HR leadership  \n• 2018–2019: Scaling tech organizations  \n• 2020–2021: Remote workforce transformation  \n• 2022–Present: Strategic HR leadership and M&A  ","label":[[0,5,"PERSON_NAME"],[6,17,"LOCATION"],[20,34,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[37,55,"EMAIL"],[56,86,"LINKEDIN"],[192,194,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[694,697,"SKILL"],[699,722,"SKILL"],[797,815,"SKILL"],[839,858,"SKILL"],[989,1010,"SKILL"],[1012,1031,"SKILL"],[1033,1048,"SKILL"],[1050,1066,"SKILL"],[1069,1086,"SKILL"],[1107,1132,"SKILL"],[1133,1151,"SKILL"],[1153,1175,"SKILL"],[1177,1194,"SKILL"],[1195,1213,"SKILL"],[1235,1254,"SKILL"],[1255,1276,"SKILL"],[1278,1282,"SKILL"],[1284,1288,"SKILL"],[1290,1294,"SKILL"],[1297,1320,"SKILL"],[1323,1341,"SKILL"],[1381,1405,"SKILL"],[1406,1412,"SKILL"],[1413,1434,"SKILL"],[1435,1453,"SKILL"],[1515,1533,"SKILL"],[1613,1623,"SKILL"],[1625,1633,"SKILL"],[1641,1652,"SKILL"],[1652,1655,"SKILL"],[1657,1664,"SKILL"],[1666,1680,"SKILL"],[1707,1726,"JOB_TITLE"]