{"id":74,"text":"SACHIN RAMESH TENDULKAR\nEnterprise Architect  •  Cloud Strategy  •  Digital Transformation\n📧 sachin.tendulkar@globetech.io   |   📱 +91-92231-00001   |   📍 Mumbai, Maharashtra\nlinkedin.com\/in\/sachintendulkar-arch   |   github.com\/sachin-arch   |   TOGAF 9.2 Certified\n\n\nPROFESSIONAL PROFILE\nDistinguished Enterprise Architect with 15 years of progressive experience designing and governing enterprise-scale IT landscapes for Fortune 500 organisations. Deep expertise in cloud strategy, application rationalisation, integration architecture and IT operating model design. Trusted advisor to CTO and Board-level executives, with a demonstrated ability to bridge business strategy and technology capability.\n\nAREAS OF EXPERTISE\n–\tTOGAF & Zachman Framework\n–\tCloud Architecture (AWS\/Azure)\n–\tAPI & Integration Strategy\n–\tApplication Portfolio Mgmt.\t–\tSecurity Architecture (SABSA)\n–\tData Architecture & Governance\n–\tSolution Design & Patterns\n–\tEnterprise Service Bus (ESB)\t–\tTechnology Roadmapping\n–\tDigital Transformation Strategy\n–\tEA Tooling: Sparx, ArchiMate\n–\tStakeholder Advisory\n\nCAREER HISTORY\nChief Enterprise Architect\tOct 2018 – Present\nGlobeTech Innovations  |  Mumbai \/ London\n–\tDefined and governed the 5-year technology architecture roadmap for a $2.5B global financial services group spanning 22 countries.\n–\tLed cloud-first strategy resulting in 72% of workloads migrated to Azure within 24 months; achieved 34% infrastructure cost reduction.\n–\tRationalised application portfolio from 1,200 to 680 applications through capability mapping and sunrising of legacy systems.\n–\tEstablished Architecture Review Board (ARB) and 48 reusable architecture patterns adopted across 35 business units.\n–\tDirected solution architecture for a core insurance platform replacement (₹220Cr programme); delivered on time within budget.\n–\tEngaged directly with Group CTO, Chief Risk Officer and CISO to ensure architecture governance and regulatory alignment (DORA, GDPR).\nPrincipal Solution Architect\tJun 2014 – Sep 2018\nSapience Technology Group  |  Pune, India\n–\tDesigned integration architecture for a large public-sector ERP consolidation programme connecting 60 legacy systems via MuleSoft ESB.\n–\tCreated reference architecture for microservices transition for a leading Indian telecom; programme impacted 40M+ subscribers.\n–\tProvided architecture assurance across 8 concurrent delivery programmes with combined budget of ₹130Cr.\n–\tLed TOGAF-based EA practice establishment including metamodel definition, viewpoint library and tooling onboarding (Sparx EA).\n–\tDelivered architecture training workshops to 120+ engineers and business analysts.\nSenior Solution Architect\tMar 2010 – May 2014\nInfovance Consulting  |  Chennai, India\n–\tArchitected a unified omni-channel commerce platform for a Top-3 Indian retailer integrating 14 disparate legacy systems.\n–\tDesigned service-oriented architecture (SOA) for a healthcare claims processing system handling 500K claims\/month.\n–\tCreated architecture documentation, HLD\/LLD artefacts and NFR compliance checklists across 6 client engagements.\nSystems Analyst\tJul 2007 – Feb 2010\nBrightEdge Technologies  |  Bengaluru, India\n–\tConducted architecture assessments and capacity planning for mid-market clients in BFSI and manufacturing verticals.\n–\tDeveloped data flow diagrams and process models for ERP integrations using IBM WebSphere and Oracle SOA Suite.\n–\tProduced business case analyses for technology investments totalling $4M.\n\nEDUCATION\nM.Tech – Software Systems\t2005 – 2007\nBITS Pilani  |  Distinction  |  Thesis: 'Adaptive Middleware Architectures for Heterogeneous Distributed Systems'\nB.E – Electronics & Communication\t2001 – 2005\nCollege of Engineering, Pune  |  First Class with Distinction\n\nCERTIFICATIONS & PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIPS\n–\tTOGAF 9.2 Level 2 – The Open Group\n–\tAWS Certified Solutions Architect – Professional\n–\tM