{"id":78,"text":"CHERRY \nSenior DevOps & Cloud Infrastructure Engineer\n+91 91234 56780\ncherry.emil@techmail.in\nMumbai, Maharashtra, India\nlinkedin.com\/in\/cherryemil-dev\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nHighly accomplished Senior DevOps & Cloud Infrastructure Engineer with 10+ years of experience architecting and managing enterprise-grade cloud platforms across AWS, Azure, and GCP. Proven expertise in building zero-downtime CI\/CD pipelines, large-scale Kubernetes orchestration, and Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) practices. Delivered measurable impact including 60% reduction in deployment lead time and 99.99% system availability. Strong leader mentoring cross-functional teams and driving DevOps transformation.\n\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nCloud Platforms:\nAWS (EC2, EKS, Lambda, CloudFront, RDS, VPC, IAM, S3, CloudWatch),\nAzure (AKS, Azure DevOps, Functions, Blob Storage),\nGCP (GKE, Compute Engine, Cloud Functions)\n\nCI\/CD & DevOps:\nJenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI\/CD, ArgoCD, Spinnaker, Helm, Flux, CircleCI\n\nContainers & IaC:\nDocker, Kubernetes, Terraform, Ansible, Pulumi, CloudFormation\n\nMonitoring & Observability:\nPrometheus, Grafana, Datadog, ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana),\nJaeger, OpenTelemetry, New Relic, Splunk\n\nProgramming:\nPython, Bash, Go, Node.js, YAML, Shell Scripting\n\nSecurity & Compliance:\nOWASP, HashiCorp Vault, AWS KMS, SAST\/DAST, SOC2, ISO 27001, GDPR\n\nWORK EXPERIENCE\n\nLead DevOps Engineer\nMar 2020 – Present\nNexGen Technologies Ltd. | Mumbai, India\n\n• Architected multi-region AWS infrastructure supporting 30M+ users with 99.99% uptime.\n• Designed GitOps pipelines using ArgoCD and GitHub Actions reducing deployment time from 4 hours to 15 minutes.\n• Migrated Kubernetes clusters to AWS EKS improving scalability and reducing infra costs by 35%.\n• Built centralized observability platform reducing MTTR by 60%.\n• Implemented Infrastructure as Code using Terraform across environments.\n• Led DevOps team and introd