{"id":80,"text":"AMAR\n\nCLOUD SOLUTIONS ARCHITECT  |  AWS & AZURE SPECIALIST  |  AI\/ML ENABLEMENT\n\n+91 87654 32109\namar.cloud@cloudmail.in\nNavi Mumbai, Maharashtra, India\nlinkedin.com\/in\/amar-cloud-arch\n\n◆ EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\nDistinguished Cloud Solutions Architect with 13+ years of experience designing and governing enterprise-grade cloud ecosystems across AWS, Azure, and GCP. Expert in distributed systems, cloud-native transformation, AI\/ML platforms, and large-scale modernization programs. Delivered 40+ enterprise cloud initiatives across BFSI, Telecom, Healthcare, and Retail domains. Trusted advisor to C-level executives, driving cloud strategy, governance, and digital transformation aligned with business goals.\n\n◆ CORE COMPETENCIES & TECHNICAL SKILLS\n\nCloud Architecture:\nAWS (Well-Architected Framework, Control Tower), Azure Landing Zones, GCP Architecture, Multi-Cloud Strategy, Hybrid Cloud, Serverless Architectures, Cloud Cost Optimization (FinOps)\n\nAI\/ML & Data Engineering:\nAWS SageMaker, Azure ML, Databricks, Apache Spark, Delta Lake, Data Lakehouse, MLOps, LLM Fine-tuning, RAG Architectures, Vector Databases (Pinecone, FAISS), MLflow\n\nSecurity & Compliance:\nZero Trust Architecture, AWS IAM, Azure AD, RBAC, HashiCorp Vault, Secrets Management, GDPR, SOC2, ISO 27001, PCI-DSS, HIPAA\n\nInfrastructure & Platforms:\nKubernetes (EKS, AKS, GKE), Docker, Terraform, Pulumi, CloudFormation, Ansible, Service Mesh (Istio, Linkerd), API Gateway, NGINX, Envoy\n\nArchitecture Patterns:\nMicroservices, Event-Driven Architecture, CQRS, Saga, Domain-Driven Design (DDD), Clean Architecture, API-First, Strangler Fig Pattern\n\nProgramming & Tools:\nJava 17, Python, Go, Node.js, SQL, Terraform HCL, Bash, PowerShell, Git, GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket\n\nDevOps & CI\/CD:\nJenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI\/CD, Azure DevOps, ArgoCD, Spinnaker, Helm, Flux, SonarQube\n\nObservability & Monitoring:\nGrafana, Datadog, Prometheus, ELK Stack, Splunk, New Relic, AWS CloudWatch, Azure Monitor, OpenTelemetry\n\nMessaging & Streaming:\nApache Kafka, AWS EventBridge, SNS\/SQS, RabbitMQ, Pulsar\n\n◆ PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nPrincipal Cloud Solutions Architect\nApr 2019 – Present\nHorizon Consulting Group | Navi Mumbai, India\n\n• Leading architecture for multiple enterprise cloud transformation programs exceeding $15M annual cloud spend.\n• Designed enterprise AI\/ML platform using AWS SageMaker enabling faster ML model deployments across multiple teams.\n• Built reusable Terraform Landing Zone framework reducing provisioning time from weeks to hours.\n• Implemented Zero Trust architecture achieving SOC2 and ISO 27001 certifications.\n• Designed enterprise data lakehouse architectures using AWS and Databricks improving analytics performance by 60%.\n• Established enterprise cloud governance frameworks adopted across global organizations.\n• Conduct architecture reviews and strategic advisory for CTO-level stakeholders.\n\nSenior Cloud Architect\nFeb 2016 – Mar 2019\nPinnacle Cloud Services | Bengaluru, India\n\n• Led large-scale cloud migration from on-premise to AWS for mission-critical systems.\n• Designed event-driven systems using Kafka and AWS EventBridge for enterprise integrations.\n• Built serverless architectures reducing operational cost by 75%.\n• Mentored architects and introduced best practices such as ADRs.\n• Delivered cloud readiness and assessment programs for enterprise clients.\n\nSolutions Architect\nJul 2013 – Jan 2016\nDataVista Technologies Pvt. Ltd. | Hyderabad, India\n\n• Designed REST API platforms handling millions of transactions daily.\n• Built big data processing pipelines using Spark and Hadoop ecosystem.\n• Developed cloud migration strategies and enterprise solution architectures.\n• Supported pre-sales architecture leading to multi-million-dollar deal wins.\n\nCloud Engineer\nJun 2011 – Jun 2013\nTechNova Systems | Pune, India\n\n• Implemented AWS-based infrastructure solutions for early-stage cloud adoption.\n• Automated deployments using scripting and configuration tools.\n• Supported production environments ensuring high availability and uptime.\n• Assisted in system monitoring, troubleshooting, and performance tuning.\n\nJunior Software Engineer\nAug 2010 – May 2011\nInfotech Global Solutions | Mumbai, India\n\n• Developed Java-based enterprise applications.\n• Assisted in database design and backend integrations.\n• Supported QA and production issue resolution.\n• Worked on initial DevOps automation scripts and build tools.\n\n◆ CERTIFICATIONS & ACCREDITATIONS\n\n• AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Professional (2023)\n• AWS Certified Machine Learning – Specialty (2023)\n• Microsoft Azure Solutions Architect Expert (2022)\n• Google Professional Cloud Architect (2021)\n• Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) (2022)\n• HashiCorp Terraform Professional (2021)\n\n◆ AWARDS & RECOGNITION\n\n• Cloud Architect of the Year – Horizon Consulting Group (2023)\n• Finalist – AWS Innovation Awards India (2022)\n• Speaker – AWS re:Invent (2022)\n• Speaker – Microsoft Build India (2023)\n• Published Author – IEEE Cloud Computing Journal (2022)\n• Top 2% performance rating across multiple years\n\n◆ EDUCATION\n\nM.Tech in Computer Science & Engineering (Cloud Computing)\nIndian Institute of Technology (IIT), Delhi | 2011 – 2013\nCGPA: 9.2 \/ 10 (Gold Medallist)\n\nB.Tech in Computer Science\nBITS Pilani | 2007 – 2011\nCGPA: 8.9 \/ 10\n\n◆ PROFESSIONAL MEMBERSHIPS & CONTRIBUTIONS\n\n• AWS Community Contributor (2022–Present)\n• Open Source Contributor – Terraform Modules & AWS CDK\n• Mentor for startup founders in cloud architecture\n• Member – Cloud Native Computing Foundation (CNCF)\n\n◆ LANGUAGES\n\nEnglish (Professional)\nHindi (Native)\nMarathi (Native)\nGujarati (Conversational)","label":[[0,4,"PERSON_NAME"],[6,31,"JOB_TITLE"],[35,58,"JOB_TITLE"],[61,79,"JOB_TITLE"],[81,96,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[97,120,"EMAIL"],[121,152,"LOCATION"],[153,184,"LINKEDIN"],[250,254,"EXP