{"id":82,"text":"LAKSHMI\nChief Technology Architect & Head of Java Engineering\n\nBengaluru, India • +91 90000 12345 • lakshmi.architect@cloudenterprise.io\nlinkedin.com\/in\/lakshmi-java-architect • Indian Citizen\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n------------------------------------------------------------\nTechnically formidable Chief Technology Architect and Engineering Leader with over 12 years \nof experience in designing, developing, and deploying enterprise-scale distributed systems \nusing the Java ecosystem.\n\nDistinguished for architecting the \"Nova-Cloud\" core engine, supporting over 500 million \nconcurrent WebSocket connections with sub-20ms latency.\n\nA visionary leader managing engineering organizations of 120+ developers, bridging low-level \nJVM optimization with high-level business strategy. Expert in transforming monolithic systems \ninto cloud-native microservices, achieving 40% infrastructure cost reduction and 600% increase \nin deployment frequency.\n\nRecognized thought leader in reactive programming (Project Loom, Vert.x) and high-performance \nJava systems. Proven experience managing $150M+ annual R&D budgets across global teams in \nNorth America, Europe, and APAC.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n------------------------------------------------------------\n• Architectural Leadership: Microservices, Event-Driven Architecture, DDD, Clean Architecture  \n• Java Expertise: JVM Tuning (ZGC, G1GC), Spring Boot 3.x, Quarkus, GraalVM  \n• Distributed Systems: Istio, API Gateways, Redis, Hazelcast  \n• Leadership: Agile Transformation, OKRs, Talent Strategy, P&L Ownership  \n• Cloud & DevOps: Kubernetes, Terraform, AWS, GCP  \n• Data Engineering: Kafka, Cassandra, PostgreSQL, Elasticsearch  \n• Security: OAuth2, JWT, mTLS, SOC2, PCI-DSS  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nTECHNICAL SKILLS\n------------------------------------------------------------\nLanguages:\nJava 17\/21, Kotlin, Scala, Go, Python, Bash, SQL\n\nFrameworks:\nSpring Boot, Quarkus, Micronaut, Vert.x, Akka, Jakarta EE\n\nReactive Stack:\nProject Reactor, RxJava, Mutiny, Akka Streams\n\nDatabases:\nPostgreSQL, Oracle, MySQL, MongoDB, Cassandra, Neo4j, DynamoDB\n\nMessaging:\nKafka, RabbitMQ, Pulsar, SQS\/SNS\n\nDevOps & Cloud:\nKubernetes, Docker, OpenShift, Terraform, AWS CDK, Pulumi\n\nMonitoring:\nPrometheus, Grafana, Datadog, Splunk, New Relic\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nChief Java Architect & VP Engineering\nNova Cloud Systems Pvt Ltd | 2021 – Present\nBengaluru, India\n\n• Leading a global engineering organization of 125+ engineers across multiple regions  \n• Managing $150M+ annual engineering and cloud infrastructure budget  \n\nKey Achievements:\n\n• Architected a global WebSocket platform handling 500M+ concurrent connections  \n• Reduced memory footprint by 70%, saving $40M annually  \n\n• Led Zero-Trust security migration using OAuth2, OIDC, mTLS  \n• Achieved full SOC2 Type II compliance across systems  \n\n• Standardized JVM tuning across 4000+ microservices  \n• Reduced latency from 150ms to 8ms  \n\n• Migrated monolithic systems to cloud-native microservices  \n• Improved availability to 99.995%  \n\n• Built internal developer platform reducing service creation time from 3 weeks to 20 minutes  \n\n• Established Architecture Guild mentoring 30+ senior engineers  \n• Achieved 90%+ retention rate  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nDirector of Backend Engineering\nQuantum FinTech Solutions | 2017 – 2021\nHyderabad, India\n\n• Led development of high-frequency trading platforms  \n• Managed team of 80 backend engineers  \n\nKey Achievements:\n\n• Built high-performance order matching engine  \n• Achieved 2M transactions per second  \n\n• Implemented event sourcing architecture using Kafka  \n• Ensured full audit compliance  \n\n• Designed resilient microservices with circuit breaker patterns  \n• Maintained 100% uptime during peak loads  \n\n• Led CI\/CD transformation  \n• Reduced production defects by 45%  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nLead Software Architect\nMedSys Health Technologies | 2014 – 2017\nPune, India\n\n• Led architecture of healthcare interoperability platform  \n\nKey Achievements:\n\n• Developed FHIR-compliant API platform supporting 12M+ patients  \n• Reduced ETL processing time from 12 hours to 2 hours  \n\n• Implemented HIPAA-compliant logging and monitoring system  \n\n• Migrated on-prem systems to AWS cloud  \n• Saved $6M infrastructure cost  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSenior Java Engineer\nLogiChain Analytics Pvt Ltd | 2011 – 2014\nChennai, India\n\nKey Achievements:\n\n• Converted monolithic logistics system into microservices  \n• Improved performance by 300%  \n\n• Migrated 500M+ records to PostgreSQL cluster  \n• Ensured zero downtime  \n\n• Introduced automated testing practices  \n• Increased code coverage to 85%  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nKEY PROJECTS\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nProject Nova-Core: Distributed Data Platform\nRole: Chief Architect\n\n• Built distributed data platform handling exabyte-scale telemetry  \n• Achieved throughput of 100GB\/sec per cluster  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nProject Quantum Trade Engine\nRole: Principal Architect\n\n• Built low-latency trading engine with microsecond-level response times  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nProject DevFlow Platform\nRole: Engineering Director\n\n• Automated developer workflows  \n• Reduced development effort by 70%  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nLEADERSHIP & MANAGEMENT\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n• Scaled engineering team from 20 to 125 engineers  \n• Built global hiring strategy  \n\n• Implemented OKR-driven delivery model  \n• Increased engineering productivity by 35%  \n\n• Led crisis management for zero-day vulnerabilities  \n• Secured 4000+ services in under 6 hours  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROCESS IMPROVEMENTS\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n• Built automated JVM profiling system  \n• Reduced MTTR by 80%  \n\n• Developed self-healing Kubernetes operators  \n\n• Implemented chaos engineering pipelines  \n• Reduced production incidents by 50%  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nSTRATEGIC VISION\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n• Driving transition to Cloud-Native Java using GraalVM  \n• Promoting multi-cloud architecture for vendor independence  \n• Advocating ethical AI usage in software development  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nBOARD & INDUSTRY CONTRIBUTIONS\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n• Technology advisor for multiple fintech startups  \n• Led technical due diligence for acquisitions worth $2B  \n\n• Open source contributor to Spring Framework ecosystem  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nEDUCATION\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nM.Tech in Distributed Systems  \nIndian Institute of Technology (IIT), Delhi  \n\nB.Tech in Computer Science  \nJawaharlal Nehru Technological University  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCERTIFICATIONS\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n• AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Professional  \n• Oracle Certified Java Developer  \n• Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)  \n• CISSP  \n• Google Cloud Professional Architect  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nTOOLS & TECHNOLOGIES\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nJava, Spring Boot, Quarkus, Kafka, Kubernetes, Terraform, AWS, GCP, \nPostgreSQL, Cassandra, Redis, Elasticsearch, Prometheus, Grafana  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPUBLICATIONS & SPEAKING\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n• Speaker – Global Java Conference 2023  \n• Speaker – Cloud Architecture Summit 2022  \n\n• Published research papers on JVM optimization and distributed systems  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nLANGUAGES\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nEnglish – Fluent  \nHindi – Native  \nKannada – Conversational  \n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nGLOBAL EXPERIENCE\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nWorked with teams across:\nIndia, USA, Germany, UK, Singapore","label":[[0,7,"PERSON_NAME"],[8,61,"JOB_TITLE"],[63,79,"LOCATION"],[81,97,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[99,136,"EMAIL"],[137,175,"LINKEDIN"],[178,192,"LOCATION"],[360,387,"JOB_TITLE"],[420,422,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[458,468,"SKILL"],[474,484,"SKILL"],[484,521,"SKILL"],[532,547,"SKILL"],[585,595,"SKILL"],[597,608,"SKILL"],[650,660,"SKILL"],[790,794,"SKILL"],[1058,1070,"SKILL"],[1070,1078,"SKILL"],[1102,1114,"SKILL"],[1157,1161,"SKILL"],[1220,1224,"SKILL"],[1395,1408,"SKILL"],[1409,1435,"SKILL"],[1437,1440,"SKILL"],[1442,1462,"SKILL"],[1465,1470,"SKILL"],[1481,1491,"SKILL"],[1493,1496,"SKILL"],[1498,1502,"SKILL"],[1504,1520,"SKILL"],[1522,1529,"SKILL"],[1531,1540,"SKILL"],[1542,1562,"SKILL"],[1564,1569,"SKILL"],[1570,1583,"SKILL"],[1618,1638,"SKILL"],[1640,1644,"SKILL"],[1646,1661,"SKILL"],[1663,1667,"SKILL"],[1681,1687,"SKILL"],[1689,1695,"SKILL"],[1697,1707,"SKILL"],[1709,1718,"SKILL"],[1720,1723,"SKILL"],[1725,1730,"SKILL"],[1751,1756,"SKILL"],[1758,1767