{"id":83,"text":"VAMSI KRISHNA REDDY\nSenior DevOps Engineer & AWS Cloud Specialist\nHyderabad, Telangana  |  vamsi.reddy.devops@techmail.com  |  +91 98765 43210  |  linkedin.com\/in\/vamsikrishna-devops\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nResults-driven Senior DevOps Engineer with 8+ years of hands-on experience designing, automating, and optimizing cloud infrastructure on AWS. Proven ability to lead CI\/CD transformation initiatives, reduce deployment cycles, and implement robust monitoring frameworks for high-traffic production environments. Expertise in Kubernetes orchestration, Terraform automation, and DevSecOps practices serving clients in BFSI, healthcare, and e-commerce domains. Passionate about building resilient, cost-efficient cloud platforms that empower development teams to ship faster with greater confidence.\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n\n•\tCloud Infrastructure: AWS Architecture Design, Multi-Account Strategy, VPC Networking, Cost Optimization, Landing Zone Setup\n•\tAutomation & IaC: Terraform Modules, Ansible Playbooks, AWS CloudFormation, GitOps Workflows, Self-Healing Infrastructure\n•\tCI\/CD Engineering: Jenkins Pipeline Design, GitHub Actions, ArgoCD, Blue-Green Deployments, Canary Releases, Rollback Automation\n•\tObservability: SLO\/SLA Monitoring, Alerting Strategy, Log Aggregation, Distributed Tracing, Incident Management\n•\tSecurity & Compliance: IAM Governance, Secrets Management, VAPT Remediation, PCI-DSS Controls, Vulnerability Scanning Automation\nTECHNICAL SKILLS INVENTORY\n\n•\tCloud Platforms: AWS (EC2, EKS, Lambda, S3, RDS, Route53, CloudFront, SQS, SNS, IAM, CloudWatch), Azure (AKS, App Services, DevOps Pipelines)\n•\tContainerization & Orchestration: Docker, Kubernetes (K8s), Helm Charts, Kustomize, Istio Service Mesh, Amazon ECS\/Fargate\n•\tInfrastructure as Code: Terraform (v1.x), AWS CloudFormation, Ansible, AWS CDK, Packer\n•\tCI\/CD Tools: Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI\/CD, ArgoCD, AWS CodePipeline, CodeBuild, Spinnaker\n•\tDatabases & Storage: PostgreSQL, MySQL, Amazon RDS, DynamoDB, Redis, MongoDB, Amazon S3, EFS\n•\tMonitoring & Observability: Prometheus, Grafana, Datadog, CloudWatch, ELK Stack, PagerDuty, Jaeger (Distributed Tracing)\n•\tScripting & Programming: Python, Bash\/Shell, PowerShell, Go (Golang), YAML, JSON\n•\tSecurity Tools: HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, SonarQube, Trivy, AWS GuardDuty, AWS Security Hub\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nHORIZON BANCORP TECHNOLOGIES | Hyderabad, IN\nSenior DevOps Engineer (Cloud Lead)   March 2021 – Present\nLead DevOps engineer responsible for cloud platform engineering and CI\/CD pipeline modernization for a mid-sized private banking firm processing 10M+ daily transactions on AWS.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tCloud Migration Strategy: Designed and executed migration of 200+ on-premise Java microservices to AWS EKS using Helm-based GitOps workflows with ArgoCD\n◦\tResult: Reduced infrastructure cost by 38% ($1.8M annual savings) and deployment lead time from 2 weeks to 4 hours.\n•\tHigh Availability Architecture: Architected multi-AZ Active-Passive failover for core banking APIs using AWS NLB, Route53 health checks, and RDS Multi-AZ instances\n◦\tResult: Achieved 99.98% uptime SLA, eliminating 6 unplanned outages per year that previously cost $200K each in penalties.\n•\tFinOps Governance: Implemented AWS Cost Anomaly Detection and Terraform Sentinel policies to enforce tagging standards and right-sizing recommendations across 12 AWS accounts\n◦\tResult: Identified $620,000 in annual waste within 3 months — orphaned EBS volumes, idle NAT Gateways, and oversized RDS instances.\n•\tDevSecOps Pipeline: Integrated Trivy container scanning, SonarQube SAST, and OWASP ZAP DAST into every Jenkins pipeline stage\n◦\tResult: Reduced production security incidents by 75% and passed RBI cybersecurity audit with zero critical findings.\n•\tTeam Enablement: Mentored 8 junior cloud engineers, ran bi-weekly knowledge sessions, and built a shared Terraform module library used across 5 product teams\n◦\tResult: Improved team onboarding time by 60% and reduced infrastructure provisioning errors by 90%.\nSWIFTRETAIL SOLUTIONS | Bengaluru, IN\nDevOps Engineer   August 2018 – February 2021\nCore DevOps contributor for a B2C e-commerce platform serving 5M+ daily users, responsible for CI\/CD toolchain and Kubernetes cluster management.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tClient: FashionMart India: Re-platformed a monolithic PHP application to containerized Node.js microservices on AWS ECS Fargate, deployed via GitHub Actions pipelines\n◦\tResult: Handled 500% Black Friday traffic spike (3M concurrent users) with zero downtime, reducing compute cost by 65%.\n•\tClient: QuickGrocer Pvt Ltd: Built an event-driven order processing pipeline using AWS SQS, Lambda, and DynamoDB Streams, replacing a brittle cron-based legacy system\n◦\tResult: Reduced order processing latency by 80% and eliminated 100+ weekly manual interventions by the operations team.\n•\tGitOps Transformation: Introduced ArgoCD-based GitOps for 150+ developer team, replacing manual kubectl deployments with declarative Helm chart management\n◦\tResult: Decreased Mean Time to Recovery (MTTR) from 3 hours to 12 minutes and increased deployment frequency by 400%.\n•\tMonitoring Overhaul: Migrated from Nagios to a Prometheus + Grafana + PagerDuty observability stack with SLO-based alerting for 40+ critical services\n◦\tResult: Reduced false-positive alerts by 80%, enabling the on-call team to respond to genuine incidents 3x faster.\nPINNACLE HEALTHTECH SERVICES | Chennai, IN\nCloud Infrastructure Engineer   June 2016 – July 2018\nManaged AWS cloud infrastructure and automation for a HIPAA-compliant healthcare SaaS provider serving 500+ hospitals.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tInfrastructure Automation: Built company's first Terraform-based infrastructure provisioning framework covering VPC, EC2, RDS, and IAM across dev\/staging\/prod environments\n◦\tResult: Reduced server provisioning time from 4 days to 30 minutes, eliminating configuration drift across environments.\n•\tContainer Adoption: Dockerized 25+ Python Django and Java Spring Boot applications and migrated from EC2 bare metal to Kubernetes (EKS v1.14)\n◦\tResult: Improved resource utilization by 55%, delaying a $400K data center capacity expansion by 24 months.\n•\tHIPAA Compliance Automation: Implemented AWS Config rules, CloudTrail, and Lambda auto-remediation to enforce HIPAA controls across 6 AWS accounts\n◦\tResult: Reduced manual compliance audit preparation from 5 weeks to 4 days per quarter, saving 200+ engineering hours annually.\nNETCORE SYSTEMS PVT LTD | Pune, IN\nLinux Systems Administrator   January 2015 – May 2016\nManaged on-premise RHEL infrastructure and virtualization for a regional IT services firm.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tVirtualization Migration: Executed P2V migration of 300+ RHEL 6\/7 servers to VMware vSphere 6.0 clusters\n◦\tResult: Reduced data center rack footprint by 25 racks, cutting power and cooling costs by $80K annually.\n•\tAutomation Scripting: Developed Python and Bash scripts for automated patching (via Ansible), user provisioning, and log rotation across 300+ servers\n◦\tResult: Saved 15 engineering hours per week, repurposed for strategic infrastructure upgrades.\nKEY PROJECTS & CASE STUDIES\n\nProject: \"Project Falcon\" — Kubernetes Platform Engineering\n•\tClient\/Employer: Horizon Bancorp Technologies\n•\tRole: Platform Lead Engineer\n•\tBudget: ₹2.8 Crore\n•\tDescription: Built a self-service internal developer platform (IDP) using Backstage.io backed by AWS EKS, enabling 200+ developers to provision ephemeral environments independently.\n•\tArchitecture: Multi-tenant EKS clusters with Namespace isolation, IRSA (IAM Roles for Service Accounts), Helm-based application templates, and ArgoCD ApplicationSets for automated environment lifecycle management.\n•\tOutcome: Developers can spin up fully configured test environments in 8 minutes without filing IT tickets. Increased developer productivity by 20% and eliminated 150+ monthly IT service requests.\nProject: \"Project Guardian\" — Automated Compliance & Security Framework\n•\tClient\/Employer: Horizon Bancorp Technologies\n•\tRole: Technical Lead\n•\tBudget: ₹90 Lakhs\n•\tDescription: Automated enforcement of RBI and PCI-DSS security controls across 12 AWS accounts using Policy-as-Code.\n•\tArchitecture: AWS Config custom rules (80+ controls), Lambda auto-remediation functions, Security Hub aggregation, and ServiceNow integration for audit trail generation and ticketing.\n•\tOutcome: Reduced manual audit preparation from 6 weeks to 3 days per quarter. Zero critical non-conformities in 2 consecutive RBI cybersecurity audits.\nProject: \"Project Phoenix\" — E-Commerce Platform Re-platforming\n•\tClient\/Employer: SwiftRetail Solutions (FashionMart India)\n•\tRole: Lead DevOps Engineer\n•\tBudget: ₹1.5 Crore\n•\tDescription: Complete infrastructure modernization from monolithic on-premise servers to cloud-native microservices architecture on AWS.\n•\tArchitecture: AWS ECS Fargate for containerized workloads, CloudFront CDN for static asset delivery, RDS Aurora for transactional data, ElastiCache Redis for session management, and GitHub Actions for CI\/CD.\n•\tOutcome: Successfully handled peak Black Friday load of 3M concurrent users with zero downtime. Reduced monthly infrastructure cost by 65% compared to previous EC2-based solution.\nLEADERSHIP & TEAM MANAGEMENT EXPERIENCE\n\n•\tAWS DevOps Guild Lead: Founded and lead the DevOps Community of Practice at Horizon Bancorp with 20+ engineers. Host monthly tech talks, maintain shared Terraform module registry, and set platform engineering standards.\n•\tMentorship Program: Established 1-on-1 mentoring for 8 junior cloud engineers. Guided 4 engineers through AWS Certified DevOps Engineer certification preparation — all 4 passed on first attempt.\n•\tHiring & Technical Interviews: Redesigned cloud engineering interview process with hands-on Terraform and Kubernetes scenario labs. Reduced mis-hires to zero and cut time-to-hire by 30%.\n•\tAgile Infrastructure: Transitioned cloud ops team from reactive ticket-based work to proactive sprint-based Kanban. Reduced unplanned work from 60% to under 20% of sprint capacity.\nPROCESS IMPROVEMENTS & AUTOMATION ACHIEVEMENTS\n\n•\t\"Zero-Touch Infrastructure Provisioning\": Created a self-service Backstage.io portal backed by Terraform Cloud and GitHub Actions. Developers provision VPCs, RDS instances, and S3 buckets via a web form.\n◦\tImpact: Reduced infrastructure provisioning lead time from 4 days to 25 minutes. Saved 120 engineering hours per month.\n•\t\"Automated DR Testing\": Replaced annual manual DR drills with continuous chaos engineering experiments using AWS Fault Injection Simulator (FIS) and Gremlin.\n◦\tImpact: Discovered and fixed 9 critical failover vulnerabilities that manual testing had missed over 3 years.\n•\t\"Secrets Management Overhaul\": Eliminated hardcoded credentials from 150+ repositories by integrating HashiCorp Vault with dynamic secret injection in all CI\/CD pipelines.\n◦\tImpact: Zero credential-related security incidents since implementation. Reduced secrets rotation effort from 20 hours\/month to fully automated.\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n•\tAWS Certified DevOps Engineer – Professional | Valid through 2026\n•\tAWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate (SAA-C03)\n•\tCertified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) | The Linux Foundation\n•\tHashiCorp Certified: Terraform Associate (003)\n•\tAWS Certified Cloud Practitioner\nEDUCATION\n\nBachelor of Technology in Computer Science & Engineering\nJawaharlal Nehru Technological University (JNTU), Hyderabad   Graduated: 2015\nTOOLS & TECHNOLOGIES\n\n•\tCloud: AWS, Microsoft Azure, Google Cloud Platform (GCP)\n•\tOperating Systems: RHEL\/CentOS 7\/8, Ubuntu 20.04\/22.04, Amazon Linux 2, Windows Server 2019\n•\tNetworking: VPC Design, VPN (Site-to-Site & Client), AWS Direct Connect, Security Groups, NACLs, ALB\/NLB, Route53\n•\tVersion Control: Git, GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, AWS CodeCommit\n•\tProject Management: Jira, Confluence, ServiceNow, Trello, Azure Boards\n•\tCollaboration: Slack, Microsoft Teams, Zoom, Google Workspace\nPUBLICATIONS & CONFERENCES\n\n•\tSpeaker, AWS Community Day Hyderabad 2023: Session: \"GitOps at Scale — Managing 200+ Microservices with ArgoCD.\"\n•\tArticle: \"Terraform at Enterprise Scale — Module Design Patterns That Actually Work\" — Published on dev.to (2022). 15K+ views.\n•\tInternal Tech Talk: \"Zero Trust Networking in AWS — From VPC Design to Service Mesh\" — Presented to 80+ engineers at Horizon Bancorp (2023).\n•\tOpen Source Contribution: Maintained terraform-aws-eks-platform module on GitHub with 400+ stars.\n","label":[[0,19,"PERSON_NAME"],[20,65,"JOB_TITLE"],[66,86,"LOCATION"],[91,122,"EMAIL"],[127,143,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[147,182,"LINKEDIN"],[220,244,"JOB_TITLE"],[249,251,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[292,302,"SKILL"],[319,339,"SKILL"],[343,346,"SKILL"],[370,391,"SKILL"],[392,403,"SKILL"],[412,429,"SKILL"],[452,473,"SKILL"],[529,540,"SKILL"],[555,565,"SKILL"],[565,575,"SKILL"],[581,591,"SKILL"],[620,624,"SKILL"],[642,659,"SKILL"],[714,729,"SKILL"],[735,743,"SKILL"],[743,755,"SKILL"],[844,867,"SKILL"],[869,892,"SKILL"],[893,907,"SKILL"],[909,926,"SKILL"],[949,960,"SKILL"],[961,962,"SKILL"],[962,965,"SKILL"],[967,977,"SKILL"],[986,1003,"SKILL"],[1005,1023,"SKILL"],[1025,1041,"SKILL"],[1073,1090,"SKILL"],[1092,1100,"SKILL"],[1109,1115,"SKILL"],[1117,1131,"SKILL"],[1133,1139,"SKILL"],[1141,1163,"SKILL"],[1165,1172,"SKILL"],[1181,1201,"SKILL"],[1219,1237,"SKILL"],[1239,1256,"SKILL"],[1258,1273,"SKILL"],[1275,1294,"SKILL"],[1341,1355,"SKILL"],[1357,1375,"SKILL"],[1377,1393,"SKILL"],[1394,1413,"SKILL"],[1413,1446,"SKILL"],[1494,1498,"SKILL"],[1499,1502,"SKILL"],[1504,1507,"SKILL"],[1509,1515,"SKILL"],[1517,1519,"SKILL"],[1521,1524,"SKILL"]