{"id":84,"text":"DEEPAK VARMA\nSenior Azure Cloud Architect & Enterprise Integration Specialist\nPune, Maharashtra  |  deepak.varma.azure@cloudmail.com  |  +91 76543 21098  |  linkedin.com\/in\/deepakvarma-azure-arch\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nSeasoned Azure Cloud Architect with 10+ years of progressive experience designing enterprise-scale cloud platforms, integration solutions, and data engineering pipelines on Microsoft Azure. Expert in Azure Integration Services (Logic Apps, API Management, Service Bus), Azure Data Platform (Synapse Analytics, Data Factory, Databricks), and enterprise migration strategies. Demonstrated success leading multi-million dollar cloud transformation programs for pharmaceutical, manufacturing, and energy sector clients. Azure Solutions Architect Expert and Microsoft Certified Trainer (MCT), passionate about enabling digital transformation through cloud-native architectures.\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n\n•\tCloud Strategy & Architecture: Azure Landing Zone Design, Enterprise Scale Architecture, Cloud Adoption Framework (CAF), Well-Architected Framework (WAF), Multi-Cloud Strategy\n•\tIntegration Architecture: Azure API Management, Logic Apps, Service Bus, Event Grid, Azure Functions, Enterprise Service Bus (ESB) Modernization\n•\tData Platform Engineering: Azure Synapse Analytics, Azure Data Factory, Databricks (PySpark), Data Lakehouse Architecture, Real-Time Analytics\n•\tSecurity & Governance: Azure Active Directory (Entra ID), Conditional Access, Defender for Cloud, Policy-as-Code (Azure Policy), GDPR\/ISO 27001 Compliance\n•\tLeadership & Delivery: Program Management, Stakeholder Engagement, Architecture Review Boards, Pre-Sales Technical Advisory, Delivery Governance\nTECHNICAL SKILLS INVENTORY\n\n•\tCloud Platform: Microsoft Azure (100+ services), AWS (secondary — EC2, S3, RDS), Google Cloud Platform (GKE, BigQuery)\n•\tAzure Integration Services: Azure API Management (APIM), Logic Apps (Standard & Consumption), Azure Service Bus, Event Grid, Event Hubs, Azure Functions, Durable Functions\n•\tAzure Data Services: Azure Synapse Analytics, Azure Data Factory (ADF v2), Azure Databricks, Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2, Azure Purview, Stream Analytics\n•\tContainerization & DevOps: Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS), Azure Container Apps, Azure Container Registry, Azure DevOps (Pipelines, Repos, Boards), GitHub Actions\n•\tInfrastructure as Code: Bicep, ARM Templates, Terraform (Azure Provider), Azure CLI, PowerShell DSC, Azure Blueprints\n•\tDatabases & Analytics: Azure SQL Database, Cosmos DB (multi-model), Azure Database for PostgreSQL, SQL Data Warehouse, Power BI, Azure Analysis Services\n•\tSecurity & Identity: Azure Active Directory \/ Entra ID, Azure Key Vault, Managed Identities, RBAC, Defender for Cloud, Microsoft Sentinel (SIEM), PIM (Privileged Identity Management)\n•\tLanguages & Scripting: Python, C# (.NET 6\/8), PowerShell, Bash, T-SQL, PySpark, KQL (Kusto Query Language), YAML\/JSON\/Bicep\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nMERIDIAN ENERGY CORP | Pune, IN\nSenior Azure Cloud Architect (Principal Level)   April 2020 – Present\nPrincipal architect leading Azure cloud strategy and platform engineering for a diversified energy conglomerate with operations across 8 Indian states, managing generation, transmission, and distribution assets worth $2B+.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tAzure Enterprise Landing Zone: Architected and deployed an Azure Enterprise Landing Zone (CAF-compliant) with Management Group hierarchy, centralized logging, and policy enforcement across 15 Azure subscriptions\n◦\tResult: Achieved ISO 27001 certification within 6 months of platform deployment. Reduced security policy violations by 95% through automated Azure Policy enforcement.\n•\tSCADA Data Integration Platform: Designed a real-time OT\/IT data integration platform using Azure Event Hubs, Stream Analytics, and Databricks to ingest telemetry from 5,000+ IoT sensors across power substations\n◦\tResult: Enabled real-time grid fault detection, reducing power outage response time from 4 hours to 18 minutes. Prevented estimated $4M in annual energy theft losses through anomaly detection.\n•\tCloud Cost Optimization: Implemented Azure Cost Management governance framework with Bicep-enforced resource tagging, Azure Advisor automation, and Reserved Instance purchasing strategy\n◦\tResult: Reduced annual Azure spend by ₹3.2 Crore (28%) within 12 months through right-sizing, reserved capacity, and elimination of orphaned resources.\n•\tAPI Modernization Program: Replaced 45 point-to-point SOAP integrations with a unified Azure API Management gateway with self-service developer portal for 12 partner organizations\n◦\tResult: Reduced integration failure rate by 85%, onboarding time for new partners from 6 weeks to 3 days, and exposed 60+ APIs generating ₹1.5 Crore in new B2B revenue.\n•\tDisaster Recovery Architecture: Designed Azure Site Recovery (ASR) and geo-redundant backup strategy for 200+ VMs across primary (Pune) and DR (Hyderabad) Azure regions\n◦\tResult: Achieved RTO of 45 minutes and RPO of 15 minutes for critical systems, passing regulatory DR audit with zero gaps.\nNOVACURE PHARMACEUTICALS | Mumbai, IN\nAzure Cloud Solutions Architect   January 2017 – March 2020\nLead Azure architect for digital transformation programs at a mid-sized pharmaceutical company, modernizing clinical trial data management and manufacturing execution systems.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tClinical Trial Data Lake: Architected a GDPR-compliant Azure Data Lakehouse using ADLS Gen2, Azure Data Factory, and Databricks to consolidate clinical trial data from 15 CRO partners\n◦\tResult: Reduced data consolidation time from 3 weeks to 4 hours per trial phase, accelerating drug approval submission timelines by 2 months per study.\n•\tClient: GlobalChem Ingredients: Designed SAP-to-Azure integration using Logic Apps and Azure Service Bus to sync ERP master data with a cloud-based quality management system (Veeva Vault)\n◦\tResult: Eliminated 200+ hours of monthly manual data reconciliation. Achieved 99.9% data consistency between SAP and Veeva across 50,000+ batch records.\n•\tAzure DevOps Transformation: Migrated 300+ developers from on-premise TFS\/SVN to Azure DevOps with Git repositories, multi-stage YAML pipelines, and Artifactory integration\n◦\tResult: Deployment frequency increased from monthly to daily. MTTR reduced from 8 hours to 35 minutes across all application teams.\n•\tRegulatory Compliance Framework: Implemented 21 CFR Part 11 compliance controls using Azure AD Conditional Access, Key Vault, Azure Monitor, and Immutable Blob Storage for audit trails\n◦\tResult: Passed US FDA inspection with zero electronic records compliance findings — first time in company's 20-year history.\nSKYBRIDGE TELECOM SOLUTIONS | Hyderabad, IN\nAzure Developer & Cloud Engineer   August 2014 – December 2016\nCloud developer for a regional telecom operator's BSS\/OSS modernization program, migrating legacy billing and CRM systems to Azure.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tAzure Migration: Migrated 120+ VMs from on-premise VMware to Azure IaaS using Azure Migrate, optimizing VM sizing and storage tiers during lift-and-shift\n◦\tResult: Reduced datacenter CAPEX by ₹1.8 Crore in first year. Reduced VM provisioning time from 2 weeks to 2 hours.\n•\tAzure Functions Integration: Built serverless ETL microservices using Azure Functions (Durable Functions for orchestration) to process 500K+ daily CDRs (Call Detail Records) for revenue assurance\n◦\tResult: Eliminated 6-hour nightly batch window, enabling real-time fraud detection and reducing revenue leakage by 15%.\n•\tMonitoring Implementation: Implemented Azure Monitor, Application Insights, and Log Analytics Workspaces for 80+ Azure resources with custom KQL dashboards and PagerDuty alerting\n◦\tResult: MTTR improved from 6 hours to 45 minutes. Proactive monitoring caught 12 performance degradations before customer impact.\nDATABRIDGE TECHNOLOGIES | Pune, IN\n.NET Developer \/ Cloud Trainee   June 2013 – July 2014\nJunior developer building .NET web applications and early Azure PaaS deployments.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tAzure PaaS Adoption: Migrated two .NET MVC applications from IIS on-premise to Azure App Service and Azure SQL Database\n◦\tResult: Reduced hosting costs by 60% and eliminated weekend patching downtime.\n•\tApplication Development: Built inventory management module using C# ASP.NET MVC, Entity Framework, and SQL Server for a manufacturing client\n◦\tResult: Replaced manual Excel tracking for 10,000+ SKUs, reducing inventory discrepancies by 70%.\nKEY PROJECTS & CASE STUDIES\n\nProject: \"Project Omega\" — Real-Time Grid Intelligence Platform\n•\tClient\/Employer: Meridian Energy Corp\n•\tRole: Chief Azure Architect\n•\tBudget: ₹4.2 Crore\n•\tDescription: Built an end-to-end IoT data analytics platform to process telemetry from 5,000+ smart meters and substation sensors for grid fault detection and energy theft prevention.\n•\tArchitecture: Azure IoT Hub for device ingestion, Azure Event Hubs Kafka-compatible endpoint for high-throughput streaming, Azure Stream Analytics for real-time anomaly detection, Databricks ML for predictive fault modeling, Azure Synapse Analytics for historical analysis, Power BI Embedded for operational dashboards.\n•\tOutcome: Power outage response time reduced from 4 hours to 18 minutes. Detected and prevented $4M in annual energy theft. Platform processes 50M+ sensor readings per day with sub-second latency.\nProject: \"Project Genesis\" — Clinical Trial Data Lakehouse\n•\tClient\/Employer: NovaCure Pharmaceuticals\n•\tRole: Lead Architect\n•\tBudget: ₹2.1 Crore\n•\tDescription: Designed a GDPR-compliant, unified data lakehouse consolidating clinical trial data from 15 Contract Research Organizations (CROs) for regulatory submission.\n•\tArchitecture: Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2 with Delta Lake format, Azure Data Factory for CRO data ingestion (50+ connectors), Azure Databricks for data curation and quality validation (Great Expectations), Azure Purview for data catalog and lineage, Azure Synapse Analytics for statistical analysis queries.\n•\tOutcome: Consolidated data processing time from 3 weeks to 4 hours. Accelerated drug approval submission by average of 2 months per study. First trial data submission approved by CDSCO without revision requests.\nProject: \"Project Fortress\" — Enterprise Security & Compliance Automation\n•\tClient\/Employer: Meridian Energy Corp\n•\tRole: Technical Lead\n•\tBudget: ₹85 Lakhs\n•\tDescription: Implemented an automated security governance framework enforcing ISO 27001 and Indian CERT-In guidelines across 15 Azure subscriptions.\n•\tArchitecture: Azure Policy (180+ custom policies), Defender for Cloud with regulatory compliance dashboards, Microsoft Sentinel SIEM with custom KQL detection rules, Logic Apps for automated remediation workflows, and ServiceNow integration for incident management.\n•\tOutcome: Achieved ISO 27001 certification in 6 months. Security policy compliance rate improved from 43% to 98.5%. Automated remediation handles 85% of policy violations without human intervention.\nLEADERSHIP & TEAM MANAGEMENT EXPERIENCE\n\n•\tAzure Center of Excellence Lead: Founded and lead Meridian Energy's Azure CoE — 15 cloud engineers setting architectural standards, managing Azure governance, and driving cloud skill development across 4 BUs.\n•\tMicrosoft Certified Trainer (MCT): Deliver AZ-104 (Administrator) and AZ-305 (Solutions Architect) training programs to internal teams and external clients. Trained 200+ engineers across 3 organizations.\n•\tPre-Sales Architecture Advisory: Partner with business development teams to craft cloud transformation proposals and ROI models for enterprise accounts. Supported 5 deals totaling ₹12 Crore in consulting contracts.\n•\tMentorship & Career Development: Mentored 10 junior Azure engineers through structured cloud learning plans. 7 achieved Azure Solutions Architect Associate certification within their first year.\nPROCESS IMPROVEMENTS & AUTOMATION ACHIEVEMENTS\n\n•\t\"Azure Landing Zone as Code\": Developed a reusable Bicep template library for Azure Enterprise Landing Zone deployment covering Networking, Governance, Security, and Monitoring — deployable in 2 hours.\n◦\tImpact: Reduced new project Azure environment setup from 4 weeks to 1 day. Adopted by 3 client organizations as standard template.\n•\t\"Automated Cost Governance\": Built an Azure Cost Management automation framework using Azure Functions and Logic Apps that emails right-sizing recommendations weekly to resource owners.\n◦\tImpact: Achieved ₹3.2 Crore (28%) annual cost reduction with zero manual FinOps team effort after initial setup.\n•\t\"Self-Healing Infrastructure\": Implemented Azure Event Grid + Logic Apps auto-remediation workflows for 25 common infrastructure health events (e.g., stopped VMs, expired certs, full disks).\n◦\tImpact: Reduced Level-1 support tickets by 60%. Platform self-heals from 85% of common infrastructure incidents without human intervention.\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n•\tMicrosoft Certified: Azure Solutions Architect Expert (AZ-305) | Valid through 2026\n•\tMicrosoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate (AZ-104)\n•\tMicrosoft Certified: Azure Data Engineer Associate (DP-203)\n•\tMicrosoft Certified Trainer (MCT) | Valid through 2025\n•\tHashiCorp Certified: Terraform Associate\n•\tTOGAF 9.2 Certified — Enterprise Architecture Framework\nEDUCATION\n\nMaster of Technology in Cloud Computing & Distributed Systems\nSymbiosis Institute of Technology (SIT), Pune   Graduated: 2014\nBachelor of Engineering in Information Technology\nPune University (SPPU), Pune   Graduated: 2012\nTOOLS & TECHNOLOGIES\n\n•\tCloud: Microsoft Azure (primary), AWS (EC2, S3, EKS), Google Cloud Platform (GKE, BigQuery)\n•\tOperating Systems: Windows Server 2019\/2022, Ubuntu 20.04\/22.04, RHEL 8, Azure Arc-enabled servers\n•\tNetworking: Azure Virtual Network, VPN Gateway, ExpressRoute, Azure Firewall, NSGs, Private Endpoints, Traffic Manager, Front Door\n•\tMonitoring & ITSM: Azure Monitor, Application Insights, Log Analytics, Microsoft Sentinel, ServiceNow, PagerDuty\n•\tCollaboration & Project Mgmt: Azure DevOps (Boards, Repos, Pipelines), Jira, Confluence, Microsoft Teams, SharePoint Online, Power Platform\n•\tData & BI Tools: Power BI Desktop\/Service, Azure Synapse Studio, Databricks Notebooks, Azure Data Studio, SSMS\nPUBLICATIONS & CONFERENCES\n\n•\tSpeaker, Microsoft Azure Global Bootcamp Pune 2023: Session: \"Azure Landing Zones — From Design to Production in 30 Days.\"\n•\tSpeaker, Data & AI Summit India 2022: Session: \"Building GDPR-Compliant Data Lakehouses on Azure for Pharma Research.\"\n•\tArticle: \"Azure vs AWS for Enterprise Integration — An Architect's Honest Comparison\" — Published on TechTarget\/SearchCloudComputing (2022). 20K+ views.\n•\tMicrosoft Tech Community Blog: \"Implementing CERT-In Compliant Security on Azure — A Practical Guide\" (2023). Featured in Microsoft Azure India newsletter.\n","label":[[0,12,"PERSON_NAME"],[13,77,"JOB_TITLE"],[78,96,"LOCATION"],[100,133,"EMAIL"],[136,153,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[157,195,"LINKEDIN"],[228,249,"JOB_TITLE"],[255,258,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[335,356,"SKILL"],[392,407,"SKILL"],[419,436,"SKILL"],[447,457,"SKILL"],[458,473,"SKILL"],[475,486,"SKILL"],[488,508,"SKILL"],[510,527,"SKILL"],[528,541,"SKILL"],[543,553,"SKILL"],[693,706,"SKILL"],[734,760,"SKILL"],[772,782,"SKILL"],[801,804,"SKILL"],[864,890,"SKILL"],[912,942,"SKILL"],[943,969,"SKILL"],[971,1000,"SKILL"],[1001,1017,"SKILL"],[1017,1027,"SKILL"],[1034,1060,"SKILL"],[1068,1088,"SKILL"],[1091,1103,"SKILL"],[1117,1137,"SKILL"],[1138,1149,"SKILL"],[1151,1162,"SKILL"],[1164,1174,"SKILL"],[1176,1191,"SKILL"],[1217,1220,"SKILL"],[1222,1235,"SKILL"],[1238,1263,"SKILL"],[1264,1288,"SKILL"],[1290,1308,"SKILL"],[1310,1321,"SKILL"],[1322,1329,"SKILL"],