{"id":85,"text":"MANJULA SRINIVASAN\nSenior Java Full Stack Developer & Microservices Architect\nBengaluru, Karnataka  |  manju.srinivasan.dev@codemail.com  |  +91 87654 32109  |  linkedin.com\/in\/manjula-srinivasan-java\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n\nAccomplished Senior Java Full Stack Developer with 9+ years of experience architecting and delivering enterprise-grade web applications, RESTful APIs, and cloud-native microservices. Deep expertise in Spring Boot ecosystem, React.js front-end development, and AWS cloud deployment. Proven track record of leading agile development teams of 10–15 engineers, modernizing legacy systems, and designing scalable distributed architectures for clients in insurance, telecom, and fintech sectors. Passionate about clean code principles, test-driven development (TDD), and domain-driven design (DDD).\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n\n•\tBackend Engineering: Microservices Design, Spring Boot\/Cloud, RESTful & GraphQL API Design, Event-Driven Architecture, Domain-Driven Design (DDD)\n•\tFrontend Development: React.js, Redux, TypeScript, Angular 14+, Material UI, Responsive Design, Web Performance Optimization\n•\tCloud & DevOps: AWS Deployment (EC2, EKS, Lambda, RDS), Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins CI\/CD, GitLab Pipelines\n•\tData Engineering: PostgreSQL Schema Design, MongoDB Document Modeling, Redis Caching Strategy, Kafka Event Streaming, ETL Pipelines\n•\tQuality Engineering: TDD\/BDD, JUnit 5, Mockito, Selenium, Cucumber, JMeter Performance Testing, SonarQube Code Quality\nTECHNICAL SKILLS INVENTORY\n\n•\tLanguages: Java 11\/17, TypeScript, JavaScript (ES6+), Python (scripting), SQL, HTML5\/CSS3\n•\tFrameworks & Libraries: Spring Boot 3.x, Spring Cloud (Eureka, Gateway, Config), Spring Security, Hibernate\/JPA, React.js, Angular, Redux Toolkit\n•\tCloud & Containerization: AWS (EC2, EKS, RDS, Lambda, S3, SQS, API Gateway, Cognito), Docker, Kubernetes, Helm, AWS Fargate\n•\tMessaging & Streaming: Apache Kafka, RabbitMQ, AWS SQS\/SNS, Spring Kafka, ActiveMQ\n•\tDatabases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, Oracle 19c, MongoDB, Redis, DynamoDB, Elasticsearch, Flyway (DB Migrations)\n•\tCI\/CD & Testing: Jenkins, GitLab CI\/CD, Maven, Gradle, JUnit 5, Mockito, Selenium WebDriver, Cucumber, JMeter\n•\tAPI & Integration: REST, GraphQL, gRPC, SOAP (Legacy), OpenAPI 3.0\/Swagger, Postman, WireMock\n•\tObservability & Security: ELK Stack, Splunk, Zipkin\/Sleuth Tracing, OAuth 2.0, JWT, Keycloak, OWASP Top 10 Remediation\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n\nQUANTUM DYNAMICS INSURANCE | Bengaluru, IN\nSenior Java Full Stack Developer (Tech Lead)   February 2021 – Present\nTechnical lead for a team of 12 developers building a next-generation policy management and claims processing platform for one of India's top-5 private insurance providers, handling 2M+ active policies.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tMicroservices Modernization: Led decomposition of a monolithic Java EE application into 18 Spring Boot microservices with event-driven communication via Apache Kafka\n◦\tResult: Reduced release cycle from quarterly to weekly, improved system resilience — single service failure no longer cascades to entire platform.\n•\tClaims Processing Engine: Designed and built a high-throughput claims adjudication engine processing 50,000+ claims daily using Spring Batch and PostgreSQL partitioning\n◦\tResult: Reduced average claims processing time from 7 days to 4 hours, saving $1.2M annually in manual review costs.\n•\tReact.js Customer Portal: Architected a fully responsive React.js + TypeScript customer self-service portal with Redux state management and AWS Cognito authentication\n◦\tResult: Increased digital self-service adoption from 20% to 68%, reducing call center volume by 35% and saving $800K annually.\n•\tAPI Gateway Consolidation: Implemented Spring Cloud Gateway as a unified API gateway with rate limiting, circuit breakers (Resilience4j), and JWT-based auth for 18 downstream services\n◦\tResult: Reduced API latency by 40% and eliminated 500+ weekly support tickets caused by direct service-to-service coupling failures.\n•\tCode Quality Initiative: Introduced SonarQube with quality gates, JUnit 5 with 80%+ coverage mandate, and Mutation Testing (PITest) for the entire development team\n◦\tResult: Reduced production defect rate by 65% over 12 months. Zero critical security vulnerabilities in last 2 VAPT assessments.\nBLUESTONE LOGISTICS TECH | Chennai, IN\nJava Developer \/ Full Stack Engineer   September 2018 – January 2021\nCore developer for a real-time shipment tracking and warehouse management platform serving 200+ enterprise logistics clients across South and South-East Asia.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tClient: AsiaPac Freight Services: Built a real-time shipment tracking API using Spring WebFlux (reactive programming), WebSockets, and Redis pub\/sub for tracking 80,000+ active consignments\n◦\tResult: Reduced shipment status query latency from 3 seconds to 120ms (p99), enabling the client to launch a premium real-time tracking product.\n•\tClient: MegaWare Distribution: Developed a Warehouse Management System (WMS) front-end using Angular 12 with barcode scanner integration (Zebra SDK) and offline-first PWA capabilities\n◦\tResult: Warehouse picking accuracy improved from 92% to 99.7%, reducing mis-shipment losses by $500K annually.\n•\tKafka Event Streaming: Designed and implemented event streaming architecture using Apache Kafka to decouple 12 logistics domain services (Order, Inventory, Dispatch, Billing)\n◦\tResult: Eliminated point-to-point API dependencies, reducing integration failures by 90% and enabling independent service deployments.\n•\tPerformance Optimization: Identified and resolved N+1 query issues in Hibernate ORM and implemented multi-level caching strategy (Caffeine L1 + Redis L2) for product catalog APIs\n◦\tResult: Reduced database CPU load by 55% and improved API response times by 300% for the 10 most-used catalog endpoints.\nTECHNOVA SYSTEMS PVT LTD | Hyderabad, IN\nJava Developer   July 2016 – August 2018\nDeveloped enterprise web applications and RESTful APIs for telecom billing and CRM solutions serving 3 regional telecom operators.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tBilling Module Development: Built a revenue assurance and invoice generation module using Spring Boot, JPA, and Oracle 19c processing 500K+ monthly subscriber bills\n◦\tResult: Eliminated billing discrepancies worth $200K\/month that were caused by race conditions in the legacy system.\n•\tLegacy Migration: Migrated a SOAP-based web service integration layer to RESTful APIs using Spring REST and OpenAPI 3.0 specifications\n◦\tResult: Reduced third-party integration onboarding time from 3 weeks to 3 days.\n•\tTest Automation: Introduced JUnit 5 + Mockito unit testing and Selenium WebDriver E2E testing for a previously untested 50K LOC codebase\n◦\tResult: Achieved 75% code coverage within 6 months, preventing 3 major production incidents during subsequent feature releases.\nINFOBRIDGE SOLUTIONS | Hyderabad, IN\nJunior Java Developer   June 2015 – June 2016\nDeveloped Java EE web applications for a mid-sized IT services firm.\nKey Responsibilities & Achievements:\n•\tModule Development: Developed employee self-service HR portal modules (leave management, payroll view) using JSP, Servlets, and MySQL\n◦\tResult: Reduced HR admin workload by 30% through employee self-service capabilities.\n•\tDatabase Optimization: Rewrote 40+ slow SQL queries and added indexed views for a reporting module\n◦\tResult: Reduced monthly report generation time from 45 minutes to 4 minutes.\nKEY PROJECTS & CASE STUDIES\n\nProject: \"Project Clarity\" — Claims Processing Microservices Platform\n•\tClient\/Employer: Quantum Dynamics Insurance\n•\tRole: Technical Lead & Architect\n•\tBudget: ₹3.5 Crore\n•\tDescription: End-to-end modernization of a legacy claims adjudication system built on Java EE\/Oracle Forms into a cloud-native microservices platform on AWS EKS.\n•\tArchitecture: 18 Spring Boot 3.x microservices communicating via Kafka topics, Spring Cloud Gateway for API routing, PostgreSQL with table partitioning for claims data, Elasticsearch for full-text claims search, and React.js dashboard for claims officers.\n•\tOutcome: Claims processing time reduced from 7 days to 4 hours. Platform processes 50,000+ claims daily with 99.97% uptime. Annual savings of $1.2M in manual processing costs.\nProject: \"Project Horizon\" — Real-Time Logistics Visibility Platform\n•\tClient\/Employer: BluStone Logistics Tech (AsiaPac Freight)\n•\tRole: Senior Developer\n•\tBudget: ₹1.8 Crore\n•\tDescription: Built a real-time shipment visibility platform integrating GPS telemetry, EDI messages from 50+ carriers, and IoT sensor data into a unified tracking dashboard.\n•\tArchitecture: Spring WebFlux reactive backend for high-concurrency tracking streams, WebSockets for real-time browser updates, Redis Pub\/Sub for event fanout, Google Maps API for geospatial visualization, Kafka for carrier event ingestion.\n•\tOutcome: Platform tracks 80,000+ active consignments in real-time. Client launched a premium tracking SLA product generating $3M in additional annual revenue.\nProject: \"Project Shield\" — Automated Security & Code Quality Pipeline\n•\tClient\/Employer: Quantum Dynamics Insurance\n•\tRole: Tech Lead\n•\tBudget: ₹60 Lakhs\n•\tDescription: Implemented a comprehensive DevSecOps pipeline integrating code quality gates, dependency vulnerability scanning, and DAST testing into all 18 microservice CI\/CD pipelines.\n•\tArchitecture: SonarQube with custom quality gate rules, OWASP Dependency-Check, Trivy container scanning, OWASP ZAP DAST, and GitLab CI integration with mandatory quality gate enforcement before merge.\n•\tOutcome: Reduced production security incidents by 80%. Zero critical vulnerabilities in 2 consecutive IRDAI regulatory audits. Production defect escape rate dropped from 12% to 2%.\nLEADERSHIP & TEAM MANAGEMENT EXPERIENCE\n\n•\tEngineering Team Lead: Led agile development team of 12 engineers at Quantum Dynamics — ran daily standups, sprint planning, code reviews, and quarterly performance assessments.\n•\tArchitecture Review Board: Member of the Architecture Review Board (ARB) at Quantum Dynamics, reviewing technical designs for 5 product teams and enforcing microservices best practices.\n•\tMentorship Program: Mentored 6 junior developers through structured learning plans covering Spring Boot, system design, and clean code principles. Three promoted to Senior Developer within 18 months.\n•\tTech Community Contribution: Organized monthly internal Java Meetups (JUG Bengaluru chapter at company level) covering topics like Reactive Programming, Virtual Threads (Java 21), and DDD patterns.\nPROCESS IMPROVEMENTS & AUTOMATION ACHIEVEMENTS\n\n•\t\"API Contract-First Development\": Mandated OpenAPI 3.0 specification-first approach for all new microservices using Swagger Codegen for server stub generation.\n◦\tImpact: Reduced API integration mismatches by 90% and enabled parallel front-end and back-end development, cutting feature delivery time by 30%.\n•\t\"Automated Database Migrations\": Introduced Flyway for versioned database schema migrations integrated into CI\/CD pipeline, replacing manual DBA-executed scripts.\n◦\tImpact: Eliminated deployment failures caused by database schema drift — 0 schema-related outages in 18 months post-implementation.\n•\t\"Performance Regression Testing\": Integrated JMeter performance tests into GitLab CI pipeline to detect regressions on every merge request for critical API endpoints.\n◦\tImpact: Detected and prevented 4 performance regressions before they reached production, each of which would have caused SLA breaches.\nCERTIFICATIONS\n\n•\tOracle Certified Professional: Java SE 11 Developer\n•\tAWS Certified Developer – Associate (DVA-C02)\n•\tSpring Professional Certification (VMware\/Broadcom)\n•\tMongoDB Certified Developer Associate\n•\tCertified Scrum Developer (CSD) | Scrum Alliance\nEDUCATION\n\nMaster of Computer Applications (MCA)\nBangalore University, Bengaluru   Graduated: 2015\nBachelor of Science in Computer Science\nMysore University, Mysore   Graduated: 2013\nTOOLS & TECHNOLOGIES\n\n•\tIDEs & Build: IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, VS Code, Maven, Gradle, npm, Webpack\n•\tDatabases: PostgreSQL, MySQL, Oracle 19c, MongoDB, Redis, DynamoDB, Elasticsearch\n•\tOperating Systems: Ubuntu 20.04\/22.04, macOS, Windows 10\/11, Amazon Linux 2\n•\tAPI Tools: Postman, Insomnia, Swagger UI, WireMock, REST Assured\n•\tVersion Control: Git, GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, Git Flow branching strategy\n•\tProject Management: Jira, Confluence, Trello, Azure DevOps Boards, Notion\nPUBLICATIONS & CONFERENCES\n\n•\tSpeaker, Java User Group (JUG) Bengaluru 2023: Session: \"Spring Boot 3 + Virtual Threads — Real-World Performance Benchmarks.\"\n•\tArticle: \"From Monolith to Microservices — Lessons from a 2M Policy Insurance Platform\" — Published on Medium (2022). 8K+ reads.\n•\tInternal Whitepaper: \"Domain-Driven Design in Practice — A Case Study from Insurance Claims Processing\" — Distributed to 3 product teams at Quantum Dynamics.\n•\tOpen Source: Contributor to spring-boot-microservices-starter template on GitHub.\n","label":[[0,18,"PERSON_NAME"],[19,77,"JOB_TITLE"],[78,98,"LOCATION"],[102,137,"EMAIL"],[140,158,"PHONE_NUMBER"],[161,199,"LINKEDIN"],[237,269,"JOB_TITLE"],[275,278,"EXPERIANCE_YEARS"],[361,373,"SKILL"],[407,421,"SKILL"],[424,436,"SKILL"],[447,457,"SKILL"],[484,505,"SKILL"],[537,543,"SKILL"],[580,607,"SKILL"],[684,691,"SKILL"],[754,777,"SKILL"],[779,782,"SKILL"],[789,810,"SKILL"],[811,814,"SKILL"],[837,857,"SKILL"],[859,879,"SKILL"],[881,892,"SKILL"],[893,898,"SKILL"],[900,908,"SKILL"],[910,928,"SKILL"],[929,955,"SKILL"],[957,978,"SKILL"],[986,1006,"SKILL"],[1007,1016,"SKILL"],[1018,1023,"SKILL"],[1025,1035,"SKILL"],[1037,1048,"SKILL"],[1050,1061,"SKILL"],[1063,1080,"SKILL"],[1081,1110,"SKILL"],[1121,1127,"SKILL"],[1129,