{"id":86,"text":"SRINU\nSenior DevOps Engineer & AWS Cloud Specialist\n\nHyderabad, Telangana | srinu.devops@techmail.com | +91 98765 43210\nlinkedin.com\/in\/srinu-devops\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\n------------------------------------------------------------\nResults-driven Senior DevOps Engineer with 8+ years of hands-on experience designing, \nautomating, and optimizing cloud infrastructure on AWS.\n\nProven ability to lead CI\/CD transformation initiatives, reduce deployment cycles, and \nimplement robust monitoring frameworks for high-traffic production environments.\n\nExpertise in Kubernetes orchestration, Terraform automation, and DevSecOps practices \nserving clients in BFSI, healthcare, and e-commerce domains.\n\nPassionate about building resilient, cost-efficient cloud platforms that empower \ndevelopment teams to ship faster with greater confidence.\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCORE COMPETENCIES\n------------------------------------------------------------\n• Cloud Infrastructure: AWS Architecture Design, Multi-Account Strategy, VPC Networking, \n  Cost Optimization, Landing Zone Setup\n\n• Automation & IaC: Terraform Modules, Ansible Playbooks, AWS CloudFormation, GitOps \n  Workflows, Self-Healing Infrastructure\n\n• CI\/CD Engineering: Jenkins Pipelines, GitHub Actions, ArgoCD, Blue-Green Deployments, \n  Canary Releases, Rollback Automation\n\n• Observability: SLO\/SLA Monitoring, Alerting Strategy, Log Aggregation, Distributed \n  Tracing, Incident Management\n\n• Security & Compliance: IAM Governance, Secrets Management, VAPT Remediation, PCI-DSS \n  Controls, Vulnerability Scanning Automation\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nTECHNICAL SKILLS INVENTORY\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCloud Platforms:\nAWS (EC2, EKS, Lambda, S3, RDS, Route53, CloudFront, SQS, SNS, IAM, CloudWatch)\nAzure (AKS, App Services, DevOps Pipelines)\n\nContainerization & Orchestration:\nDocker, Kubernetes, Helm, Kustomize, Istio, ECS, Fargate\n\nInfrastructure as Code:\nTerraform, AWS CloudFormation, Ansible, AWS CDK, Packer\n\nCI\/CD Tools:\nJenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI\/CD, ArgoCD, CodePipeline, CodeBuild, Spinnaker\n\nDatabases & Storage:\nPostgreSQL, MySQL, DynamoDB, Redis, MongoDB, S3, EFS\n\nMonitoring:\nPrometheus, Grafana, Datadog, CloudWatch, ELK Stack, PagerDuty, Jaeger\n\nProgramming:\nPython, Bash, PowerShell, Go, YAML, JSON\n\nSecurity:\nHashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, SonarQube, Trivy, GuardDuty, Security Hub\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\nPROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nHORIZON BANCORP TECHNOLOGIES | Hyderabad, India\nSenior DevOps Engineer (Cloud Lead) | March 2021 – Present\n\n• Led cloud platform engineering and CI\/CD modernization for a banking system \n  processing 10M+ daily transactions\n\nKey Achievements:\n• Migrated 200+ microservices to AWS EKS using GitOps\n  → Reduced costs by 38% ($1.8M annually)\n  → Reduced deployment time from 2 weeks to 4 hours\n\n• Designed high availability architecture (Multi-AZ failover)\n  → Achieved 99.98% uptime SLA\n\n• Implemented FinOps governance\n  → Identified $620K annual savings\n\n• Built DevSecOps pipelines (Trivy, SonarQube, OWASP ZAP)\n  → Reduced security incidents by 75%\n\n• Mentored 8 engineers\n  → Reduced onboarding time by 60%\n\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\nSWIFTRETAIL SOLUTIONS | Bengaluru, India\nDevOps Engineer | August 2018 – February 2021\n\n• Managed CI\/CD and Kubernetes for large-scale e-commerce platform\n\nKey Achievements:\n• Migrated monolith to microservices (ECS Fargate)\n  → Handled 3M users with zero downtime\n  → Reduced cost by 65%\n\n• Built event-driven architecture using SQS, Lambda\n  → Reduced latency by 80%\n\n• Implemented GitOps (ArgoCD)\n  